\v 23 \x + \xo 2:23: \xt Mrk 1:24; Luk 2:39; Yhn 1:45.\x*Once he got there, he settled into the town of \nd NazarethВҰ969\nd*, so that what had been spokenВҰ973 throughВҰ975 the prophetsВҰ977 would be fulfilledВҰ971: вҖңHe'll be called a Nazarene.вҖқ\f + \fr 2:23 \ft This is not a specific quote from the Hebrew Scriptures, but note that Matthew does say вҖҳthe prophet\bd s\bd*вҖҷ (not вҖҳthe prophetвҖҷ). This could be: В№A play on Hebrew вҖҳЧ ЧҰЧЁвҖҷ from Yeshayah (Isaiah) 11:1 where вҖҳbranch/shootвҖҷ (netser) is similar to вҖҳNatsaretвҖҷ (Nazareth/natsrat), ВІa play on Shamshon (Samson) the вҖҳNaziriteвҖҷ (Ч Ц°Ч–ЦҙЧҷЧЁ) from Heroes (Judges) 13:5,7, or Віjust a slur on Yeshua being from insignificant Nazareth as per Yohan (John) 1:46.\f*
