\v 5 \add People from\add* Yerushalem and all YudeaВҰ1066 and all of the regionsВҰ1070 surroundingВҰ1070 the YordanВҰ1072 River went out \add into the wilderness\add* to \add listen to\add* Yohan,
\v 6 and many confessedВҰ1081 theirВҰ1084 sinsВҰ1083 and asked himВҰ1080 to immerseВҰ1074 them in the river.
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 3:7: \xt Mat 12:34; 23:33.\x*But when Yohan saw many from the partyВҰ1089 of the Pharisees and from the Sadducee sect coming for immersionВҰ1095, he told them, вҖңYou brood of snakes, who warnedВҰ1102 you to flee from \add God's\add* severeВҰ1108 angerВҰ1108 that's coming?
\v 8 Turning from your sins should be accompanied by evidence that you've changed.
\v 9 \x + \xo 3:9: \xt Yhn 8:33.\x*And don'tВҰ1118 think that you can just tell yourselvesВҰ1122 that you're descendants of Abraham, becauseВҰ1128 I can tell you that \nd GodВҰ1133\nd* could turn theseВҰ1137 stonesВҰ1136 into descendants of Abraham.
\v 10 \x + \xo 3:10: \xt Mat 7:19.\x*The axeВҰ1147 has alreadyВҰ1143 been placed at the base of the treesВҰ1152 ready to cut down any treeВҰ1156 that's not producingВҰ1158 goodВҰ1160 fruitВҰ1159, andВҰ1162 thenВҰ1144 it'll be thrownВҰ1166 into the fireВҰ1165.
\v 11 I'm immersing people in waterВҰ1174 as a sign that they're turning away from their sins, but there's another one comingВҰ1182 afterВҰ1180 me who's greater than meвҖ”so much so that I'm not even worthyВҰ1189 to carry his sandalsВҰ1191. He'll immerse you in the holy \nd spiritВҰ1197\nd* and fireВҰ1200.
