\rem /s1 The Calling of the First Disciples; The First Disciples; Jesus Calls the First Disciples; Jesus Calls Four Fishermen
\r (Mark 1:16-20; Luke 5:1-11)
\p
\v 18 As he walked besideВҰ1658 Lake GalileeВҰ1662, he saw two brothersВҰ1665, SimonВҰ1666 (later nicknamed PeterВҰ1670) andВҰ1655 AndrewВҰ1672, throwing their netВҰ1677 into the sea becauseВҰ1682 they were fishermenВҰ1683.
\v 19 вҖң\wj Come and follow me,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua told them, вҖң\wj and I'll make youВҰ1692 fishersВҰ1694 of peopleВҰ1695.\wj*вҖқ
\v 20 SoВҰ1697 theyВҰ1703 left their netsВҰ1701 immediatelyВҰ1698 andВҰ1697 followedВҰ1703 afterВҰ1704 himВҰ1704.
\p
\v 21 Going on a bit further, he sawВҰ1708 two otherВҰ1709 brothersВҰ1711, Yacob and Yohan, in the boatВҰ1725 getting their netsВҰ1733 ready along with their fatherВҰ1729 ZebedeeВҰ1715, and Yeshua also calledВҰ1736 the two of them.
\v 22 SoВҰ1739 theyВҰ1749 too immediatelyВҰ1740 left the boatВҰ1743 and theirВҰ1748 fatherВҰ1747 and followedВҰ1749 afterВҰ1750 himВҰ1750.
\s1 Yeshua's healing is very popular
\rem /s1 The Ministry of Jesus in Galilee; Jesus Teaches, Preaches, and Heals; Jesus Heals the Sick; Jesus Ministers to Crowds of People
\r (Luke 6:17-19)
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 4:23: \xt Mat 9:35; Mrk 1:39.\x*ThenВҰ1751 \nd YeshuaВҰ1755\nd* went aroundВҰ1752 all of GalileeВҰ1762, teachingВҰ1765 in theirВҰ1771 JewishВҰ1770 meetingВҰ1770 hallsВҰ1770 and proclaimingВҰ1774 the goodВҰ1776 messageВҰ1776 about the kingdomВҰ1778, and healingВҰ1780 all the people'sВҰ1788 diseasesВҰ1782 and sicknessesВҰ1785,
\v 24 andВҰ1789 the newsВҰ1794 about this wentВҰ1791 all the way up to SyriaВҰ1800.
\v 25 Large crowdsВҰ1828 from GalileeВҰ1832 and DecapolisВҰ1834 and Yerushalem, and from all of YudeaВҰ1838 and even beyondВҰ1840 the YordanВҰ1842 River, followedВҰ1826 afterВҰ1827 Yeshua.
\c 5
\s1 Yeshua's sermon on the hillside
\rem /s1 The Sermon on the Mount; The Beatitudes
\r (Luke 6:20-23)
\p
\v 1 After seeing all the crowdsВҰ1846, Yeshua climbed up a hill, andВҰ1844 when he satВҰ1852 down, hisВҰ1858 apprenticesВҰ1857 approachedВҰ1854 him
\rem /s1 The Beatitudes
\v 2 andВҰ1859 he taughtВҰ1864 them:
\rem /s1 True Happiness
\rem /r (Luke 6.20-23)
\p
\v 3 вҖң\wj Those who are poor in the spiritВҰ1872 are blessed, becauseВҰ1873 the heavenlyВҰ1879 kingdomВҰ1877 is theirs.\wj*
\p
\v 4 \x + \xo 5:4: \xt Isa 61:2.\x*вҖң\wj Those who are mourningВҰ1882 are blessed, becauseВҰ1884 theyВҰ1885 will be comfortedВҰ1886.\wj*
\p
\v 5 \x + \xo 5:5: \xt Psa 37:11.\x*вҖң\wj Those who are gentleВҰ1889 are blessed, becauseВҰ1890 theyВҰ1891 will inheritВҰ1892 the earthВҰ1894.\wj*
\p
\v 6 \x + \xo 5:6: \xt Isa 55:1-2.\x*вҖң\wj Those who are hungry andВҰ1898 thirstyВҰ1899 to obey God are blessed, becauseВҰ1902 theyВҰ1903 will be satisfiedВҰ1904.\wj*
\p
\v 7 вҖң\wj Those who are mercifulВҰ1907 are blessed, becauseВҰ1908 theyВҰ1909 will receive mercyВҰ1910.\wj*
\p
\v 8 \x + \xo 5:8: \xt Psa 24:3.\x*вҖң\wj Those who have pure heartsВҰ1915 are blessed, becauseВҰ1916 theyВҰ1917 will see \+nd GodВҰ1919\+nd*.\wj*
\p
\v 9 вҖң\wj Those who are peacemakersВҰ1923 are blessed, becauseВҰ1924 theyВҰ1925 will be calledВҰ1928 \+nd God\+nd*'s children.\wj*
\p
\v 10 \x + \xo 5:10: \xt 1Pe 3:14.\x*вҖң\wj Those who are persecutedВҰ1931 for being godly are blessed, becauseВҰ1935 the heavenlyВҰ1942 kingdomВҰ1940 belongs to them.\wj*
\p
\v 11 \x + \xo 5:11: \xt 1Pe 4:14.\x*вҖң\wj Everyone who's deridedВҰ1947 or chased or lied about is blessed, along with those who have evilВҰ1956 things said about them just because they \+add follow\+add* me.\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 5:12: \xt 2Ch 36:16; Acts 7:52.\x*\wj Be happy andВҰ1967 praising \+add God\+add* because you'll all have a wonderful rewardВҰ1971 in the heavensВҰ1977, because \+add in the past\+add* theyВҰ1981 also persecutedВҰ1981 the prophetsВҰ1983 like thatВҰ1984.\wj*
\s1 Being salt and light
\rem /s1 Teaching about Salt and Light
\r (Mark 9:50; Luke 14:34-35)
\p
\v 13 \x + \xo 5:13: \xt Mrk 9:50; Luk 14:34-35.\x*вҖң\wj You \add people\add* are the earth'sВҰ1993 salt, but if the salt is made tastelessВҰ1999, what would you use to salt your food? The salt wouldn't be useful for anything anymoreВҰ2007 and would just get thrownВҰ2011 out and trampledВҰ2014 on by the people.\wj*
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 5:14: \xt Yhn 8:12; 9:5.\x*вҖң\wj You are the world'sВҰ2023 lightВҰ2021. A cityВҰ2026 up on a hill can'tВҰ2024 be hiddenВҰ2027.\wj*
\v 15 \x + \xo 5:15: \xt Mrk 4:21; Luk 8:16; 11:33.\x*\wj No one lights a lamp and puts it underВҰ2037 a basketВҰ2040вҖ”you put it on a lampstandВҰ2044 and it lightens up the houseВҰ2051.\wj*
\v 16 \x + \xo 5:16: \xt 1Pe 2:12.\x*\wj In the same way, let your lightВҰ2055 shineВҰ2053 in front of everyoneВҰ2059, so thatВҰ2072 theyВҰ2061 can seeВҰ2061 your goodВҰ2064 behaviour andВҰ2066 then might praise your fatherВҰ2069 in the heavensВҰ2075.\wj*
\s1 Mosheh's law won't be broken
\rem /s1 The Law and the Prophets; The Fulfillment of the Law; Teaching about the Law
\p
\v 17 вҖң\wj Don't imagine that I came to criticise the prophetsВҰ2085 or \+add Mosheh's\+add* instructions. I didn'tВҰ2076 come to oppose \+add the scriptures\+add*, but to fulfilВҰ2090 them,\wj*
\v 18 \x + \xo 5:18: \xt Luk 16:17.\x*\wj becauseВҰ2092 I can assure youВҰ2094 all that until heavenВҰ2099 andВҰ2100 earthВҰ2102 reach their end, not one letter or mark will be taken away from those instructions until everything is fulfilled.\wj*
\v 19 \wj ThereforeВҰ2121 anyone who breaksВҰ2122 even a minor commandВҰ2126, and teaches others to do the same, will be seen as one of the least in the heavenlyВҰ2141 kingdom, but anyone who practicesВҰ2145 and teaches those instructions will be considered outstanding in the kingdom.\wj*
\v 20 \wj Let me tell all of you, unless you're more godly than the religiousВҰ2169 teachersВҰ2169 and the Pharisees, there's no way that you'll get to enter the heavenlyВҰ2179 kingdomВҰ2177.\wj*
\s1 Teaching about murder and anger
\rem /s1 Murder; Teaching about Anger; Concerning Anger
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj You've all heardВҰ2180 that your ancestors were told not to murder, because any murderer will be sentenced.\wj*\x + \xo 5:21: \xt Exo 20:13; Deu 5:17.\x*
\v 22 \wj But I'm telling you thatВҰ2202 anyone who gets angry at another will be liable for judgementВҰ2212, and anyone who calls another person a numbskull will have to face the court, and if you call them a fool, you're liable for hellfire.\wj*
\v 23 \wj SoВҰ2239 if you're thereВҰ2248 at the altarВҰ2247 to offerВҰ2240 yourВҰ2244 giftВҰ2243 and remember that someone has somethingВҰ2257 againstВҰ2258 you,\wj*
\v 24 \wj leaveВҰ2260 your gift thereВҰ2261 at the altarВҰ2267 and go and sort that out firstВҰ2270, beforeВҰ2265 coming back to offerВҰ2279 your gift.\wj*
\p
\v 25 вҖң\wj Resolve things with your opponent as soon as you can, hopefully while you'reВҰ2292 still on the wayВҰ2297 \+add to the court\+add*, in case your opponent turns you in to the judge, and the judge to the officer, and then you'll end up in prisonВҰ2318.\wj*
\v 26 \wj I can assure you that you won'tВҰ2324 get out of prison untilВҰ2327 the fine is completely paid.\wj*
\s1 Teaching about adultery and lust
\rem /s1 Concerning Adultery; Teaching about Adultery
\p
\v 27 вҖң\wj You all know that \+add the scriptures\+add* say not to commitВҰ2340 adulteryВҰ2340,\wj*\x + \xo 5:27: \xt Exo 20:14; Deu 5:18.\x*
\v 28 \wj butВҰ2342 I'm telling you thatВҰ2347 if you look at a womanВҰ2349 lustfully then you've alreadyВҰ2355 committedВҰ2356 adulteryВҰ2356 in your mindВҰ2360.\wj*
\v 29 \wj If yourВҰ2367 rightВҰ2369 eyeВҰ2366 is causing you to stumbleВҰ2371, thenВҰ2364 pluckВҰ2373 it out andВҰ2364 throwВҰ2376 it away,\wj*\x + \xo 5:29: \xt Mat 18:9; Mrk 9:47.\x*
\v 30 \wj and if your rightВҰ2402 hand is causing you to stumbleВҰ2405, cut it off and throwВҰ2411 it away, becauseВҰ2415 it's better for you that one of your \+add вүҲbody partsВҰ2421\+add* would \+add вүҲbe taken than for\+add* your whole body to \+add вүҲend up in the judgement fire\+add*.\wj*\x + \xo 5:30: \xt Mat 18:8; Mrk 9:43.\x*
\s1 Teaching about divorce
\rem /s1 Concerning Divorce; Teaching about Divorce
\r (Mat. 19:9; Mark 10:11-12; Luke 16:18)
\p
\v 31 \x + \xo 5:31: \xt Deu 24:1-4; Mat 19:7; Mrk 10:4.\x*вҖң\wj It's saidВҰ2434 that any man can divorceВҰ2446 hisВҰ2443 wifeВҰ2442 just by sending herВҰ2445 away.\wj*
\v 32 \x + \xo 5:32: \xt Mat 19:9; Mrk 10:11-12; Luk 16:18; 1Cor 7:10-11.\x*\wj But I'm telling you all that anyone who sends hisВҰ2460 wife away, exceptВҰ2461 in the case where she's committed sexualВҰ2463 immoralityВҰ2463, is causing her to commit adultery, and anyone who marries a wife that's been sent away is causing \+add her\+add* to commit adultery.\wj*
\s1 Teaching about oaths and honesty
\rem /s1 Teaching about Vows; Concerning Oaths
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 5:33: a \xt Lev 19:12; \xo b \xt Num 30:2; Deu 23:21.\x*вҖң\wj Also, you've heardВҰ2478 that itВҰ2480 was saidВҰ2480 to our ancestors that you shouldn'tВҰ2483 break yourВҰ2492 oath, but you must do whatever you promised to \+nd YahwehВҰ2489\+nd*.\wj*
\v 34 \x + \xo 5:34: a \xt Jam 5:12; \xo b \xt Isa 66:1; Mat 23:22.\x*\wj But I'm telling youВҰ2496 not to make oaths in the first placeвҖ”don'tВҰ2497 swearВҰ2498 by heavenВҰ2503 becauseВҰ2504 it's God's throneВҰ2505,\wj*
\v 35 \x + \xo 5:35: a \xt Isa 66:1; \xo b \xt Psa 48:2.\x*\wj nor by the earthВҰ2512 because it's God's footrest, nor by Yerushalem because it's the supreme king's cityВҰ2523.\wj*
\v 36 \wj And don'tВҰ2536 swearВҰ2534 by yourВҰ2533 own strength, becauseВҰ2535 you can'tВҰ2536 even make one strand of hair grow a different colour.\wj*
\v 37 \wj Just say вҖҳyesвҖҷ when you commit to doing something, and вҖҳnoвҖҷ when you don't, because going beyond that is \+add actually\+add* evilВҰ2563.\wj*
\s1 Teaching about being taken advantage of
\rem /s1 Concerning Retaliation; Teaching about Revenge; An Eye for an Eye
\r (Luke 6:29-30)
\p
\v 38 \x + \xo 5:38: \xt Exo 21:24; Lev 24:20; Deu 19:21.\x*вҖң\wj You'veВҰ2568 all heardВҰ2565 it said that it's an eye for an eye and a tooth for a tooth,\wj*
\v 39 \wj butВҰ2576 I'm telling you not to resistВҰ2580 those who want to hurt you. If someone slaps you on your rightВҰ2591 cheek, turnВҰ2595 your left cheek towards them,\wj*
\v 40 \wj and to the person suing you in court and claiming your robe, let them have your coatВҰ2618 as well.\wj*
\v 41 \wj And if someone forces youВҰ2622 to walk a mile, walk twoВҰ2634 miles with them.\wj*
\v 42 \wj Give whatever others requestВҰ2636 from you, and don'tВҰ2649 turn away from anyone who wants to borrowВҰ2648 from you.\wj*
\s1 Love your enemies
\rem /s1 Teaching about Love for Enemies
\r (Luke 6:27-28,32-36)
\p
\v 43 вҖң\wj You've all heardВҰ2651 itВҰ2653 saidВҰ2653 that you should love your neighbourВҰ2656 and hate your enemyВҰ2662,\wj*
\v 44 \wj butВҰ2665 I'm telling you to love yourВҰ2672 enemiesВҰ2671 and to pray for anyone who's persecutingВҰ2692 you,\wj*
\v 45 \wj so that you might becomeВҰ2695 children of yourВҰ2699 fatherВҰ2698 in the heavensВҰ2703, becauseВҰ2704 he causes hisВҰ2707 sunВҰ2706 to rise on both evilВҰ2710 and goodВҰ2712 people, and sends the rain for both godlyВҰ2716 and ungodly people.\wj*
\v 46 \wj If you \add people\add* just love people who love you, what rewardВҰ2726 would you expect for that? Don't \+add even\+add* the taxВҰ2732 collectorsВҰ2732 do that?\wj*
\v 47 \wj And if you're only polite to yourВҰ2743 own circle, how is that achieving anything? Aren't non-Jews just the sameВҰ2755?\wj*
\v 48 \x + \xo 5:48: \xt Lev 19:2; Deu 18:13.\x*\wj Instead you should all \+add aim to\+add* be perfect just like yourВҰ2766 heavenlyВҰ2772 fatherВҰ2765 is perfect.\wj*
\c 6
\s1 Giving to the poor
\rem /s1 Giving to the Needy; Concerning Almsgiving; Teaching about Charity; Teaching about Giving to the Needy
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 6:1: \xt Mat 23:5.\x*вҖң\wj \add You peopleВҰ2786 should\add* take care not to \+add only\+add* obey God in front of others so they'll think well of you, because if you do, you'll certainly get no rewardВҰ2795 from yourВҰ2781 fatherВҰ2800 in the heavensВҰ2805.\wj*
\p
\v 2 вҖң\wj SoВҰ2807 when you're giving to the poor, don'tВҰ2811 make a big display of it like the hypocritesВҰ2817 do in the meetingВҰ2821 hallsВҰ2821 and in the streetsВҰ2825 so they'll get the people'sВҰ2830 praises. I can assure you that they've already receivedВҰ2835 theirВҰ2838 rewardВҰ2837 in full.\wj*
\v 3 \wj But when you give to the poor, don'tВҰ2843 let your left hand know what your rightВҰ2851 hand is doing,\wj*
\v 4 \wj so that your givingВҰ2873 will be private, yet your fatherВҰ2865 who sees everything you do will give back to you.\wj*
\s1 Teaching about praying
\rem /s1 Concerning Prayer; Teaching about Prayer; Teaching about Prayer and Fasting
\r (Luke 11:2-4)
\p
\v 5 \x + \xo 6:5: \xt Luk 18:10-14.\x*вҖң\wj Whenever you pray, don'tВҰ2882 be like the hypocritesВҰ2888 who love to pray in the meetingВҰ2894 hallsВҰ2894 andВҰ2878 on street cornersВҰ2898 so everyoneВҰ2909 will notice them. I can assure you that they've already receivedВҰ2914 theirВҰ2917 rewardВҰ2916 in full.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Instead, when you pray, go into a privateВҰ2927 room and shut the doorВҰ2932, then pray to your father who's not visible to you. Then your father who sees everything will reward you.\wj*
\p
\v 7 вҖң\wj And when youВҰ2960 do pray, don'tВҰ2959 babbleВҰ2960 \+add away\+add* like people of other religions who think they'll be listenedВҰ2973 to just because of how much they pray.\wj*
\v 8 \wj There'sВҰ2975 no need to be like them, becauseВҰ2979 \+nd GodВҰ2981\+nd* your fatherВҰ2983 already knows your needs beforeВҰ2988 you even ask himВҰ2993.\wj*
\v 9 \wj SoВҰ2997 pray like this:\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳOurВҰ3001 fatherВҰ3000 in the heavensВҰ3006,\wj*
\q1 \wj we want yourВҰ3010 nameВҰ3009 to be honoured \+add forever\+add*.\wj*
\q1
\v 10 \wj We want your kingdomВҰ3013 to come\wj*
\q1 \wj and your plans to be fulfilled here on earthВҰ3025 just like they are in heavenВҰ3021.\wj*
\q1
\v 11 \wj Give us \+add everything\+add* we need todayВҰ3034\wj*
\q1
\v 12 \wj andВҰ3035 write off what we owe \+add you\+add*\wj*
\q1 \wj as we also write off what others owe us.\wj*
\q1
\v 13 \wj Don't bring us to \+add the point of\+add* being temptedВҰ3058,\wj*
\q1 \wj butВҰ3059 keep us away from doing evilВҰ3064 things.вҖҷ\wj*
\m
\v 14 \x + \xo 6:14-15: \xt Mrk 11:25-26.\x*вҖң\wj BecauseВҰ3081 if you \add people\add* forgive other people's wrongs, then your heavenlyВҰ3097 fatherВҰ3094 will also forgive your wrongs.\wj*
\v 15 \wj But if you don'tВҰ3100 forgive other people'sВҰ3103 wrongs, then your fatherВҰ3109 won'tВҰ3100 forgive your wrongs either.\wj*
\s1 Teaching about fasting
\rem /s1 Concerning Fasting
\p
\v 16 вҖң\wj Whenever you \add peopleВҰ3139\add* are abstaining from food, don'tВҰ3121 look miserable like the hypocritesВҰ3126, becauseВҰ3129 they intentionally try to look awful so that everyoneВҰ3139 will notice that they're fasting. I can assure you that they've already receivedВҰ3146 theirВҰ3135 rewardВҰ3148 in full.\wj*
\v 17 \wj Instead, when you fast, comb your hair and wash your faceВҰ3160\wj*
\v 18 \wj so that no one will realise that you're fastingВҰ3170, other than your father who's not visible to you. Then your father who sees everything will reward you.\wj*
\s1 Wealth in heaven
\rem /s1 Treasures in Heaven; Concerning Treasures; Teaching about Money and Possessions; Riches in Heaven
\r (Luke 12:33-34)
\p
\v 19 \x + \xo 6:19: \xt Jam 5:2-3.\x*вҖң\wj Don't amass wealth for yourselves here on earthВҰ3203, where insects and corrosionВҰ3207 destroyВҰ3208 things, and where it can be stolen.\wj*
\v 20 \wj Instead, store your wealth in heavenВҰ3222, where there's no destructiveВҰ3229 insects or corrosionВҰ3228 or thievesВҰ3232 \+add or scammers\+add*,\wj*
\v 21 \wj becauseВҰ3239 whereverВҰ3238 your wealth is, your values will also be focussed thereВҰ3245.\wj*
\s1 The eyes
\rem /s1 The Light of the Body; The Sound Eye
\r (Luke 11:34-36)
\p
\v 22 вҖң\wj YourВҰ3265 eyes are your body's lamps, so if your eyes are healthyВҰ3266, then your entire body will be brightВҰ3272.\wj*
\v 23 \wj But if your eyes are evilВҰ3280, your entireВҰ3282 bodyВҰ3284 will be dark.\wj*
\s1 God and wealth
\rem /s1 Serving Two Masters; God and Possessions
\r (Luke 16:13; 12:22-31)
\p
\v 24 вҖң\wj No one can serve twoВҰ3303 mastersВҰ3304, becauseВҰ3308 they'll eitherВҰ3307 hate one and like the other one, or else will support one and despiseВҰ3322 the other. So you \add people\add* can'tВҰ3323 serve both \+nd GodВҰ3325\+nd* and moneyВҰ3328.\wj*
\rem /s1 Do Not Worry
\p
\v 25 вҖң\wj So that's why I'm telling you all not to worryВҰ3334 about yourВҰ3338 \+add worldly\+add* lifeвҖ”\+add things like\+add* what you'll eat or drinkВҰ3344, or how you look and what you'll wear. Isn't life more than food, and the body more than clothingВҰ3362?\wj*
\v 26 \wj Think about the birdsВҰ3366 in the skyВҰ3368вҖ”they don'tВҰ3388 plant seeds or harvest crops or gatherВҰ3375 grain into barnsВҰ3378, but it's yourВҰ3382 heavenlyВҰ3384 fatherВҰ3381 who feeds them. Aren't each of you worth more than them?\wj*
\v 27 \wj Who can add an hourВҰ3404 to their lifetime by worryingВҰ3397?\wj*
\p
\v 28 вҖң\wj Why would youВҰ3410 worryВҰ3410 aboutВҰ3407 clothesВҰ3408? Look how the flowers grow in the fieldsВҰ3415вҖ”they don'tВҰ3419 work or make fabric,\wj*
\v 29 \x + \xo 6:29: \xt 1Ki 10:4-7; 2Ch 9:3-6.\x*\wj butВҰ3426 I can tell youВҰ3427 that not even \+add King\+add* SolomonВҰ3430 at the peak of hisВҰ3435 reign was dressed as well as the flowers.\wj*
\v 30 \wj So if \+nd GodВҰ3457\+nd* dressesВҰ3459 the plants in the fieldsВҰ3446 that are here todayВҰ3447 and thrownВҰ3455 away tomorrowВҰ3452, won'tВҰ3460 he care much more for you, you people with littleВҰ3464 faithВҰ3464?\wj*
\p
\v 31 вҖң\wj That means that youВҰ3467 \add people\add* don'tВҰ3465 need to worryВҰ3467 about having anything to eatВҰ3470 or drinkВҰ3473, or having clothesВҰ3476 to wear.\wj*
\v 32 \wj People with no trust in God try to obtain all those things, but yourВҰ3492 heavenlyВҰ3494 fatherВҰ3491 \+add already\+add* knows that you need these things.\wj*
\v 33 \wj So instead youВҰ3517 should be striving \+add to enter God's\+add* kingdomВҰ3504 and to be guiltless in hisВҰ3512 eyes, and then all theseВҰ3514 other things will just follow.\wj*
\v 34 \wj Don't worry about tomorrow, becauseВҰ3525 tomorrow can worry about itselfВҰ3529вҖ”today's problems are enough by themselves.\wj*
\c 7
\s1 Teaching about judging
\rem /s1 Judging Others; Don't Condemn Others
\r (Luke 6:37-38,41-42)
\p
\v 1 вҖң\wj Don't judge \+add others\+add*, so that youВҰ3541 won'tВҰ3537 be judgedВҰ3541 yourselves,\wj*
\v 2 \x + \xo 7:2: \xt Mrk 4:24.\x*\wj becauseВҰ3544 you'll all be judgedВҰ3547 in the same way that you judge others. Whatever standard you use on others will be the same standard used on you.\wj*
\v 3 \wj And why are you lookingВҰ3558 at the speck in another person's eye when you have a massive lump in yourВҰ3567 own eye?\wj*
\v 4 \wj How could you say to them, вҖҳLet me get the speckВҰ3590 out of your eye,вҖҷ when the lump is still in your eye?\wj*
\v 5 \wj What a hypocrite! First get the lump out of yourВҰ3612 own eye, and then you'll be able to see clearlyВҰ3617 so that you can help them with their eye.\wj*
\rem /s1 Profaning the Holy
\p
\v 6 вҖң\wj Don't giveВҰ3629 special things to dogs, and don'tВҰ3628 throwВҰ3635 pearlsВҰ3637 to pigs, because they'll all just trampleВҰ3644 them underfoot, and then they're just as likely to turn and attackВҰ3652 you.\wj*
\s1 Requesting, searching, and knocking
\rem /s1 Effective Prayer; Ask, Search, Knock; Ask, Seek, Knock
\r (Luke 11:9-13)
\p
\v 7 вҖң\wj Make your requestsВҰ3654, and they'll be givenВҰ3656 to you. Keep lookingВҰ3658, and you'll find it. Knock \+add on doors\+add*, and they'll be openedВҰ3663.\wj*
\v 8 \wj Everyone who asks for something will get something, and everyone who searches for something will find something, and the door will be openedВҰ3678 for everyone who knocksВҰ3677.\wj*
\v 9 \wj If you have a child thatВҰ3681 asks for something to eat, whichВҰ3681 of you would give them a stoneВҰ3696?\wj*
\v 10 \wj Or if the child asked for some fishВҰ3703, who would give them a snake?\wj*
\v 11 \wj SoВҰ3711 if evilВҰ3713 people know how to give good giftsВҰ3716 to their childrenВҰ3720, how much more will yourВҰ3721 fatherВҰ3725 in the heavensВҰ3730 give good things to those who ask him?\wj*
\rem /s1 The Golden Rule
\p
\v 12 \x + \xo 7:12: \xt Luk 6:31.\x*вҖң\wj SoВҰ3737 in every area, whatever you'd like others to do for you, that's how you \add peopleВҰ3746\add* should be treating them. That's \add what Mosheh's\add* instructions and the prophets' \add writings were about\add*.\wj*
\s1 The wide and narrow gates
\rem /s1 The Narrow and Wide Gates; The Narrow Gate
\r (Luke 13:24)
\p
\v 13 вҖң\wj Come in through the narrowВҰ3763 gate, becauseВҰ3765 there's a big gateway and a wide pathВҰ3772 that leads away to destructionВҰ3777, and lots of people go that way.\wj*
\v 14 \wj The gateway leadingВҰ3796 away to lifeВҰ3799 is narrow, and the pathВҰ3794 has been kept narrow, and not many people find itВҰ3805.\wj*
\s1 Recognising the tree by the fruit
\rem /s1 The Tree and Its Fruit; A Tree and Its Fruit
\r (Luke 6:43-44)
\p
\v 15 вҖң\wj Watch out for falseВҰ3810 prophetsВҰ3810 who come to youВҰ3814 in sheep'sВҰ3817 clothingВҰ3816, butВҰ3819 insideВҰ3818 they're swindlingВҰ3822 wolvesВҰ3821.\wj*
\v 16 \wj You \add people\add* will know who theyВҰ3830 are if you observe theirВҰ3826 fruitВҰ3825. Does anyone pick grapesВҰ3833 from thornВҰ3832 bushes, or figsВҰ3838 from thistlesВҰ3837?\wj*
\v 17 \wj Similarly, everyВҰ3840 good tree produces good fruit, but the bad tree produces evil fruit.\wj*
\v 18 \wj A good tree can't produce bad fruit, and a bad tree can't produce good fruit.\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 7:19: \xt Mat 3:10; Luk 3:9.\x*\wj EveryВҰ3869 treeВҰ3870 that doesn't produceВҰ3872 goodВҰ3874 fruitВҰ3873 will be chopped down andВҰ3876 thrownВҰ3879 into the fireВҰ3878.\wj*
\v 20 \x + \xo 7:20: \xt Mat 12:33.\x*\wj So then, you'll know the false teachers by observing theirВҰ3886 fruitВҰ3885.\wj*
\s1 Words need actions
\rem /s1 Concerning Self-Deception; I Never Knew You; True Disciples
\r (Luke 13:25-27)
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj Not everyoneВҰ3890 who goes around calling me вҖҳmasterвҖҷ will enter the heavenlyВҰ3901 kingdomsВҰ3899вҖ”only those who \+add actually\+add* do what myВҰ3911 fatherВҰ3910 who lives in the heavens wants.\wj*
\v 22 \wj Many people will complain on \+add judgement\+add* dayВҰ3929 sayingВҰ3924, вҖҳ\+nd MasterВҰ3930\+nd*, master, didn'tВҰ3933 we prophesyВҰ3937 using your name, and exorcise demonsВҰ3942 using your name, and do many miraclesВҰ3950 using your name?вҖҷ\wj*
\v 23 \x + \xo 7:23: \xt Psa 6:8.\x*\wj ThenВҰ3953 I'll have to tell them, вҖҳI don't even know you. Go away from me, all of you whose behaviour is against \+add God's\+add* laws.вҖҷ\wj*
\s1 The importance of foundations
\rem /s1 The Wise and Foolish Builders; The Two House Builders; Hearers and Doers; Building on a Solid Foundation
\r (Luke 6:47-49)
\p
\v 24 вҖң\wj ThereforeВҰ3969 anyone who hears theseВҰ3975 messagesВҰ3974 of mine andВҰ3976 puts them into practice, theyВҰ3979 can be likenedВҰ3979 to a sensible person who builtВҰ3985 their houseВҰ3988 on the rockВҰ3992.\wj*
\v 25 \wj When the rains started and the floodsВҰ4000 came and the windsВҰ4004 blew and battered that houseВҰ4011, it was stable becauseВҰ4017 its foundation was the rockВҰ4020.\wj*
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj ButВҰ4021 anyone who hears theseВҰ4029 messagesВҰ4028 of mine andВҰ4021 doesn't put them into practice, they can be likenedВҰ4034 to a stupid person who builtВҰ4038 their houseВҰ4041 on the sand.\wj*
\v 27 \wj When the rains started and the floodsВҰ4053 came and the windsВҰ4057 blew and battered that houseВҰ4062, it collapsed with a loud crash.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's authority
\rem /s1 The Authority of Jesus
\p
\v 28 \x + \xo 7:28-29: \xt Mrk 1:22; Luk 4:32.\x*When \nd Yeshua\nd* had finishedВҰ4076 sharing all theseВҰ4081 messagesВҰ4080, the crowdsВҰ4084 were astonishedВҰ4082 at hisВҰ4088 teachingВҰ4087
\v 29 becauseВҰ4092 he taughtВҰ4093 like someone who had authorityВҰ4096, and not like theirВҰ4103 \add regular\add* religiousВҰ4102 teachersВҰ4093.
\c 8
\s1 Yeshua heals a man with leprosy
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Man; Jesus Cleanses a Leper; Jesus Heals a Man with Leprosy; Miracles and teaching; The Man With Leprosy
\r (Mark 1:40-45; Luke 5:12-16)
\p
\v 1 When Yeshua came down from the hillside, a large crowdВҰ4117 followedВҰ4115 him,
\v 2 and thenВҰ4119 a man with leprosy approachedВҰ4122 him and knelt down in front of him and asked, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ4127\nd*, if you're willingВҰ4129, you're able to get rid of this disease.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 вҖң\wj I am willingВҰ4143,\wj*вҖқ said Yeshua as he stretchedВҰ4134 out hisВҰ4148 handВҰ4136 \add andВҰ4133 commanded\add*, вҖң\wj Be clean.\wj*вҖқ The leprosyВҰ4150 disappeared immediatelyВҰ4146
\v 4 \x + \xo 8:4: \xt Lev 14:1-32.\x*and \nd Yeshua\nd* told himВҰ4154, вҖң\wj Make sure thatВҰ4170 you don't tell anyoneВҰ4158 \+add about this\+add* but you do need to go and show yourselfВҰ4162 to the priestВҰ4165 and make the offeringВҰ4167 required by Mosheh's law as a testimonyВҰ4174 to \+add the authorities\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua heals a Roman's slave
\rem /s1 The Faith of the Centurion; Jesus Heals a Centurion's Servant; Jesus Heals a Roman Officer's Servant; Faith of the Roman Officer
\r (Luke 7:1-10)
\p
\v 5 When Yeshua arrived in CapernaumВҰ4184, a \add Roman\add* army commander approachedВҰ4185 him andВҰ4178 begged him,
\v 6 sayingВҰ4192, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ4193\nd*, I have a slave who's paralysedВҰ4201 andВҰ4191 had to kept in bed because he's beingВҰ4203 badly tormentedВҰ4203.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 вҖң\wj I'll comeВҰ4212 andВҰ4204 heal him,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answered.
\p
\v 8 вҖңButВҰ4217 \nd masterВҰ4222\nd*,вҖқ the commander replied, вҖңI'm not worthyВҰ4225 that youВҰ4231 should comeВҰ4231 to my house, butВҰ4232 just give the command andВҰ4237 my slave will be healedВҰ4238,
\v 9 becauseВҰ4243 I'm also a manВҰ4245 given a position under authorityВҰ4248 with soldiersВҰ4253 under me, and I tell this one, вҖҳCome here,вҖҷ and he comes, and tell myВҰ4268 slaveВҰ4267, вҖҳDo this,вҖҷ and he does it.
\p
\v 10 \nd Yeshua\nd* was amazed when he heardВҰ4273 that andВҰ4274 saidВҰ4279 to his followersВҰ4281 \add around him\add*, вҖң\wj I can assure you that I haven't discovered faithВҰ4290 like this from any Israeli.\wj*
\v 11 \x + \xo 8:11: \xt Luk 13:29.\x*\wj I'm telling youВҰ4299 that many people from all over the world will come and join AbrahamВҰ4310 and IsaacВҰ4312 and YacobВҰ4314 at the table in the heavenlyВҰ4319 kingdomВҰ4317,\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 8:12: \xt Mat 22:13; 25:30; Luk 13:28.\x*\wj butВҰ4321 the \+add ones who thought they were the true\+add* children will be thrownВҰ4326 out into the distant darknessВҰ4329 where there'llВҰ4332 be crying andВҰ4336 regrets.\wj*
\v 13 ThenВҰ4341 he saidВҰ4342 to the commander, вҖң\wj Go thenВҰ4341 and it will happen according to your faith,\wj*вҖқ and his slave was healedВҰ4355 that very moment.
\s1 Yeshua heals the people
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals Many at Peter's House; Jesus Heals Many People
\r (Mark 1:29-34; Luke 4:38-41)
\p
\v 14 When \nd Yeshua\nd* came to Peter's houseВҰ4390, he sawВҰ4392 Peter's mother-in-law lying in bed with the feverВҰ4398.
\v 15 Yeshua touchedВҰ4400 her handВҰ4402 and the feverВҰ4408 left her. Then sheВҰ4410 got up and looked after her guest.
\p
\v 16 In the eveningВҰ4416, the people broughtВҰ4419 many who were possessedВҰ4421 by evil spirits and Yeshua drove out the spirits with a command and healedВҰ4433 all of them that were sickВҰ4431.
\v 17 This fulfilledВҰ4435 what the prophetВҰ4441 Yeshayah had written: вҖҳHe tookВҰ4448 our sicknessВҰ4446 andВҰ4449 bore our diseasesВҰ4451.вҖҷ\x + \xo 8:17: \xt Isa 53:4.\x*
\s1 Some wanted to follow Yeshua
\rem /s1 The Cost of Following Jesus; The Would-Be Followers of Jesus
\r (Luke 9:57-62)
\p
\v 18 When \nd Yeshua\nd* saw the crowdВҰ4459 aroundВҰ4461 him, he told \add his apprentices\add* to take him acrossВҰ4467 to the other side \add of the lake\add*.
\v 19 One of the teachers of the law came up to Yeshua andВҰ4468 told himВҰ4473, вҖңTeacherВҰ4474, I'll followВҰ4475 you whereverВҰ4477 you go.вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖң\wj FoxesВҰ4487 have burrowsВҰ4488,\wj*вҖқ said \nd YeshuaВҰ4485\nd*, вҖң\wj andВҰ4490 birdsВҰ4492 have their nestsВҰ4495, butВҰ4497 humanity's child doesn't \+add even\+add* have a place to lay his head.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 21 Another one of his followers saidВҰ4513 to himВҰ4514, вҖң\add I'll follow you,\add* \nd MasterВҰ4515\nd*, but firstВҰ4518 let me wait until I can buryВҰ4521\f + \fr 8:21 \ft It's not certain from either the text or the context whether this person meant that their father had just died (less likely, perhaps, because they probably wouldn't have been there at all), or that they wanted to delay until their (presumably, elderly) father passed away before following Yeshua.\f* myВҰ4524 father.вҖқ
\p
\v 22 вҖң\wj Follow afterВҰ4532 me,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* responded, вҖң\wj and leaveВҰ4534 the dead to buryВҰ4537 the dead by themselvesВҰ4539.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua commands the wind
\rem /s1 Jesus Calms a Storm; Jesus Calms the Storm; Jesus Stills the Storm
\r (Mark 4:35-41; Luke 8:22-25)
\p
\v 23 ThenВҰ4541 Yeshua and hisВҰ4551 apprenticesВҰ4550 followedВҰ4547 him and got into the boatВҰ4546 \add and launched it\add*.
\v 24 ThenВҰ4552 wowВҰ4553, a hugeВҰ4555 stormВҰ4554 rose up on the lakeВҰ4559 andВҰ4552 the wavesВҰ4567 started coming into the boatВҰ4562, butВҰ4569 Yeshua was asleep.
\v 25 They woke himВҰ4578 up andВҰ4571 pleaded, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ4580\nd*, saveВҰ4581 us, we're going to drown.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj What are you worried about,\wj*вҖқ, asked Yeshua, вҖң\wj you who don't have much faithВҰ4590.\wj*вҖқ ThenВҰ4584 he stood up and told the windsВҰ4596 and the water to stop, and the lakeВҰ4600 becameВҰ4602 very calm.
\p
\v 27 The peopleВҰ4607 were astonished and asked, вҖңWhat kind of manВҰ4610 is this that the windsВҰ4618 and the lakeВҰ4621 just do what he says?вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua banishes demons into a herd of pigs
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals Two Men with Demons; Jesus Heals the Gadarene Demoniacs; The Healing of Two Demon-possessed Men; Jesus Heals Two Demon-Possessed Men
\r (Mark 5:1-20; Luke 8:26-39)
\p
\v 28 And when Yeshua arrived at the country of the GadarenesВҰ4639 on the other side \add of the lake\add*, he was met by twoВҰ4643 very dangerousВҰ4649 demon-possessed men who were comingВҰ4648 out of the cemetery. Because of them, some \add people\add* weren't able to travel on that road.
\v 29 Suddenly the two men yelledВҰ4662 out sayingВҰ4664, вҖңSon of \nd GodВҰ4672\nd*, what's the connection between us andВҰ4660 you? Have you come here to cause us pain beforeВҰ4679 the \add designated\add* timeВҰ4680?вҖқ
\p
\v 30 Now there was a herd of many pigs grazing not far away from them,
\v 31 andВҰ4694 the demonsВҰ4695 begged Yeshua sayingВҰ4698, вҖңIf youВҰ4700 do drive us out, sendВҰ4702 us into the herd of pigs.вҖқ
\p
\v 32 And he saidВҰ4713 to them, вҖңDepart!вҖқ SoВҰ4712 they came out and wentВҰ4722 away into the pigs, and next thing all the herd rushedВҰ4732 down the bank into the lakeВҰ4744 and drowned in the waterВҰ4750.
\p
\v 33 ThenВҰ4752 the men who had been grazing them took off, andВҰ4752 when they got to the cityВҰ4759 they reportedВҰ4760 everything, including what had happened to the demon-possessed men.
\v 34 Soon all the cityВҰ4770 cameВҰ4771 out to meet with \nd Yeshua\nd*, andВҰ4766 when they found him they asked him to leave theirВҰ4788 regionВҰ4787.
\c 9
\s1 Yeshua forgives and heals a paralysed man
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Paralysed Man; Jesus Heals a Paralytic
\r (Mark 2:1-12; Luke 5:17-26)
\p
\v 1 SoВҰ4789 Yeshua got into a boatВҰ4793 andВҰ4797 crossedВҰ4796 back over to his own cityВҰ4803 \add of Capernaum\add*.
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Paralytic
\v 2 Some people there brought a paralysedВҰ4809 man to him lying on a stretcher. And when \nd Yeshua\nd* saw theirВҰ4819 faithВҰ4818, he saidВҰ4820 to the man, вҖңSon, be encouraged. YourВҰ4829 sinsВҰ4831 are forgivenВҰ4825.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 Immediately some of the law teachersВҰ4837 saidВҰ4838 amongВҰ4839 themselvesВҰ4840, вҖңThis manВҰ4841 presumes to be God.вҖқ
\p
\v 4 ButВҰ4843 \nd Yeshua\nd* knew theirВҰ4850 thoughtsВҰ4849 andВҰ4843 saidВҰ4851, вҖңWhy are you thinking evilВҰ4857 things in yourВҰ4861 heartsВҰ4860?
\v 5 Do you think it's easierВҰ4865 to say, вҖҳYourВҰ4869 sinsВҰ4872 are forgivenВҰ4868,вҖҷ or to say, вҖҳStand up and walkВҰ4878вҖҷ?
\v 6 But so that you will know that humanity's child has the authorityВҰ4884 here on earthВҰ4895 to forgiveВҰ4896 sinsВҰ4897,вҖқ he said, вҖңstand up, takeВҰ4905 your stretcher, and go to your houseВҰ4914.вҖқ
\p
\v 7 ThenВҰ4916 the man stood up andВҰ4916 wentВҰ4918 off to hisВҰ4922 houseВҰ4921.
\v 8 The crowdsВҰ4927 were struck with fear after seeing this, yet theyВҰ4931 praised \nd GodВҰ4933\nd* for giving such authorityВҰ4936 to men.
\s1 Yeshua calls Matthew and they dine with вҖҳsinnersвҖҷ
\rem /s1 Jesus Calls Matthew; The Call of Matthew; The Calling of Matthew
\r (Mark 2:13-17; Luke 5:27-32)
\p
\v 9 And as \nd Yeshua\nd* was leaving thereВҰ4945, he sawВҰ4946 a manВҰ4947 calledВҰ4955 Matthew \add (also known as Levi)\add* sittingВҰ4948 in the taxВҰ4951 officeВҰ4951. He said to Matthew, вҖңFollow me.вҖқ And he gotВҰ4962 upВҰ4962 andВҰ4940 followedВҰ4963 him.
\p
\v 10 \x + \xo 9:10-11: \xt Luk 15:1-2.\x*Later when Yeshua was eating at \add Matthew's\add* houseВҰ4974, many taxВҰ4979 collectorsВҰ4979 and sinnersВҰ4982 came in and sat at the table together with Yeshua and hisВҰ4968 disciples.
\v 11 Some of the Pharisee partyВҰ4997 noticed this and said to hisВҰ5002 disciples, вҖңHow come yourВҰ5018 teacherВҰ5017 eats with taxВҰ5010 collectorsВҰ5010 and sinnersВҰ5013?вҖқ
\p
\v 12 ButВҰ5021 Yeshua heardВҰ5023 this andВҰ5021 saidВҰ5024, вҖңPeople who are well don'tВҰ5026 need a doctorВҰ5031вҖ”only the ones with problems do.
\v 13 \x + \xo 9:13: a \xt Mat 12:7; \xo b \xt Hos 6:6.\x*So go andВҰ5045 find out the meaning of this: I like mercy not sacrificeВҰ5047. Because it's sinnersВҰ5055 that I cameВҰ5050 to call, not those \add considered\add* righteousВҰ5052.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is asked about fasting
\rem /s1 Jesus Questioned About Fasting; A Discussion about Fasting; The Question about Fasting
\r (Mark 2:18-22; Luke 5:33-39)
\p
\v 14 Then the disciples of Yohan approachedВҰ5059 Yeshua and said, вҖңHow come that weВҰ5067 and the Pharisees fast regularly, but yourВҰ5077 disciples don'tВҰ5078 fast?вҖқ
\p
\v 15 And \nd Yeshua\nd* replied to them, вҖңSurely the groomsmen aren'tВҰ5086 sad while the groom is with them? ButВҰ5080 the time will come when the groom has to leave them andВҰ5115 thenВҰ5080 theyВҰ5117 will fast.
\p
\v 16 No one patches old clothes with new material becauseВҰ5134 the patch will shrink andВҰ5141 the clothes would end up with a worseВҰ5142 hole.
\v 17 And they don'tВҰ5154 put new wine into an old container, otherwise the container could split and be ruined and the wine would be lost. Rather they put new wine into a new container and both survive.вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua raises a dead girl and heals a woman from bleeding
\rem /s1 The Official's Daughter and the Woman Who Touched Jesus' Cloak; A Girl Restored to Life and a Woman Healed; A Dead Girl and a Sick Woman; Jesus Heals in Response to Faith
\r (Mark 5:21-43; Luke 8:40-56)
\p
\v 18 While Yeshua was speakingВҰ5193 to them, an official came and bowed to him sayingВҰ5202, вҖңMyВҰ5206 daughterВҰ5205 has just passed away, but comeВҰ5210 and put yourВҰ5214 handВҰ5213 on her and sheВҰ5218 will revive.
\p
\v 19 SoВҰ5219 \nd YeshuaВҰ5222\nd* and hisВҰ5229 disciples got up and followedВҰ5224 him.
\p
\v 20 Just thenВҰ5230 a womanВҰ5232 who had been bleeding internally for twelveВҰ5234 yearsВҰ5235 came up behindВҰ5237 Yeshua andВҰ5230 touchedВҰ5238 the edge of hisВҰ5243 robe
\v 21 becauseВҰ5245 she had told herselfВҰ5247 that if she could just touchВҰ5250 hisВҰ5254 robe, she would be healedВҰ5255.
\p
\v 22 \nd Yeshua\nd* turnedВҰ5260 and saw her and said, вҖңBe encouraged, daughterВҰ5267, yourВҰ5271 faithВҰ5270 has healed you.вҖқ And the womanВҰ5277 was healed that very moment.
\p
\v 23 Now when \nd Yeshua\nd* went into the houseВҰ5288 of the rulerВҰ5290, he saw the funeral musicians andВҰ5282 the distressedВҰ5298 people
\v 24 andВҰ5310 he said, вҖңGo away. The girlВҰ5307 hasn't diedВҰ5305вҖ”she's sleepingВҰ5309.вҖқ ButВҰ5310 they ridiculedВҰ5311 him.
\v 25 However when the crowdВҰ5321 was moved out, he went in and tookВҰ5324 herВҰ5329 handВҰ5327, and the girlВҰ5333 got up.
\v 26 ThenВҰ5334 the newsВҰ5337 of this spread all around that region.
\s1 Yeshua heals two blind men
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals Two Blind Men; Jesus Heals the Blind and Mute
\p
\v 27 As \nd Yeshua\nd* left the ruler's home, twoВҰ5354 blindВҰ5355 menВҰ5355 followedВҰ5352 himВҰ5353 andВҰ5358 called out, вҖңHave mercyВҰ5360 on us, son of DavidВҰ5364.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 When he went into the houseВҰ5373, the blindВҰ5379 menВҰ5379 went to him andВҰ5369 \nd Yeshua\nd* said to them, вҖңDo you believeВҰ5385 that I'm able to do this?вҖқ
\p They replied, вҖңYes, \nd masterВҰ5397\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 29 Then he touchedВҰ5399 theirВҰ5403 eyesВҰ5402 sayingВҰ5405, вҖңLet it be done to you in line with yourВҰ5410 faithВҰ5409.вҖқ
\v 30 ThenВҰ5413 theirВҰ5415 eyesВҰ5417 were healed andВҰ5413 \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖңDon't let anyoneВҰ5427 know about this.вҖқ
\p
\v 31 But after theyВҰ5432 had departed, the men told the whole region about himВҰ5433.
\s1 Yeshua heals a man who couldn't talk
\rem /s1 Jesus Heals a Man Who Could Not Speak; Jesus Heals One Who Was Mute
\p
\v 32 As theyВҰ5443 were leaving, some people broughtВҰ5443 a man to Yeshua who was demon-possessed andВҰ5440 unable to talk.
\v 33 After the demonВҰ5451 was driven out, the manВҰ5454 was able to speak andВҰ5448 the crowdsВҰ5458 were amazed sayingВҰ5459, вҖңNever before has anything like this happened in Yisrael.вҖқ
\v 34 \x + \xo 9:34: \xt Mat 10:25; 12:24; Mrk 3:22; Luk 11:15.\x*But the Pharisees said, вҖңHe casts out demons with the help of the rulerВҰ5474 of the demons.вҖқ
\s1 The large harvest
\rem /s1 Jesus Has Pity for the People; The Workers Are Few; The Need for Workers; The Harvest Is Great, the Labourers Few
\p
\v 35 \x + \xo 9:35: \xt Mat 4:23; Mrk 1:39; Luk 4:44.\x*And \nd Yeshua\nd* went aroundВҰ5481 teachingВҰ5490 in the meetingВҰ5493 hallsВҰ5493 in all the citiesВҰ5485 and the villagesВҰ5489 and announcingВҰ5496 the goodВҰ5498 news about the kingdomВҰ5500, and healingВҰ5502 every kind of diseaseВҰ5504 and sicknessВҰ5507.
\v 36 \x + \xo 9:36: \xt Num 27:17; 1Ki 22:17; 2Ch 18:16; Eze 34:5; Mrk 6:34.\x*When he saw the crowdsВҰ5517, he felt for them becauseВҰ5523 they were tired andВҰ5515 stressed like sheepВҰ5531 with no shepherdВҰ5534.
\v 37 \x + \xo 9:37-38: \xt Luk 10:2.\x*He said to hisВҰ5539 disciples, вҖңThe harvestВҰ5542 is large, but there's not enough workersВҰ5546.
\v 38 So ask the owner of the harvest to send more workersВҰ5558 to help with it.вҖқ
\c 10
\s1 Yeshua commissions the twelve
\rem /s1 Jesus Sends Out the Twelve Apostles; The Twelve are commissioned
\r (Mark 3:13-19; Luke 6:12-16)
\p
\v 1 ThenВҰ5563 callingВҰ5564 hisВҰ5568 twelveВҰ5566 apprenticesВҰ5567, he gaveВҰ5569 them authorityВҰ5571 over evil spiritsВҰ5572 so they could drive them out, and they could heal every diseaseВҰ5582 and sicknessВҰ5585.
\v 2 These are the namesВҰ5591 of the twelveВҰ5588: SimonВҰ5595 (nicknamed PeterВҰ5598) and his brother AndrewВҰ5600, Yacob and his brother Yohan (the sons of ZebedeeВҰ5608),
\v 3 Philip and BartholomewВҰ5616, ThomasВҰ5617 and MatthewВҰ5619 the taxВҰ5621 collectorВҰ5621, Yacob (nicknamed ThaddeusВҰ5631, son of Alfaeus),
\v 4 Simon (memberВҰ5636 of the Caananites) andВҰ5638 YudasВҰ5640 IscariotВҰ5642 (who \add eventually\add* turned Yeshua in).
\s1 Yeshua sends out the twelve
\rem /s1 The Mission of the Twelve
\r (Mark 6:7-13; Luke 9:1-6)
\p
\v 5 \nd Yeshua\nd* sentВҰ5652 out theseВҰ5648 twelveВҰ5650, instructing them, вҖң\wj Don't goВҰ5663 onto the roads of non-Jews or into the cityВҰ5666 of SamariaВҰ5667,\wj*
\v 6 \wj butВҰ5672 ratherВҰ5673 go to the lost sheepВҰ5676 who a descendants of YisraelВҰ5680.\wj*
\v 7 \wj As you go, announce to the people that the heavenlyВҰ5690 kingdomВҰ5688 is close.\wj*
\v 8 \wj Heal those who need it, bring the deadВҰ5695 back to life, get rid of leprosy, and drive evil spirits away. You all freely receivedВҰ5708, \+add so\+add* giveВҰ5710 freely.\wj*
\v 9 \wj Don't accept any money for yourВҰ5723 wallets,\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 10:10: \xt 1Cor 9:14; 1Tim 5:18.\x*\wj and don't take a backpack, or a change of clothes or footwear, or a staffВҰ5739, becauseВҰ5741 a workerВҰ5744 deserves to be fed.\wj*
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj Whatever cityВҰ5755 or villageВҰ5757 you arrive at, look around to discover who is godly, andВҰ5753 stay with them untilВҰ5770 you all leave.\wj*
\v 12 \wj When you enter a home, bless itВҰ5779,\wj*
\v 13 \wj andВҰ5785 if the houseВҰ5791 is worthy of it, let your peace come onto it, but if not, let your peace returnВҰ5813 to you.\wj*
\v 14 \x + \xo 10:14: \xt Acts 13:51.\x*\wj If there's any that don't accept you or don't want to hearВҰ5823 your messagesВҰ5826, shakeВҰ5841 the dust off your feetВҰ5848 as you leave that houseВҰ5834 or cityВҰ5837 \+add as a sign that you all accept no responsibility for them\+add*.\wj*
\v 15 \x + \xo 10:15: a \xt Mat 11:24; \xo b \xt Gen 19:24-28.\x*\wj I can assure you that it will be more tolerableВҰ5853 for the towns of SodomВҰ5856 and Amorah \add (GomorrahВҰ5859)\add* on the dayВҰ5863 of judgementВҰ5864 that it will be for those places.\wj*
\s1 The coming persecution
\rem /s1 Coming Persecutions
\r (Mark 13:9-13; Luke 21:12-17)
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 10:16: \xt Luk 10:3.\x*вҖң\wj LookВҰ5869 out, because I'm sendingВҰ5871 you out like sheepВҰ5874 among the wolvesВҰ5879, so you'll all need to be as shrewdВҰ5882 as snakes andВҰ5888 as innocentВҰ5890 as dovesВҰ5893.\wj*
\v 17 \x + \xo 10:17-20: \xt Mrk 13:9-11; Luk 12:11-12; 21:12-15.\x*\wj But watch out becauseВҰ5901 there's peopleВҰ5898 that will turn you in to the councilsВҰ5904 and then you'll be floggedВҰ5913 in theirВҰ5912 meetingВҰ5910 hallsВҰ5910.\wj*
\v 18 \wj You'll be stood beforeВҰ5916 governorsВҰ5917 and even kingsВҰ5921 on my accountВҰ5927, but it'll be a testimonyВҰ5930 to them and to the non-Jews.\wj*
\v 19 \wj However, wheneverВҰ5935 they turn you in, you don'tВҰ5941 need to worryВҰ5942 about what to say or how to say it, becauseВҰ5948 whatever you all need to say will be givenВҰ5947 to you at the \+add right\+add* time,\wj*
\v 20 \wj becauseВҰ5959 you won'tВҰ5958 be the ones speaking, but it'll be yourВҰ5969 father'sВҰ5968 \+nd spiritВҰ5966\+nd* speaking through you.\wj*
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 10:21: \xt Mrk 13:12; Luk 21:16.\x*вҖң\wj One sibling will turn in another to be executed, and a fatherВҰ5982 his childВҰ5983, and childrenВҰ5988 will be rebelling againstВҰ5989 their parentsВҰ5990 and having them put to death.\wj*
\v 22 \x + \xo 10:22: a \xt Mat 24:9; Mrk 13:13; Luk 21:17; \xo b \xt Mat 24:13; Mrk 13:13.\x*\wj You all will be hatedВҰ5996 by everyone becauseВҰ5999 of myВҰ6002 nameВҰ6001, butВҰ6004 the ones who endureВҰ6005 until the endВҰ6007, they are the ones who will be savedВҰ6009.\wj*
\v 23 \wj Whenever they persecuteВҰ6012 you in one city, escape to the next city, becauseВҰ6037 I can assure you that you won'tВҰ6042 get through all the citiesВҰ6045 in Yisrael before humanity's child comes.\wj*
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 10:24: a \xt Luk 6:40; \xo b \xt Yhn 13:16; 15:20.\x*вҖң\wj An apprenticeВҰ6057 is not above their teacherВҰ6060, nor is a slaveВҰ6063 above their masterВҰ6066.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 10:25: \xt Mat 9:34; 12:24; Mrk 3:22; Luk 11:15.\x*\wj The apprenticeВҰ6070 is happy to \+add eventually\+add* become like their teacherВҰ6075, and the slaveВҰ6079 to become like their masterВҰ6082. If they accuse the homeВҰ6087 ownerВҰ6087 of being a devil, then that will apply to hisВҰ6076 followers even more.\wj*
\s1 Who to fear
\rem /s1 Whom to Fear
\r (Luke 12:2-7)
\p
\v 26 \x + \xo 10:26: \xt Mrk 4:22; Luk 8:17.\x*вҖң\wj ThereforeВҰ6106 don'tВҰ6105 be afraidВҰ6107 of them, becauseВҰ6110 nothing is coveredВҰ6112 up that won't eventually be revealedВҰ6115, andВҰ6116 nothing is hiddenВҰ6117 that won't be made knownВҰ6120.\wj*
\v 27 \wj Anything that I tell you all in the darknessВҰ6126, speakВҰ6127 it out in the lightВҰ6130, and what you hearВҰ6137 whispered, go and yell it out from up on the top porch.\wj*
\v 28 \wj Don't be afraidВҰ6148 of anyone who can killВҰ6175 your body but who can'tВҰ6145 touch your soul, but ratherВҰ6165 work to please the one who can destroyВҰ6175 both soul andВҰ6144 body in fire.\wj*
\v 29 \wj Aren't twoВҰ6181 sparrowsВҰ6182 sold for almost nothing? Yet not one of them falls to the groundВҰ6195 without yourВҰ6199 fatherВҰ6198 beingВҰ6185 involved.\wj*
\v 30 \wj For youВҰ6200 all, even hairВҰ6205 on yourВҰ6200 head has been counted,\wj*
\v 31 \wj so don'tВҰ6212 worry about things, because youВҰ6220 are more valuable than any sparrowsВҰ6218.\wj*
\s1 Acknowledging the messiah
\rem /s1 Confessing and Rejecting Christ
\r (Luke 12:8-9)
\p
\v 32 вҖң\wj Everyone who acknowledges in front of others that they're my followers, then I will also acknowledge them in front of my fatherВҰ6237 who is in the heavensВҰ6242,\wj*
\v 33 \x + \xo 10:33: \xt 2Tim 2:12.\x*\wj butВҰ6245 anyone who disowns me in front of others, then I will also disownВҰ6247 them in front of myВҰ6259 fatherВҰ6258 who is in the heavensВҰ6263.\wj*
\s1 Don't expect peace
\rem /s1 Not Peace, but a Sword
\r (Luke 12:51-53; 14:26-27)
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj Don't imagine that I came to bring peace to the earthВҰ6274. No, I came to bring war not peace,\wj*
\v 35 \x + \xo 10:35-36: \xt Mic 7:6.\x*\wj becauseВҰ6283 I came to divideВҰ6284 a son against hisВҰ6291 fatherВҰ6290 and a daughter against her mother, and a daughter-in-law against her mother-in-law\wj*
\v 36 \wj andВҰ6304 personВҰ6307 to become an enemy of their own householdВҰ6309.\wj*
\p
\v 37 вҖң\wj Anyone who loves their fatherВҰ6313 or motherВҰ6315 more than they love me is not worthy of being mine, andВҰ6322 anyone who loves their son or daughterВҰ6327 more than they love me is not worthy of being mine.\wj*
\v 38 \x + \xo 10:38: \xt Mat 16:24; Mrk 8:34; Luk 9:23.\x*\wj Anyone who doesn't pick up their own executionВҰ6339 stakeВҰ6339 \+add andВҰ6341 carry it\+add* as they followВҰ6342 me, is not worthyВҰ6348 of being mine.\wj*
\v 39 \x + \xo 10:39: \xt Mat 16:25; Mrk 8:35; Luk 9:24; 17:33; Yhn 12:25.\x*\wj Anyone who has foundВҰ6350 their life will lose it, and anyone who loses their life because of \+add following\+add* me, will find it.\wj*
\s1 Acceptance rewards
\rem /s1 Rewards
\r (Mark 9:41)
\p
\v 40 \x + \xo 10:40: a \xt Luk 10:16; Yhn 13:20; \xo b \xt Mrk 9:37; Luk 9:48.\x*\wj Anyone who accepts youВҰ6369 is accepting me, andВҰ6372 anyone who accepts me is accepting the one who sentВҰ6379 me \+add down here\+add*.\wj*
\v 41 \wj Anyone who accepts a prophet in the name of a prophet will receive the reward of a prophet, and anyone who accepts a godly person in the name of a godly person will receive the reward of a godly person.\wj*
\v 42 \wj AnyoneВҰ6405 who as a follower \+add of me\+add* gives a cup of cool waterВҰ6412 to one of theseВҰ6409 littleВҰ6408 ones to drinkВҰ6404, I'm telling youВҰ6419 that that person certainly won'tВҰ6421 lose their rewardВҰ6426.\wj*
\c 11
\s1 Yeshua and Yohan-the-immerser
\rem /s1 Jesus and John the Baptist; The Messengers from John the Baptist
\r (Luke 7:18-35)
\p
\v 1 When \nd Yeshua\nd* had finishedВҰ6432 giving those instructions to hisВҰ6439 twelveВҰ6437 apprenticesВҰ6438, he \add also\add* left thereВҰ6441 and went to teachВҰ6443 and preach in the Jewish citiesВҰ6448.
\rem /s1 Recognizing the Messiah; Messengers from John the Baptist
\p
\v 2 ThenВҰ6451 YohanВҰ6452, who was in prisonВҰ6456, heardВҰ6453 about what the \nd messiahВҰ6461\nd* was doing, he sentВҰ6462 some of hisВҰ6467 apprenticesВҰ6466
\v 3 to ask Yeshua, вҖңAre youВҰ6470 the promised one, or should weВҰ6477 be waitingВҰ6477 for someone else?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖң\wj \+add Well,\+add*\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ6479, вҖң\wj go and tell Yohan everything that you're hearingВҰ6490 and seeingВҰ6492:\wj*
\v 5 \x + \xo 11:5: a \xt Isa 35:5-6; \xo b \xt Isa 61:1.\x*\wj those who were blindВҰ6493 can see now, lame people are now walkingВҰ6497, people will leprosy are вҖҳcleanВҰ6499вҖҷ, deaf people can now hearВҰ6502, deadВҰ6504 people have been brought back to life, and the goodВҰ6508 messageВҰ6508 is being preachedВҰ6508 to the poor.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Anyone who's not embarrassed by me will be blessedВҰ6510.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 Jesus Praises John the Baptist
\p
\v 7 As Yohan's apprentices left, Yeshua started talkingВҰ6525 to the crowdВҰ6527 about Yohan: вҖң\wj What was it that youВҰ6531 all wentВҰ6531 out to the wildernessВҰ6534 to seeВҰ6535? A reed beingВҰ6540 blown around by the windВҰ6539?\wj*\f + \fr 11:7 \ft We've left the original idiom here in the OET-RV as something to puzzle over, because no one now really knows what aspect of Yohan's behaviour or appearance that Yeshua was referring to here.\f*вҖқ
\v 8 \wj Yes, what did youВҰ6543 all go out to seeВҰ6544? A manВҰ6545 wearingВҰ6555 fine clothes? People in palaces wear fine clothes.\wj*
\v 9 \wj So why did you go out \+add there\+add*? To seeВҰ6569 a prophet? Yes, I'm telling you that \+add he is a prophet\+add*, and even more importantВҰ6574 than the prophets.\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 11:10: \xt Mal 3:1.\x*\wj He is the one that was writtenВҰ6581 about: вҖҳSeeВҰ6582, I'm sendingВҰ6584 out myВҰ6587 messengerВҰ6586 ahead of you and he'll prepareВҰ6592 yourВҰ6590 pathВҰ6594 before you.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 11 \wj I can assure youВҰ6600 that no person who's ever been born is greater than Yohan-the-immerser. But even the leastВҰ6615 important person in the heavenlyВҰ6620 kingdomВҰ6618 is greater than him.\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 11:12-13: \xt Luk 16:16.\x*\wj FromВҰ6629 the time of Yohan-the-immerser through to the present time, the heavenlyВҰ6637 kingdomВҰ6635 has been opposed, andВҰ6639 the opposition is grabbing at itВҰ6644.\wj*
\v 13 \wj All the prophets andВҰ6649 the law prophesied before Yohan came,\wj*
\v 14 \x + \xo 11:14: \xt Mal 4:5; Mat 17:10-13; Mrk 9:11-13.\x*\wj andВҰ6656 now, if you're all willingВҰ6658 to believe it, he is EliyahВҰ6662вҖ”the one who would come \+add ahead\+add*.\wj*
\v 15 \wj Anyone who is willing, let them strive to understand this.\wj*
\p
\v 16 вҖң\wj So what should I likenВҰ6673 this generationВҰ6675 to? It's like young childrenВҰ6680 sittingВҰ6681 in the town centre who are callingВҰ6691 out to othersВҰ6694\wj*
\v 17 \wj and sayingВҰ6698, вҖҳWe played lively music for you but you didn't danceВҰ6703. Then we played sad music, but you didn't mournВҰ6709.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 18 \wj BecauseВҰ6711 Yohan cameВҰ6710 and he wasn't eatingВҰ6714 or drinkingВҰ6716, and theyВҰ6718 said, вҖҳHe's possessed by a demonВҰ6719!вҖҷ\wj*
\v 19 \wj Then humanity's childВҰ6748 cameВҰ6721 and he was eatingВҰ6726 and drinkingВҰ6728, butВҰ6741 they said, вҖҳLookВҰ6731 at this fellowвҖ”he's a gluttonВҰ6733 and a drunkardВҰ6735вҖ”a friendВҰ6737 of taxВҰ6736 collectorsВҰ6736 and immoral people.вҖҷ But wisdomВҰ6744 is only recognised with hindsight.\wj*
\s1 Cities that rejected the messiah
\rem /s1 The Unbelieving Towns; Woe on Unrepentant Cities; Woes to Unrepentant Cities; Judgment for the Unbelievers
\r (Luke 10:13-15)
\p
\v 20 Then Yeshua beganВҰ6751 deridingВҰ6754 the citiesВҰ6756 thatВҰ6758 he had done most of hisВҰ6765 miraclesВҰ6764 in, becauseВҰ6766 they hadn't turned from their sins.
\v 21 \x + \xo 11:21: \xt Isa 23:1-18; Eze 26:1вҖ“28:26; Yoel 3:4-8; Amos 1:9-10; Zech 9:2-4.\x*вҖң\wj ChorazinВҰ6771 you're doomed. BethsaidaВҰ6775 you're doomed. BecauseВҰ6776 if the miraclesВҰ6786 thatВҰ6787 were done in you had been done in TyreВҰ6780 and Tsidon, they wouldВҰ6792 have shown their turning from their sins by wearing coarse cloth and showering themselves with ashesВҰ6796.\wj*
\v 22 \wj HoweverВҰ6799, I'm telling you all that it will be more tolerableВҰ6805 for the people of TyreВҰ6802 and Tsidon on judgementВҰ6809 dayВҰ6808 than it will be for you.\wj*
\v 23 \x + \xo 11:23: a \xt Isa 14:13-15; \xo b \xt Gen 19:24-28.\x*\wj Same with you, CapernaumВҰ6815. You won'tВҰ6816 be lifted up to heavenВҰ6820 but you'll be sent down to hell, because if the miraclesВҰ6835 whichВҰ6836 were done in you had been done in SodomВҰ6831, thatВҰ6836 city wouldВҰ6843 still be here todayВҰ6847.\wj*
\v 24 \x + \xo 11:24: \xt Mat 10:15; Luk 10:12.\x*\wj HoweverВҰ6848, I'm telling you all that it will be more tolerableВҰ6855 for the people of SodomВҰ6854 on judgementВҰ6861 dayВҰ6860 than it will be for you.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's load is light
\rem /s1 Rest for the Weary; Come to Me and Rest; Jesus Thanks His Father; Jesus' Prayer of Thanksgiving
\r (Luke 10:21-22)
\p
\v 25 At that timeВҰ6869 \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ6874, вҖң\wj I am acknowledging you, fatherВҰ6877, \+nd masterВҰ6878\+nd* of the heavenВҰ6880 and earthВҰ6883, that you hid theseВҰ6887 things from вҖҳwiseвҖҷ and вҖҳintelligentВҰ6891вҖҷ people and revealedВҰ6893 them to the вҖҳnaiveвҖҷ.\wj*
\v 26 \wj Yes fatherВҰ6898, becauseВҰ6899 that was your desire.\wj*
\p
\v 27 \x + \xo 11:27: a \xt Yhn 3:35; \xo b \xt Yhn 1:18; 10:15.\x*\wj MyВҰ6912 father has givenВҰ6908 control of everything over to me, but no one really knows the son except the father, and no one really knows the father except the son and anyoneВҰ6926 who the son wants to tell about him.\wj*
\p
\v 28 \wj Come to me all of you who are tired and feel overloaded, and I'll help you relax.\wj*
\v 29 \x + \xo 11:29: \xt Jer 6:16.\x*\wj You all can take on myВҰ6956 workload and learnВҰ6960 from me, becauseВҰ6963 I'm gentleВҰ6964 and humbleВҰ6967 and yourВҰ6975 soulsВҰ6974 will be able to relax\wj*
\v 30 \wj becauseВҰ6977 myВҰ6979 workload is easy, andВҰ6981 the load \+add on your shoulders\+add* is \+add just\+add* lightВҰ6985.\wj*
\c 12
\s1 The discussion about rest days
\rem /s1 Lord of the Sabbath; The Question about the Sabbath; Opposition to Jesus; Plucking Grain on the Sabbath; Controversy about the Sabbath
\r (Mark 2:23-28; Luke 6:1-5)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 12:1: \xt Deu 23:25.\x*At that time, \nd Yeshua\nd* was going throughВҰ6997 some fields of grain on a rest day, and hisВҰ7004 apprenticesВҰ7003 were hungry and beganВҰ7007 to pluckВҰ7008 some headsВҰ7011 of grain and crunch them.
\v 2 ButВҰ7016 some from the PhariseesВҰ7017 partyВҰ7017 saw them andВҰ7016 saidВҰ7020, вҖңLookВҰ7022, yourВҰ7025 followers are harvesting when it's not permittedВҰ7029 to harvest on a rest dayВҰ7032.вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \x + \xo 12:3-4: \xt 1Sam 21:1-6.\x*вҖң\wj Haven't youВҰ7038 read about what DavidВҰ7041 did when himВҰ7048 andВҰ7045 his fighters were hungry?\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ7035.
\v 4 \x + \xo 12:4: \xt Lev 24:9.\x*\wj He wentВҰ7051 into God's tent andВҰ7057 theyВҰ7064 ateВҰ7064 the Bread of the Presence whichВҰ7066 none of them were allowed to eatВҰ7073вҖ”only the priestsВҰ7081.\wj*
\v 5 \x + \xo 12:5: \xt Num 28:9-10.\x*\wj Or haven't youВҰ7085 understood that when the priestsВҰ7096 work in the templeВҰ7099 on the rest dayВҰ7101, it's against the law andВҰ7103 yet they're innocentВҰ7104?\wj*
\v 6 \wj But I'm telling youВҰ7109 that someone greaterВҰ7113 than the templeВҰ7112 is here.\wj*
\v 7 \x + \xo 12:7: a \xt Mat 9:13; \xo b \xt Hos 6:6.\x*\wj But you all should have knownВҰ7119 that what I want is mercy over sacrificesВҰ7127вҖ”you shouldn'tВҰ7126 have convictedВҰ7130 the innocentВҰ7132\wj*
\v 8 \wj becauseВҰ7134 humanity's child is the \+nd masterВҰ7133\+nd* over the rest dayВҰ7138.\wj*
\s1 The man with the clawed fist
\rem /s1 The Man with a Withered Hand; The Man with a Paralysed Hand
\r (Mark 3:1-6; Luke 6:6-11)
\p
\v 9 After leaving that place, Yeshua wentВҰ7148 into the JewishВҰ7151 meetingВҰ7151 hallВҰ7151,
\v 10 andВҰ7153 look, there was a manВҰ7155 there with a clawed fist. SoВҰ7153 the people there askedВҰ7163 Yeshua if itВҰ7167 was permittedВҰ7167 to heal people on the rest daysВҰ7169.
\p
\v 11 \x + \xo 12:11: \xt Luk 14:5.\x*вҖң\wj Which of you,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ7178, вҖң\wj if you owned a single sheepВҰ7192 and it fell into a pit on a rest day, wouldn't thenВҰ7177 grab hold of it and lift it out?\wj*
\v 12 \wj Now a humanВҰ7216 is worth much more than a sheepВҰ7218, so then itВҰ7220 must be permissibleВҰ7220 to do goodВҰ7223 on a rest day.\wj*вҖқ
\v 13 ThenВҰ7234 he said to the man, вҖң\wj StretchВҰ7229 out yourВҰ7230 hand.\wj*вҖқ
\p The man stretchedВҰ7235 his hand out andВҰ7234 it was restoredВҰ7237вҖ”now just as healthyВҰ7238 as the otherВҰ7241 one,
\v 14 butВҰ7245 the Pharisees came out and sought legal advice because theyВҰ7255 wanted to ruin Yeshua.
\s1 Yeshua was chosen by God
\rem /s1 Jesus, God's Chosen Servant
\p
\v 15 \nd Yeshua\nd* knew what they were trying to do, so he left that place. A lot of people followedВҰ7263 along afterВҰ7264 him andВҰ7262 he healedВҰ7268 them all
\v 16 but warnedВҰ7278 them not to reveal who heВҰ7278 was
\v 17 in orderВҰ7285 to fulfilВҰ7287 what the prophetВҰ7293 YeshayahВҰ7291 had written:
\q1
\v 18 \x + \xo 12:18-21: \xt Isa 42:1-4 (LXX).\x*вҖҳSeeВҰ7295 my servantВҰ7297 who I choseВҰ7301,
\q1 the one I dearly love and who my soulВҰ7311 takes pleasureВҰ7309 in.
\q1 I will place my \nd spiritВҰ7315\nd* on him
\q2 and he will bring justiceВҰ7320 to the nations.
\q1
\v 19 He won'tВҰ7325 be arguing or yelling out,
\q2 and no one on the roadsВҰ7335 will hearВҰ7330 hisВҰ7338 voiceВҰ7337.
\q1
\v 20 He won't breakВҰ7343 off a bruisedВҰ7340 reed
\q2 and certainly won't extinguishВҰ7350 a smoldering wick
\q1 before he sends justiceВҰ7357 forward into victoryВҰ7355.
\q1
\v 21 The other nations will put their hope in hisВҰ7363 nameВҰ7362 andВҰ7358 authority.вҖҷ
\s1 Yeshua accused of being the leader of demons
\rem /s1 Jesus and Beelzebub; Jesus and Beelzebul; Jesus and the Prince of Demons
\r (Mark 3:20-30; Luke 11:14-23)
\p
\v 22 Then a man possessedВҰ7371 by evil spirits was broughtВҰ7368 to Yeshua. He was blindВҰ7373 and unable to speak, but Yeshua healedВҰ7379 him so that he could both speak and see.
\v 23 All the people were amazedВҰ7394 andВҰ7398 were sayingВҰ7399, вҖңSurelyВҰ7400 this must be the \add promised\add* descendant of DavidВҰ7406?вҖқ
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 12:24: \xt Mat 9:34; 10:25.\x*When the Pharisees' partyВҰ7409 heardВҰ7410 about that, they saidВҰ7411, вҖңThat manВҰ7412 is only drivingВҰ7414 out demons because he's Beelzebul, the leader of the demons.вҖқ
\p
\v 25 ButВҰ7427 Yeshua, knowingВҰ7426 theirВҰ7432 thoughtsВҰ7431, saidВҰ7433, вҖң\wj EveryВҰ7435 kingdomВҰ7436 that's divided against itself is doomed, andВҰ7427 any cityВҰ7445 or householdВҰ7447 that's divided against itself will self-destruct.\wj*
\v 26 \wj If Satan is drivingВҰ7464 out Satan, thenВҰ7456 he's dividedВҰ7467 againstВҰ7465 himselfВҰ7466 andВҰ7456 how could hisВҰ7473 kingdomВҰ7472 possibly be establishedВҰ7470?\wj*
\v 27 \wj And if I'm driving out demonsВҰ7482 by Beelzebul, thenВҰ7474 by who are yourВҰ7485 sonsВҰ7484 driving them out?\wj*
\v 28 \wj But if I am drivingВҰ7505 out demonsВҰ7507 by God's \+nd spiritВҰ7502\+nd*, then that must mean that God's kingdomВҰ7514 has \+add already\+add* arrived among youВҰ7512 all.\wj*
\p
\v 29 вҖң\wj How can someone go into the houseВҰ7524 of a strong man andВҰ7539 steal his goodsВҰ7529 if they don'tВҰ7534 tie him up firstВҰ7535? Only thenВҰ7539 can his home be plunderedВҰ7544.\wj*
\p
\v 30 \x + \xo 12:30: \xt Mrk 9:40.\x*вҖң\wj Anyone who's not for me is againstВҰ7551 me, andВҰ7554 anyone who isn'tВҰ7547 helping me gatherВҰ7557 others is scatteringВҰ7560 them.\wj*
\v 31 \wj That's why I'm telling you that peopleВҰ7573 can be forgiven for all kinds of sinВҰ7567 and slander, except that slandering \+add God's\+add* \+nd spiritВҰ7577\+nd* won'tВҰ7579 be forgiven.\wj*
\v 32 \x + \xo 12:32: \xt Luk 12:10.\x*\wj AnyoneВҰ7593 who speaks out against humanity's child can be forgiven, but anyone who speaks out against the holy \+nd spiritВҰ7604\+nd* won'tВҰ7607 be forgiven either in this age or in the comingВҰ7621 one.\wj*
\s1 A tree is recognised by its fruit
\rem /s1 A Tree and Its Fruit
\r (Luke 6:43-45)
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 12:33: \xt Mat 7:20; Luk 6:44.\x*вҖң\wj EitherВҰ7622 make both the tree and its fruit good, or make them both bad, becauseВҰ7646 a tree is knownВҰ7653 by its fruit.\wj*
\v 34 \x + \xo 12:34: a \xt Mat 3:7; 23:33; Luk 3:7; \xo b \xt Mat 15:18; Luk 6:45.\x*\wj You brood of snakes! You're evilВҰ7662 inside so why do you think you can say anything that's goodВҰ7660 becauseВҰ7665 your mouthsВҰ7671 speak out of what's plentiful in your heartsВҰ7669.\wj*
\v 35 \wj A good person produces good words out of their store of goodness, and an evil person produces evil words out of their store of evil.\wj*
\p
\v 36 вҖң\wj But I'm telling youВҰ7698 that peopleВҰ7709 will have to give an accountВҰ7715 on judgementВҰ7718 dayВҰ7717 for everyВҰ7700 worthless sentence that they've spoken,\wj*
\v 37 \wj becauseВҰ7720 you'll be either be convictedВҰ7731, or be declared guiltless, by the things that you \+add yourself\+add* have said.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The religious leaders ask for a sign
\rem /s1 The Demand for a Miracle; The Sign of Jonah
\r (Mark 8:11-12; Luke 11:29-32)
\p
\v 38 \x + \xo 12:38: \xt Mat 16:1; Mrk 8:11; Luk 11:16.\x*Then some of the teachersВҰ7737 of the law andВҰ7738 some from the Pharisees' partyВҰ7739 responded to himВҰ7734, вҖңTeacherВҰ7741, weВҰ7742 want to seeВҰ7746 a signВҰ7745 from youВҰ7744.вҖқ
\p
\v 39 \x + \xo 12:39: \xt Mat 16:4; Mrk 8:12.\x*вҖң\wj It's an evil and adulterousВҰ7755 generation that's lookingВҰ7757 forВҰ7757 a sign,\wj*вҖқ answeredВҰ7749 Yeshua, вҖң\wj and no sign will be givenВҰ7761 to it apart from the sign of the prophetВҰ7770 YonahВҰ7768 \+add (Jonah)\+add*.\wj*
\v 40 \x + \xo 12:40: \xt Yonah 1:17.\x*\wj BecauseВҰ7773 just like Yonah was in the bellyВҰ7778 of the huge fish for three days and three nights, in the same way humanity's child will be three days and three nights in the heartВҰ7795 of the earthВҰ7797.\wj*
\v 41 \x + \xo 12:41: \xt Yonah 3:5.\x*\wj The inhabitants of Nineveh will standВҰ7805 up and condemnВҰ7815 this generationВҰ7812 on judgementВҰ7808 day, becauseВҰ7817 they turned from their sins when Yonah preached, and look, now there's one here who's greaterВҰ7825 than Yonah.\wj*
\v 42 \x + \xo 12:42: \xt 1Ki 10:1-10; 2Ch 9:1-12.\x*\wj The queenВҰ7828 of the southВҰ7829 will get up and condemnВҰ7839 this generationВҰ7836 on judgementВҰ7833 day, becauseВҰ7841 sheВҰ7842 travelled a great distance to hearВҰ7848 \+add King\+add* Solomon's wisdomВҰ7850, and look, now there's one here who's greater than Solomon.\wj*
\s1 The demon's revenge
\rem /s1 The Return of the Evil Spirit; The Return of the Unclean Spirit
\r (Luke 11:24-26)
\p
\v 43 вҖң\wj Whenever an evil spiritВҰ7862 comes out of a personВҰ7866, it goes through arid lands lookingВҰ7871 forВҰ7871 a placeВҰ7870 to rest, andВҰ7859 doesn't find any.\wj*
\v 44 \wj SoВҰ7887 it says to itself, вҖҳI'll go back to the houseВҰ7882 that I just leftВҰ7886.вҖҷ ThenВҰ7887 when it gets back, it finds that it's not only unoccupiedВҰ7893, but it's been sweptВҰ7895 andВҰ7887 tidied up.\wj*
\v 45 \wj So it goes and find sevenВҰ7904 otherВҰ7905 spiritsВҰ7906 more evil than itself and they all go to live thereВҰ7913, so the later stateВҰ7917 of that personВҰ7920 is worseВҰ7922 that it was at the beginning. So now, it'll be just like that for this evil generationВҰ7930.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The mother and siblings of Yeshua
\rem /s1 The True Family of Jesus; Jesus' Mother and Brothers; The True Kindred of Jesus
\r (Mark 3:31-35; Luke 8:19-21)
\p
\v 46 While Yeshua was stillВҰ7934 talkingВҰ7938 to the crowdВҰ7940, hisВҰ7947 motherВҰ7943 and siblings stoodВҰ7948 outsideВҰ7949, wanting to speakВҰ7952 to him.
\v 47 Someone told himВҰ7957, вҖңLookВҰ7961, your motherВҰ7963 andВҰ7955 your siblings are outsideВҰ7969, waiting to speakВҰ7977 with you.вҖқ
\p
\v 48 вҖң\wj Who's my motherВҰ7990 andВҰ7992 who are my siblings?\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answeredВҰ7981 to that person.
\v 49 ThenВҰ7999 extending his handВҰ8002 around to his followers he saidВҰ8008, вҖң\wj SeeВҰ8009, these are my motherВҰ8011 andВҰ7999 my siblings,\wj*
\v 50 \wj becauseВҰ8018 anyone who obeys my fatherВҰ8026 in the heavensВҰ8030 is my brotherВҰ8033 and my sisterВҰ8035 and my motherВҰ8037.\wj*вҖқ
\c 13
\s1 The parable about spreading seed
\rem /s1 Parables; Story of the Farmer Scattering Seed; The Parable of the Sower
\r (Mark 4:1-9; Luke 8:4-8)
\p
\v 1 That same dayВҰ8042, \nd Yeshua\nd* went outside and sat by the lakeВҰ8056.
\v 2 \x + \xo 13:2: \xt Luk 5:1-3.\x*A large crowd of people gatheredВҰ8058 around him, so he got into a boatВҰ8067 andВҰ8057 sat there while the crowd remained standing on the beach,
\v 3 where he told them many parablesВҰ8083, sayingВҰ8085, вҖң\wj ListenВҰ8086, a farmer wentВҰ8087 out to plant seed at that timeВҰ8090 of the year.\wj*
\v 4 \wj As he was spreading the seed, some of it fell beside a pathВҰ8104 and the birdsВҰ8110 come and ate that seed.\wj*
\v 5 \wj Some fell on stony ground whereВҰ8121 there wasn't much soil, and it sprouted immediatelyВҰ8127 becauseВҰ8130 the thin layer of soil \+add was moist and warm\+add*,\wj*
\v 6 \wj but when the sunВҰ8138 rose high, it was scorchedВҰ8142 and not having any deep roots, it witheredВҰ8150 up.\wj*
\v 7 \wj Some seed fell in a thistle patch, but the thistles grew over them and chokedВҰ8165 them out.\wj*
\v 8 \wj However, some seed landed on the goodВҰ8176 soil and it grew to bear a harvestвҖ”some a hundredВҰ8183 times more, some sixtyВҰ8186 times, and some thirtyВҰ8189 times.\wj*
\v 9 \wj Anyone who wants to hearВҰ8194 shouldВҰ8194 strive to understand this.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua's use of parables
\rem /s1 The Purpose of the Parables
\r (Mark 4:10-12; Luke 8:9-10)
\p
\v 10 After this, his apprenticesВҰ8199 came to himВҰ8202 andВҰ8195 asked, вҖңWhy do youВҰ8207 speakВҰ8207 to the people in parablesВҰ8206?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj You guys have been permitted to knowВҰ8218 the mysteriesВҰ8220 of the heavenlyВҰ8224 kingdomВҰ8222,\wj*вҖқ replied Yeshua, вҖң\wj butВҰ8226 not thoseВҰ8225 others.\wj*вҖқ
\v 12 \x + \xo 13:12: \xt Mat 25:29; Mrk 4:25; Luk 8:18; 19:26.\x*\wj BecauseВҰ8230 anyone who already has will be givenВҰ8232 more andВҰ8234 they will end up with plenty, butВҰ8237 anyone who doesn't have, even what they have will be takenВҰ8243 away from them.\wj*
\v 13 \wj That's why I speakВҰ8252 to them in parablesВҰ8249, becauseВҰ8253 when they look they don't see, and when they listen, they don't hearВҰ8261 or understandВҰ8269,\wj*
\v 14 \x + \xo 13:14-15: \xt Isa 6:9-10 (LXX).\x*\wj and so the prophecyВҰ8280 \+add written\+add* by Yeshayah is beingВҰ8276 fulfilledВҰ8276:\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳWhen you listen you will hearВҰ8291 but you certainly won't understandВҰ8298,\wj*
\q1 \wj and when you look you will see but you certainly won't perceiveВҰ8306 anything.\wj*
\q1
\v 15 \wj BecauseВҰ8308 these people'sВҰ8312 hearts are insensitive and they can barely hear with their ears,\wj*
\q1 \wj and they shut their eyes so they can't see with them.\wj*
\q1 \wj Otherwise they might see with their eyes and hear with their ears,\wj*
\q1 \wj and understandВҰ8338 with their heart and then returnВҰ8340 to me and then I would heal them.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 13:16-17: \xt Luk 10:23-24.\x*вҖң\wj But your eyesВҰ8350 are blessedВҰ8348 because they can see, and your earsВҰ8355 also, because they can hearВҰ8359,\wj*
\v 17 \wj becauseВҰ8361 I can assure you all that many prophetsВҰ8366 and godlyВҰ8368 people wanted to see what you're seeingВҰ8372, but they didn't see, and they wanted to hear what you're all hearingВҰ8381, but they didn't hear it either.\wj*
\s1 The meaning/salvation of parable concerning the planting
\rem /s1 Jesus Explains the Parable of the Sower; The Parable of the Sower Explained
\r (Mark 4:13-20; Luke 8:11-15)
\p
\v 18 вҖң\wj SoВҰ8386 now listenВҰ8387 concerning the parableВҰ8389 about the person spreading seed.\wj*
\v 19 \wj EveryoneВҰ8392 who hears the messageВҰ8395 about the kingdomВҰ8397 and doesn't understandВҰ8401 it, the evilВҰ8404 one comes and snatchesВҰ8406 what was sown in that person's heartВҰ8412. That's the seed that landed by the pathВҰ8420.\wj*
\v 20 \wj The seed that landed on the rockyВҰ8426 ground, that's the person who hears the messageВҰ8432 andВҰ8435 is immediatelyВҰ8436 happy to accept itВҰ8441,\wj*
\v 21 \wj but doesn't have any roots of their own so it's just fleetingвҖ”they stumbleВҰ8460 as soon as there's any difficulties or persecutionВҰ8455 becauseВҰ8456 of the messageВҰ8458.\wj*
\v 22 \wj The seed the landed amongВҰ8463 the thornsВҰ8465 is the person who hears the message, but the worries of the time and the seductionВҰ8483 of wealth chokes out the message and it becomesВҰ8492 unfruitfulВҰ8491.\wj*
\v 23 \wj The seed that landed on the goodВҰ8499 soil is the person who hears the messageВҰ8507 and understandsВҰ8511 it and goes on to bear fruitВҰ8515вҖ”some people producingВҰ8517 a hundredВҰ8520 times more, some sixtyВҰ8523 times, and some thirtyВҰ8526 times.\wj*вҖқ\f + \fr 13:23 \ft See http://scrollandscreen.com/biblestudyresources/Matthew%2013.1-23%20mgvh%20notes.pdf\f*
\s1 The parable about the bad wheat
\rem /s1 Story of the Wheat and Weeds; The Parable of the Weeds; The Parable of Weeds among the Wheat
\p
\v 24 Then Yeshua told them anotherВҰ8527 parableВҰ8528, sayingВҰ8531, вҖң\wj The heavenlyВҰ8537 kingdomВҰ8535 is like a farmer who's planted goodВҰ8541 seed in hisВҰ8548 fieldВҰ8546.\wj*
\v 25 \wj But the while they were all sleepingВҰ8552, his enemyВҰ8558 cameВҰ8555 and spread black-grained вҖҳwheatвҖҷ seeds around his wheat field and left again.\wj*
\v 26 \wj Then when the wheat grew andВҰ8574 producedВҰ8576 grains, the \+add poisonous\+add* вҖҳwheatвҖҷ could also be seenВҰ8578.\wj*
\v 27 \wj The farmer's slaveВҰ8585 came andВҰ8583 told himВҰ8590, вҖҳMasterВҰ8591, wasn't itВҰ8603 \+em goodВҰ8593\+em* wheat seed that youВҰ8595 planted? SoВҰ8583 why is there so much false wheat?вҖҷ\wj*
\v 28 \wj вҖҳAn enemyВҰ8610 must have done this,вҖҷ the farmer replied. вҖҳSoВҰ8607 should weВҰ8626 go andВҰ8607 pull out the bad stuff,вҖҷ asked the slavesВҰ8616.\wj*
\v 29 \wj вҖҳNo,вҖҷ said the farmer, вҖҳbecause pulling that out might also pull up some of the wheatВҰ8646 plants.\wj*
\v 30 \wj вҖҳLet them all grownВҰ8650 together, and then at harvest timeВҰ8661 I can just tell the harvesters to pull the false wheat plants out firstВҰ8668 and put then in bundlesВҰ8675 to be incinerated, and then harvest the wheat to go into myВҰ8690 barn.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\s1 The parable about the small mustard seed
\rem /s1 The Parables of the Mustard Seed and the Yeast; Illustration of the Mustard Seed; The Parable of the Mustard Seed
\r (Mark 4:30-32; Luke 13:18-19)
\p
\v 31 AnotherВҰ8691 one of his parablesВҰ8692 went like this: вҖң\wj The heavenlyВҰ8702 kingdomВҰ8700 is like a mustardВҰ8704 seed thatВҰ8705 a manВҰ8707 planted in his fieldВҰ8711.\wj*
\v 32 \wj Even though it's a very smallВҰ8714 seed, it grows larger than \+add most\+add* gardenВҰ8727 plantsВҰ8727 and becomesВҰ8730 such a large bush thatВҰ8713 birdsВҰ8735 even comeВҰ8733 and nest in itsВҰ8743 branchesВҰ8742.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The parable about the yeast
\rem /s1 Illustration of the Yeast; The Parable of the Yeast
\r (Luke 13:20-21)
\p
\v 33 In another parableВҰ8745, Yeshua said, вҖң\wj The heavenlyВҰ8755 kingdomВҰ8753 is like yeast, which a womanВҰ8759 took and hid it in a month's worth of flourВҰ8763, and eventually all of it rose.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The reason Yeshua used parables
\rem /s1 The Use of Parables; Jesus' Use of Parables
\r (Mark 4:33-34)
\p
\v 34 \nd YeshuaВҰ8774\nd* told all theseВҰ8770 things to the crowdsВҰ8778 in the form of parables, in fact he said nothingВҰ8782 that wasn't a parable,
\v 35 \x + \xo 13:35: \xt Psa 78:2.\x*so that that what had been \add written\add* by the prophetВҰ8794 would be fulfilledВҰ8788:
\q1 вҖҳI will be sayingВҰ8795 things that have been hiddenВҰ8803 since the creation of the worldВҰ8806.вҖҷ
\s1 Yeshua explains about the false wheat
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Weeds Explained; Jesus Explains the Parable of the Weeds; The Wheat and Weeds Explained
\p
\v 36 ThenВҰ8818 Yeshua left the crowdВҰ8810 and wentВҰ8812 into the houseВҰ8815. HisВҰ8824 apprenticesВҰ8823 followed him in and asked him for the interpretation of the parableВҰ8830 about the poisonous black wheat in the fieldВҰ8834.
\p
\v 37 вҖң\wj The farmer spreading the goodВҰ8843 seed,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answeredВҰ8837, вҖң\wj is humanity's child,\wj*
\v 38 \wj and the fieldВҰ8852 is the worldВҰ8855 and the goodВҰ8858 seeds are the heirs to the kingdomВҰ8865. The false wheat seeds are the disciples of the evilВҰ8874 one,\wj*
\v 39 \wj and the enemyВҰ8877 who planted them in the devilВҰ8884. The harvestВҰ8887 is at the end of this age, and the harvesters are \+add God's\+add* messengersВҰ8895.\wj*
\v 40 \wj ThereforeВҰ8898 at the end of this age, the false wheat plants will be gatheredВҰ8899 andВҰ8903 incinerated.\wj*
\v 41 \wj humanity's child will be sendingВҰ8918 out his messengersВҰ8924 to remove all the temptationsВҰ8934 out of his kingdomВҰ8930, and all those who don't obey \+add God's\+add* law,\wj*
\v 42 \wj and theyВҰ8941 will throwВҰ8941 them into the incinerator, and thereВҰ8949 will be crying and much anguish.\wj*
\v 43 \wj Then the godlyВҰ8960 people will be shiningВҰ8962 \+add as bright as\+add* the sunВҰ8965 in theirВҰ8971 father'sВҰ8970 kingdomВҰ8968. Anyone who is interested to hearВҰ8976, let them listen.\wj*
\s1 The parable about the treasure in the field
\rem /s1 The Parables of the Hidden Treasure and the Pearl; The Parable of the Hidden Treasure; Three Parables; Illustration of the Hidden Treasure
\p
\v 44 вҖң\wj The heavenlyВҰ8985 kingdomВҰ8982 is like a field that had had treasure hiddenВҰ8987 in it. When someone foundВҰ8992 the treasure, they hid it again, and with great excitement went and sold everything they had so they could buy that field.\wj*
\s1 The parable about the valuable pearl
\rem /s1 Illustration of the Pearl Merchant; The Parable of the Pearl
\p
\v 45 вҖң\wj Also the heavenlyВҰ9019 kingdomВҰ9017 is like a trader wanting to buy beautifulВҰ9023 pearlsВҰ9024,\wj*
\v 46 \wj and when they foundВҰ9026 one outstanding pearl, they went and sold everything they had so they could buy that pearl.\wj*
\s1 The parable about the dragnet
\rem /s1 Illustration of the Fishing Net; The Parable of the Net
\p
\v 47 вҖң\wj Also the heavenlyВҰ9047 kingdomВҰ9045 is like a dragnetВҰ9048 that was thrownВҰ9049 into the lakeВҰ9052 andВҰ9053 picked up everythingВҰ9055 from under the water.\wj*
\v 48 \wj When it was full, they pulledВҰ9062 it up onto the beach and satВҰ9070 and sorted the catchвҖ”throwing the goodВҰ9074 catch into containersВҰ9078 and throwing out the badВҰ9081 stuff.\wj*
\v 49 \wj It'll be just like that at the end of this ageвҖ”\+add God's\+add* messengersВҰ9096 will be comingВҰ9094 out andВҰ9099 will separate evilВҰ9102 people from the godlyВҰ9106 people,\wj*
\v 50 \wj and theyВҰ9108 will throwВҰ9108 the evil ones into the incinerator. ThereВҰ9116 will be crying and great anguish.\wj*
\rem /s1 New Truths and Old; Treasures New and Old
\p
\v 51 вҖң\wj Did you all understandВҰ9129 all of that?\wj*
\p вҖңYes,вҖқ his apprentices answered.
\p
\v 52 ThenВҰ9137 he said to them, вҖң\wj BecauseВҰ9142 of this, everyВҰ9144 teacher who's been trainedВҰ9146 about the heavenlyВҰ9154 kingdomВҰ9151 is like a person who's a homeВҰ9159 ownerВҰ9159 who gives presents of both new andВҰ9137 old things of out their valuables.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Those from Nazareth cannot accept the messiah
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Rejected at Nazareth; A Prophet Without Honour
\r (Mark 6:1-6; Luke 4:16-30)
\p
\v 53 After \nd Yeshua\nd* had finishedВҰ9173 explaining the parablesВҰ9177, he left that place
\rem /s1 The Rejection of Jesus at Nazareth
\v 54 and went to his hometownВҰ9186 \add of Nazareth\add* and taughtВҰ9188 the people in the JewishВҰ9192 meetingВҰ9192 hallВҰ9192. They were amazedВҰ9195 at his teachingВҰ9188, asking \add each other\add*, вҖңWhere did this fellow get his wisdomВҰ9206 and his ability to do miraclesВҰ9210?
\v 55 Isn't he the son of Yosef, the carpenterВҰ9216? Don't we know his motherВҰ9221 MariaВҰ9224 and his brothersВҰ9227 Yacob and Yosef and SimonВҰ9235 and YudasВҰ9237?
\v 56 Aren't hisВҰ9241 sistersВҰ9240 still here in town? SoВҰ9238 whereВҰ9247 did he get all theseВҰ9250 abilities?вҖқ
\v 57 \x + \xo 13:57: \xt Yhn 4:44.\x*As a result, they didn'tВҰ9263 have any respect for him.
\p ButВҰ9253 \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ9261 to them, вҖң\wj A prophetВҰ9265 is not dishonouredВҰ9266 exceptВҰ9267 in his own hometownВҰ9272 andВҰ9253 among his own householdВҰ9277.\wj*вҖқ
\v 58 SoВҰ9279 he didn'tВҰ9280 do many miraclesВҰ9283 thereВҰ9282 becauseВҰ9285 of theirВҰ9290 unbeliefВҰ9288.
\c 14
\s1 The beheading of Yohan-the-immerser
\rem /s1 The Death of John the Baptist; John the Baptist Beheaded
\r (Mark 6:14-29; Luke 9:7-9)
\p
\v 1 Around that timeВҰ9297, \add King\add* HerodВҰ9299 the Tetrarch heardВҰ9298 the newsВҰ9303 about \nd Yeshua\nd*
\v 2 and he saidВҰ9306 to hisВҰ9309 slaves, вҖңThis must be Yohan-the-immerser having come back from the deadВҰ9324 and so that's why he can do all these miraclesВҰ9329!вҖқ
\p
\v 3 \x + \xo 14:3-4: \xt Luk 3:19-20.\x*HerodВҰ9335 said this because he had previously had Yohan arrested and put in prisonВҰ9346 because of HerodiasВҰ9349, hisВҰ9355 brotherВҰ9354 Philip's wifeВҰ9351.
\v 4 Yohan had been sayingВҰ9356 that it was against God's law for Herod to take his brother's wife.
\v 5 Herod had been wantingВҰ9368 to have Yohan executed, but he was afraidВҰ9372 of the crowdВҰ9374 becauseВҰ9376 they considered Yohan to be a prophetВҰ9378.
\p
\v 6 However at Herod's birthdayВҰ9381 celebrationВҰ9381, Herodias' daughterВҰ9391 had dancedВҰ9389 in the middle of them all andВҰ9399 had pleasedВҰ9400 Herod so much
\v 7 that he promisedВҰ9406 with an oath to giveВҰ9408 her anything that she requestedВҰ9413.
\p
\v 8 The young woman was urgedВҰ9416 on by herВҰ9420 motherВҰ9419 to tell Herod thatВҰ9414 sheВҰ9424 wanted the head of Yohan-the-immerser on a plate.
\p
\v 9 The kingВҰ9437 was upset, but becauseВҰ9438 of his oathsВҰ9441 in front of the other guests, he commandedВҰ9446 it to be so
\v 10 andВҰ9448 sentВҰ9449 \add his soldiers\add* to beheadВҰ9450 YohanВҰ9452 in prisonВҰ9455.
\v 11 SoВҰ9456 then hisВҰ9460 head was brought in on a plate andВҰ9456 givenВҰ9465 to the young woman who then took it to herВҰ9472 motherВҰ9471.
\v 12 \add Hearing the news,\add* Yohan's followers went \add to the prison\add* and collected hisВҰ9477 body and buriedВҰ9484 it. ThenВҰ9473 theyВҰ9489 went and told \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\s1 The feeding of 5,000 families
\rem /s1 Jesus Feeds the Five Thousand; Feeding the Five Thousand; More miracles and teaching
\r (Mark 6:30-44; Luke 9:10-17; Yhn 6:1-14)
\p
\v 13 When \nd Yeshua\nd* heard \add what had happened to Yohan\add*, he got a boatВҰ9500 to take him to a quietВҰ9502 placeВҰ9503 by himselfВҰ9505, but the crowdsВҰ9509 from the citiesВҰ9516 heard about it, andВҰ9494 followedВҰ9510 him around the shore of the lake on footВҰ9513.
\v 14 SoВҰ9517 when he got out of the boat, he sawВҰ9521 a large crowdВҰ9523 of people and he felt compassionВҰ9526 towards them, and he healedВҰ9533 the sickВҰ9536 people \add that they had brought\add*.
\p
\v 15 As eveningВҰ9538 was approachingВҰ9541, his followers came up and asked, вҖңThis placeВҰ9550 is quite isolated and it's alreadyВҰ9554 late. Send the people back into the villagesВҰ9566 so theyВҰ9568 can buy themselvesВҰ9569 something to eat.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖң\wj Oh, there's no need to send them away,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answered. вҖң\wj you all giveВҰ9580 them somethingВҰ9580 to eatВҰ9583.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖңWe don'tВҰ9589 have anythingВҰ9590 hereвҖқ theyВҰ9585 responded, вҖңexceptВҰ9593 for fiveВҰ9595 buns andВҰ9597 twoВҰ9598 \add cooked\add* fish.вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖң\wj Bring them here to me,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua instructed,
\v 19 thenВҰ9608 he told the crowds to sit down on the grassВҰ9623. He took the five buns and two fish and looking up to the sky, he blessedВҰ9638 \add God/the food/the people???\add*, brokeВҰ9640 the buns and gave the pieces to his apprentices to distribute to the crowds.
\v 20 Everyone there ateВҰ9652 enough to be full, andВҰ9651 thenВҰ9651 \add the apprentices\add* picked up twelveВҰ9662 basketsВҰ9663 of leftoverВҰ9659 bread.
\v 21 There were aboutВҰ9671 fiveВҰ9672 thousandВҰ9672 families there.
\s1 Yeshua and Peter walk on the lake
\rem /s1 Jesus Walks on the Water
\r (Mark 6:45-52; Yhn 6:15-21)
\p
\v 22 Straight after thatВҰ9698, Yeshua instructed his apprenticesВҰ9685 to boardВҰ9687 the boatВҰ9690 andВҰ9679 to head back to the other side of the lake while he dismissed the crowdsВҰ9701.
\v 23 He sentВҰ9703 them all back to their homes, thenВҰ9702 climbed up a hill by himselfВҰ9711 to pray.
\v 24 By thenВҰ9720 the boatВҰ9721 was in the middle of the lakeВҰ9731, but it was beingВҰ9734 beaten by the wavesВҰ9737 becauseВҰ9740 a strong windВҰ9743 had come up.
\p
\v 25 In the early hours of the morning, Yeshua wentВҰ9752 out to them on the lakeВҰ9764, walkingВҰ9759 on the surface.
\v 26 When his apprenticesВҰ9768 saw himВҰ9771 coming over the lakeВҰ9778, theyВҰ9789 were worried thinking it was a ghostВҰ9783 andВҰ9785 yelling out in fearВҰ9788.
\p
\v 27 But \nd Yeshua\nd* answered them immediatelyВҰ9790 sayingВҰ9798, вҖң\wj Be brave, I'm here, don'tВҰ9802 worry.\wj*вҖқ
