\r (Mark 7:14-23)
\p
\v 10 ThenВҰ10115 Yeshua calledВҰ10116 out to the crowdВҰ10118, вҖң\wj Listen carefully so you can understandВҰ10123 this:\wj*
\v 11 \wj It's not what goes into your mouth that defiles you, but rather, it's what comes out of your mouth.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 12 His followers then came up to him and told him, вҖңYou know that the Pharisees were offendedВҰ10164 by what you just said?вҖқ
\p
\v 13 вҖң\wj EveryВҰ10169 plant,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answeredВҰ10167, вҖң\wj that wasn't planted by myВҰ10176 heavenlyВҰ10178 fatherВҰ10175 will get pulled out.\wj*
\v 14 \x + \xo 15:14: \xt Luk 6:39.\x*\wj Just ignore them. They are blind guidesВҰ10184, andВҰ10191 if blind people are leading the blind, both of them will stumble into a pit.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ButВҰ10202 PeterВҰ10204 asked himВҰ10206, вҖңSoВҰ10202 interpret the parableВҰ10211 for us.вҖқ
\p
\v 16 вҖң\wj Can't youВҰ10219 all figure it out yet?\wj*вҖқ Yeshua replied.
\v 17 \wj Can't youВҰ10224 all see that everythingВҰ10227 that goes into your mouthВҰ10233, goes down into your stomachВҰ10236 andВҰ10238 then eventually ends up in the toilet?\wj*
\v 18 \x + \xo 15:18: \xt Mat 12:34.\x*\wj But the things that come out of your mouthВҰ10248 are comingВҰ10252 from your mindВҰ10251 andВҰ10254 that's what defilesВҰ10256 a personВҰ10258.\wj*
\v 19 \wj BecauseВҰ10260 lust, murderВҰ10267, adulteryВҰ10269, sexualВҰ10270 immoralityВҰ10270, stealing, falselyВҰ10273 accusing and slanderВҰ10274, these all come of the mindВҰ10262.\wj*
\v 20 \wj It's those things that defile a person, not eating without \+add ceremonially\+add* washing your handsВҰ10287.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The non-Jewish woman with amazing faith
\rem /s1 The Canaanite Woman's Faith; The Faith of the Canaanite Woman; The Faith of a Gentile Woman
\r (Mark 7:24-30)
\p
\v 21 ThenВҰ10294 \nd Yeshua\nd* left Galilee and went out to the districtsВҰ10302 of TyreВҰ10303 and Tsidon.
\v 22 ThenВҰ10306, look, a womanВҰ10308 from that area and of Caananite ancestry came to hum and called out, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ10324\nd*, David's descendant, myВҰ10330 daughterВҰ10329 is suffering from demonВҰ10332 possessionВҰ10332.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 ButВҰ10339 Yeshua didn'tВҰ10335 even answerВҰ10336 her. SoВҰ10339 hisВҰ10343 apprenticesВҰ10342 came up andВҰ10339 suggested, вҖңSend her away becauseВҰ10349 she's still yelling out back there.вҖқ
\p
\v 24 Yeshua answeredВҰ10356, вҖң\wj I was only sentВҰ10359 to the lost sheepВҰ10364 thatВҰ10366 descended from Yisrael.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 25 But sheВҰ10370 came and knelt down in front of himВҰ10375, begging, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ10377\nd*, helpВҰ10378 me.вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖң\wj It's not goodВҰ10387,\wj*вҖқ, Yeshua respondedВҰ10383, вҖң\wj to takeВҰ10388 the children'sВҰ10392 food off them andВҰ10393 throwВҰ10394 itВҰ10394 out to the puppies.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 27 вҖңTrue, \nd masterВҰ10401\nd*,вҖқ she saidВҰ10399, вҖңbutВҰ10398 even the puppies eat the little crumbsВҰ10411 thatВҰ10413 fall off theirВҰ10423 masters' tableВҰ10419.вҖқ
\p
\v 28 вҖң\wj Oh, womanВҰ10431\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ10425, вҖң\wj you have lots of faithВҰ10435, so what you asked for will becomeВҰ10436 reality.\wj*вҖқ And so herВҰ10444 daughterВҰ10443 was healedВҰ10441 that very hourВҰ10447.
\s1 Yeshua heals many different afflictions
\rem /s1 Jesus Cures Many People; Jesus Feeds the Four Thousand; Jesus Heals Many People
\p
\v 29 ThenВҰ10449 \nd Yeshua\nd* left that place and after walking alongВҰ10455 Lake GalileeВҰ10459, he climbed up a hill and sat down.
\v 30 Big crowdsВҰ10470 came up to him, bringing those who were lame, maimedВҰ10481, blindВҰ10482, mute, and many othersВҰ10485, and they laid them down in front of him and he healedВҰ10498 them.
\v 31 The crowdsВҰ10505 marvelledВҰ10507, seeing people speakingВҰ10512 that had been mute, and maimedВҰ10514 people now healthyВҰ10515, and lame people walkingВҰ10518 and the blindВҰ10521 now seeing, and they praised Yisrael's \nd GodВҰ10527\nd*.
\s1 The feeding of 4,000 families
\rem /s1 Jesus Feeds Four Thousand; Feeding the Four Thousand
\r (Mark 8:1-10)
\p
\v 32 ThenВҰ10530 \nd Yeshua\nd* calledВҰ10532 hisВҰ10536 apprenticesВҰ10535 and told them, вҖң\wj I feel sorry for this crowdВҰ10543 becauseВҰ10545 they've been out here with me for threeВҰ10549 daysВҰ10547 and haven't had anythingВҰ10557 to eat, but I'm not happy to just send them away hungryВҰ10563 in case they collapse on the way home.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 33 вҖңOut here in the wildernessВҰ10582,вҖқ replied his apprenticesВҰ10576, вҖңwhereВҰ10578 could we possibly get enough bread to feed a crowdВҰ10589 this size?вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj How many buns do youВҰ10598 have?\wj*вҖқ asked \nd Yeshua\nd*.
\p вҖңSevenВҰ10603,вҖқ, theyВҰ10599 replied, вҖңandВҰ10604 a few smallВҰ10606 fish.вҖқ
\p
\v 35 ThenВҰ10607 instructing the crowdВҰ10615 to sitВҰ10616 down on the groundВҰ10619,
\v 36 he tookВҰ10622 the sevenВҰ10624 buns and the fish, and gave thanksВҰ10631. Then he brokeВҰ10632 them and gave the pieces to his apprentices to distribute to the crowdsВҰ10645.
\v 37 Everyone ateВҰ10647 andВҰ10646 when they were full, they collected sevenВҰ10658 basketsВҰ10659 full of the leftoverВҰ10654 food.
\v 38 There were about fourВҰ10668 thousandВҰ10668 families there.
\p
\v 39 After sending the crowdsВҰ10679 home, Yeshua got into the boatВҰ10685 andВҰ10686 they wentВҰ10687 to the regionsВҰ10691 of MagadanВҰ10693.
\c 16
