\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 16:1: \xt Mat 12:38; Luk 11:16.\x*Some from the Pharisee partyВҰ10697 and some from the Sadducee sect approachedВҰ10695 Yeshua, and trying to temptВҰ10700 him they askedВҰ10701 him to make a signВҰ10705 in the skyВҰ10708 to show \add his power\add* to them.
\v 2 But in answerВҰ10713 heВҰ10711 saidВҰ10714 to them,
\v 3 в—ҳ
\v 4 \x + \xo 16:4: \xt Mat 12:39; Luk 11:29.\x*вҖң\wj This is an evil and adulterousВҰ10755 generationВҰ10752 that's wanting a sign, and no sign will be givenВҰ10763 to it exceptВҰ10765 for the sign of YonahВҰ10769.\wj*вҖқ ThenВҰ10772 he left them and went away.
\s1 The yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees
\rem /s1 The Yeast of the Pharisees and Sadducees
\r (Mark 8:14-21)
\p
\v 5 Now Yeshua's apprenticesВҰ10779 had crossed the lake, but theyВҰ10784 forgotВҰ10784 to takeВҰ10788 any yeast
\v 6 \x + \xo 16:6: \xt Luk 12:1.\x*and \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj Watch out for the yeast from the Pharisees and the Sadducees.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 7 ThisВҰ10813 caused a discussion amongВҰ10809 them trying to figure out if he was scolding them for not bringing any bread.
\p
\v 8 But \nd Yeshua\nd* knew what they were saying, and asked them, вҖң\wj You all with littleВҰ10826 faithВҰ10826. Why are you discussing amongВҰ10824 yourselvesВҰ10825 about not having bread?\wj*
\v 9 \x + \xo 16:9: \xt Mat 14:17-21.\x*\wj Haven't you understoodВҰ10833 what's going on here yet? Don't you rememberВҰ10836 that there were twelve basketsВҰ10847 of leftovers when five buns were used to feed 5,000 families?\wj*
\v 10 \x + \xo 16:10: \xt Mat 15:34-38.\x*\wj And then seven basketsВҰ10859 of leftovers when seven buns were used to feed 4,000 families?\wj*
\v 11 \wj How can you fail to understandВҰ10863 that I wasn't talking to you about bread? Watch out for the yeast from the Pharisees andВҰ10875 Sadducees.\wj*
\p
\v 12 Then they understoodВҰ10884 that he wasn't talking about yeast that's used to make bread, but about the teachingВҰ10903 of the Pharisee partyВҰ10905 and of the Sadducee sect.
\s1 Peter acknowledges Yeshua as God's son
\rem /s1 Jesus the Son of God; Peter's Confession of Christ; Peter's Declaration about Jesus
\r (Mark 8:27-30; Luke 9:18-21)
\p
\v 13 When \nd Yeshua\nd* arrived in the outskirts of CaesareaВҰ10918 PhilippiВҰ10920, he asked hisВҰ10924 apprenticesВҰ10923, вҖң\wj Who are peopleВҰ10931 saying thatВҰ10919 humanity's child \+em is\+em*?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 16:14: \xt Mat 14:1-2; Mrk 6:14-15; Luk 9:7-8.\x*вҖңSome say Yohan-the-immerser \add come back to life\add*,вҖқ theyВҰ10939 answered, вҖңbut others say the \add promised prophet\add* Eliyah, andВҰ10940 others, Jeremiah or one of the other prophets.вҖқ
\p
\v 15 вҖң\wj But you yourselves,\wj*вҖқ he asked, вҖң\wj Who do \+em you\+em* say I am?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 16:16: \xt Yhn 6:68-69.\x*вҖңYou are the \add promised\add* \nd messiahВҰ10977\nd*,вҖқ SimonВҰ10970 PeterВҰ10971 answeredВҰ10968, вҖңthe son of the livingВҰ10984 \nd GodВҰ10981\nd*.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 ThenВҰ10988 \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ10987, вҖң\wj You are blessedВҰ10993, SimonВҰ10995 BarYonah, becauseВҰ10997 itВҰ11002 wasn't any person that revealedВҰ11002 that to youВҰ11003, butВҰ11004 rather, myВҰ11007 fatherВҰ11006 who is in the heavensВҰ11011.\wj*
\v 18 \wj And I can add that you are PeterВҰ11019 \+add (meaning вҖҳrockвҖҷ)\+add* and I will buildВҰ11028 myВҰ11029 assemblyВҰ11031 on this rock and the gatesВҰ11034 of hell won'tВҰ11036 be able to hold it back.\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 16:19: \xt Mat 18:18; Yhn 20:23.\x*\wj I've give you the keys of the heavenlyВҰ11048 kingdomВҰ11046, and whatever you restrain on the earth will be restrained in the heavens, and whatever you free on the earth, will be freed in the heavens.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 20 Then he instructedВҰ11078 his apprenticesВҰ11081 not to tell anyoneВҰ11084 that he is the \nd messiahВҰ11092\nd*.
\s1 Yeshua talks about future suffering and death
\rem /s1 Jesus Foretells His Death and Resurrection; Jesus Speaks about His Suffering and Death; Jesus Predicts His Death
\r (Mark 8:31вҖ“9:1; Luke 9:22-27)
\p
\v 21 From that time onwards, \nd Yeshua\nd* beganВҰ11096 showingВҰ11100 hisВҰ11104 apprenticesВҰ11103 that he needed to goВҰ11112 to Yerushalem and to sufferВҰ11115 at the hands of the eldersВҰ11119 and chiefВҰ11121 priestsВҰ11121 and teachersВҰ11123 of the law there, before being executed and then coming back to life on the thirdВҰ11129 dayВҰ11131.
\p
\v 22 ButВҰ11135 PeterВҰ11139 took him asideВҰ11136 andВҰ11135 started telling him off, sayingВҰ11149, вҖңGoodness gracious, \nd masterВҰ11152\nd*, this certainly won'tВҰ11154 happen to you.вҖқ
\p
\v 23 Yeshua turnedВҰ11162 towards PeterВҰ11165 and saidВҰ11163, вҖң\wj Get behindВҰ11167 me, SatanВҰ11169. You're temptingВҰ11170 me becauseВҰ11175 youВҰ11177 not thinkingВҰ11177 in a godly way, butВҰ11181 only in humanВҰ11185 terms.\wj*вҖқ
\rem /s1 The Cross and Self-Denial
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 16:24: \xt Mat 10:38; Luk 14:27.\x*Then \nd Yeshua\nd* told hisВҰ11193 apprenticesВҰ11192, вҖң\wj If anyoneВҰ11195 wants to be my follower, they need to suppress their own desires and be ready to sacrifice and to suffer, and then follow me.\wj*
\v 25 \x + \xo 16:25: \xt Mat 10:39; Luk 17:33; Yhn 12:25.\x*\wj BecauseВҰ11212 anyone who wants to save their life will lose it, but anyone who loses their life on my accountВҰ11230, will be findingВҰ11232 it.\wj*
\v 26 \wj What help would it be to a person if they gain everything in the worldВҰ11241, and yet lose their soul? Or \+add put another way\+add*, what could a person give in exchangeВҰ11253 for their soul?\wj*
\v 27 \x + \xo 16:27: a \xt Mat 25:31; \xo b \xt Psa 62:12; Rom 2:6.\x*\wj BecauseВҰ11258 humanity's child is goingВҰ11257 to return displaying the splendour of his fatherВҰ11268 and accompanied by his messengersВҰ11273, and then he'll reward each individual accordingВҰ11282 to their behaviour.\wj*
\v 28 \wj I can assure youВҰ11290 that some people standing here won'tВҰ11300 experience deathВҰ11302 untilВҰ11303 theyВҰ11305 first seeВҰ11305 humanity's child comingВҰ11310 in hisВҰ11314 kingdomВҰ11313.\wj*вҖқ
\c 17
\s1 Yeshua's face shines brightly
\rem /s1 The Transfiguration
\r (Mark 9:2-13; Luke 9:28-36)
\p
\v 1 After sixВҰ11319 daysВҰ11318, \nd Yeshua\nd* took PeterВҰ11324, and Yacob and hisВҰ11333 brotherВҰ11332 Yohan, and they went up a highВҰ11340 hill by themselvesВҰ11343,
\v 2 and Yeshua was changed in front of them so that his faceВҰ11354 shone like the sunВҰ11358 and his clothesВҰ11361 becameВҰ11363 as whiteВҰ11365 as the lightВҰ11368.
\v 3 ThenВҰ11370 look, Mosheh and Eliyah appearedВҰ11373 and they could seeВҰ11371 them talking with Yeshua.
\v 4 ThenВҰ11383 PeterВҰ11385 spoke up and saidВҰ11386 to \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ11389\nd*, it's goodВҰ11390 that we're here. If you want, I could make threeВҰ11400 shelters here: one for you and one for Mosheh and one for Eliyah.вҖқ
\p
\v 5 \x + \xo 17:5: a \xt Gen 22:2; Psa 2:7; Isa 42:1; Mat 3:17; 12:18; Mrk 1:11; Luk 3:22; \xo b \xt Deu 18:15.\x*While he was stillВҰ11414 speakingВҰ11416, a brightВҰ11419 cloud came over the top of them and wowВҰ11417, a voiceВҰ11425 came out of the cloud sayingВҰ11429, вҖңThis is myВҰ11434 dear son that I get great pleasureВҰ11439 from. Just listen to him.вҖқ
\p
\v 6 When the \add three\add* apprenticesВҰ11447 heardВҰ11444 the voice, theyВҰ11453 lay faceВҰ11450 down andВҰ11452 were extremely scared.
\v 7 ButВҰ11455 \nd Yeshua\nd* went across to them, and touchingВҰ11462 them he saidВҰ11465, вҖң\wj Get up now and don'tВҰ11469 be afraid,\wj*вҖқ
\v 8 andВҰ11472 when they looked around, they didn't see anyoneВҰ11477 other than \nd YeshuaВҰ11484\nd* himselfВҰ11482.
\p
\v 9 As they started heading down the hill, \nd Yeshua\nd* instructedВҰ11495 them, вҖң\wj Don't tell anyoneВҰ11500 what youВҰ11501 saw untilВҰ11504 after humanity's child comes back to life.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 10 \x + \xo 17:10: \xt Mal 4:5.\x*SoВҰ11515 hisВҰ11520 apprenticesВҰ11519 askedВҰ11516 him, вҖңWhy do the religiousВҰ11525 teachersВҰ11525 say that Eliyah has to comeВҰ11531 \add before the messiah\add*?вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj In a way, Eliyah is comingВҰ11542\wj*вҖқ he saidВҰ11537, вҖң\wj andВҰ11534 he will restoreВҰ11545 everything.\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 17:12: \xt Mat 11:14.\x*\wj But I'm also telling you that in another way, Eliyah alreadyВҰ11553 cameВҰ11554 and they didn'tВҰ11556 recognise him, but they \+add mistreated\+add* him just however they wantedВҰ11564, and humanity's child will sufferВҰ11572 from their actions like that too.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 13 ThenВҰ11581 the apprenticesВҰ11578 realised that he was talking to them about Yohan-the-immerser.
\s1 Yeshua drives a demon out of a boy
\rem /s1 The Healing of a Boy With a Demon; Jesus Heals a Demon-Possessed Boy; Jesus Cures a Boy with a Demon; Jesus Heals a Boy with a Demon
\r (Mark 9:14-29; Luke 9:37-43a)
\p
\v 14 When they got back to the crowdВҰ11602, a manВҰ11605 approachedВҰ11603 Yeshua andВҰ11596 knelt down beforeВҰ11609 him
\v 15 sayingВҰ11612, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ11613\nd*, show mercyВҰ11614 to myВҰ11615 son, becauseВҰ11619 he has seizures and isn't well, often fallingВҰ11627 into the fireВҰ11630 or the waterВҰ11636.
\v 16 I broughtВҰ11638 him to yourВҰ11642 apprenticesВҰ11641, but they weren't able to healВҰ11647 him.вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖң\wj Oh you unbelievingВҰ11659 andВҰ11651 depraved generationВҰ11658,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ11650, вҖң\wj how much longer will I have to be with you all? How much longer can I tolerateВҰ11670 you all? Bring yourВҰ11671 son here to me.\wj*вҖқ
\v 18 ThenВҰ11676 \nd YeshuaВҰ11680\nd* rebukedВҰ11677 the demonВҰ11686 and itВҰ11678 cameВҰ11682 out of himВҰ11684, and the boyВҰ11690 was healedВҰ11688 that very hourВҰ11693.
\p
\v 19 Later the apprenticesВҰ11698 went by themselvesВҰ11702 to \nd Yeshua\nd* and asked him how come they hadn't been able to drive away the demon.
\p
\v 20 \x + \xo 17:20: \xt Mat 21:21; Mrk 11:23; 1Cor 13:2.\x*вҖң\wj It's because your faith is so smallВҰ11720,\wj*вҖқ he told them, вҖң\wj because I can assure you that if your faith was a big as a mustardВҰ11734 seed, you'd be able to command a mountainВҰ11737 to move and it would move, and thenВҰ11713 there'dВҰ11742 be nothingВҰ11746 that you all couldn't do.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua speaks again about his forthcoming death
\rem /s1 Jesus Again Predicts His Death; Jesus Speaks Again about His Death
\r (Mark 9:30-32; Luke 9:43b-45)
\p
\v 21 в—ҳ
\rem /s1 Jesus Again Foretells His Death and Resurrection
\v 22 Another time when they were all together in GalileeВҰ11769, \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj Humanity's child is goingВҰ11774 to be handed over to the peopleВҰ11782,\wj*
\v 23 \wj and they're going to kill himВҰ11785 and thenВҰ11795 he'll come back to life on the thirdВҰ11789 dayВҰ11791.\wj*вҖқ \add Those listening\add* were very upset.
\s1 Paying the temple tax
\rem /s1 Payment of the Temple Tax; Jesus and the Temple Tax
\p
\v 24 \x + \xo 17:24: \xt Exo 30:13; 38:26.\x*ThenВҰ11800 when they got to CapernaumВҰ11803, the tax-collectors collecting the poll tax approachedВҰ11804 PeterВҰ11811 andВҰ11812 asked him, вҖңIsn't yourВҰ11818 teacherВҰ11817 going to pay the tax?вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңYes, he will.вҖқ replied Peter.
\p ThenВҰ11827 when he went inside the houseВҰ11838, before he could say anything \nd Yeshua\nd* asked him, вҖң\wj What do you think, SimonВҰ11847? Do earthlyВҰ11851 kingsВҰ11849 extract taxes from theirВҰ11862 own children, or from strangersВҰ11866?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 26 вҖңFrom strangers,вҖқ answered PeterВҰ11871.
\p вҖң\wj SoВҰ11878 surelyВҰ11888 the children are exempt?\wj*вҖқ, \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ11877,
\v 27 вҖң\wj butВҰ11894 so that we don'tВҰ11895 offendВҰ11896 them, go down to the lakeВҰ11901 and throwВҰ11902 in a line. Pull out the firstВҰ11908 fish that you hook, and when you open itsВҰ11915 mouthВҰ11914, you'll find a coin that'll be enough to pay the tax for both of us.\wj*вҖқ
\c 18
\s1 Who is the greatest?
\rem /s1 True Greatness; Who Is the Greatest?; The Greatest in the Kingdom of Heaven; Teaching about the kingdom
\r (Mark 9:33-37; Luke 9:46-48; 17:1-2)
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 18:1: \xt Luk 22:24.\x*Around that time his apprenticesВҰ11934 approachedВҰ11932 \nd Yeshua\nd* and asked him, вҖңSo who will be the greatestВҰ11940 in the heavenlyВҰ11947 kingdomВҰ11945?вҖқ
\p
\v 2 Yeshua calledВҰ11949 in a smallВҰ11952 child andВҰ11948 stoodВҰ11953 the child in the middle of the room
\v 3 \x + \xo 18:3: \xt Mrk 10:15; Luk 18:17.\x*and saidВҰ11960, вҖң\wj I can assure you all that if you don'tВҰ11965 turn and becomeВҰ11968 like a smallВҰ11971 childВҰ11971, you all certainly won'tВҰ11965 enter the heavenlyВҰ11979 kingdomВҰ11977,\wj*
\v 4 \wj so anyone who humblesВҰ11983 themself like this smallВҰ11988 childВҰ11988 is greaterВҰ11993 in the heavenlyВҰ12000 kingdomВҰ11997.\wj*
\v 5 \wj AnyoneВҰ12006 who receives a smallВҰ12007 childВҰ12007 like this in myВҰ12015 nameВҰ12014, is receivingВҰ12017 me,\wj*
\rem /s1 Temptations to Sin
\rem /r (Mark 9.42-48; Luke 17.1,2)
\p
\v 6 вҖң\wj But anyoneВҰ12022 who causes one of theseВҰ12025 smallВҰ12024 ones who believeВҰ12027 in me to stumbleВҰ12021, itВҰ12030 would have been better for thatВҰ12026 person if a heavyВҰ12035 stoneВҰ12034 had been hung aroundВҰ12036 their neck andВҰ12042 if they'd been sunk in the deep lakeВҰ12048.\wj*
\v 7 \wj The worldВҰ12051 suffers due to temptations, becauseВҰ12052 it's necessaryВҰ12055 for temptations to comeВҰ12058, but it won't be good for the personВҰ12066 who brings the temptation.\wj*
\p
\v 8 \x + \xo 18:8: \xt Mat 5:30.\x*вҖң\wj If yourВҰ12077 handВҰ12076 or footВҰ12080 causes you to stumbleВҰ12082, cut it off and throwВҰ12089 it away because it's betterВҰ12092 for you to enter \+add eternal\+add* lifeВҰ12098 maimedВҰ12101 or lame than to be thrown into the eternal fireВҰ12116 with two handsВҰ12108 and feetВҰ12111.\wj*
\v 9 \x + \xo 18:9: \xt Mat 5:29.\x*\wj Also if yourВҰ12126 eye causes you to stumbleВҰ12127, pluckВҰ12129 it out andВҰ12121 throw it away because it's betterВҰ12135 for you to enter \+add eternal\+add* life with only one eye than to be thrown into the pit of fire with two eyesВҰ12145.\wj*
\s1 Finding the lost sheep
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Lost Sheep
\r (Luke 15:3-7)
\p
\v 10 вҖң\wj Make sure that you all don'tВҰ12154 despiseВҰ12155 any of theseВҰ12160 smallВҰ12159 ones, becauseВҰ12166 I'm telling you all that theirВҰ12171 messengersВҰ12170 in the heavens are always in front of myВҰ12183 fatherВҰ12182 who is in the heavens.\wj*
\rem /s1 Story of the Lost Sheep
\p
\v 11 в—ҳ\f + \fr 18:11 \ft Some Greek manuscripts add in the text of Luke 19:10 here: because humanity's child came to look for those who are lost, and save them.\f*
\v 12 вҖң\wj What do you think about this: a manВҰ12204 had a hundredВҰ12205 sheep and one of them strayed away. Won't he leave the ninety-nine there in the hills and go and look for the sheep that was missing?\wj*
\v 13 \wj And if he happens to find it, I can assure you that he'll be happier about that one than about the ninety-nine who never strayedВҰ12249 away.\wj*
\v 14 \wj In the same way, yourВҰ12259 fatherВҰ12256 in the heavensВҰ12263 doesn't want \+add even\+add* one of theseВҰ12270 smallВҰ12269 ones to perishВҰ12265.\wj*
\s1 Confronting an offender
\rem /s1 Correcting a Fellow Believer; When Someone Sins; Reproving Another Who Sins; A Brother Who Sins Against You
\p
\v 15 \x + \xo 18:15: \xt Luk 17:3.\x*вҖң\wj If a fellow believer sins, go where there's just the two of you andВҰ12272 rebukeВҰ12281 that person privately. If they listenВҰ12291 to you, you have gainedВҰ12292 \+add back\+add* a fellow believer.\wj*
\v 16 \x + \xo 18:16: \xt Deu 19:15.\x*\wj But if they don'tВҰ12298 listenВҰ12299 to you, takeВҰ12300 one or two others with you, so that there'll be two or threeВҰ12316 witnessesВҰ12314 to verify the messageВҰ12320.\wj*
\v 17 \wj ThenВҰ12322 if that person still refuses to listenВҰ12323, tell the \+add whole\+add* assembly. If they \+add still\+add* refuse to hear from the assembly, treat them like a non-believer or a tax-collector.\wj*\f + \fr 18:17 \ft Some might read this as a command to shun the person, but perhaps it would be better read as вҖҳtreat them as a lost person who needs to be savedвҖҷ?\f*
\s1 Restricting and releasing
\rem /s1 Prohibiting and Permitting
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 18:18: \xt Mat 16:19; Yhn 20:23.\x*вҖң\wj I can assure you that whatever you restrain on the earth will be restrained in heaven, and what ever you set free on the earth will be set free in heaven.\wj*
\p
\v 19 вҖң\wj Again, I can assure you that if twoВҰ12386 of you on earthВҰ12396 agreeВҰ12390 about anything they requestВҰ12405 \+add in prayer\+add*, then myВҰ12412 fatherВҰ12411 who is in the heavensВҰ12415 will action itВҰ12406,\wj*
\v 20 \wj becauseВҰ12420 any place whereВҰ12417 twoВҰ12422 or threeВҰ12424 people have gatheredВҰ12425 togetherВҰ12425 in my nameВҰ12429 and authority, I will be thereВҰ12433 right among them.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The importance of forgiveness
\rem /s1 Story of the Unforgiving Debtor; The Parable of the Unforgiving Servant; The Parable of the Unmerciful Servant; Forgiveness
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 18:21-22: \xt Luk 17:3-4.\x*Then PeterВҰ12442 approachedВҰ12439 Yeshua and asked, вҖң\nd MasterВҰ12445\nd*, how oftenВҰ12446 can someone sin againstВҰ12449 me and I'll still have to forgiveВҰ12457 them?вҖқ
\p
\v 22 \x + \xo 18:22: \xt Gen 4:24.\x*вҖң\wj I won'tВҰ12465 say seven times,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj but seventy times seven times!\wj*
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Unforgiving Servant
\p
\v 23 вҖң\wj It's because of this that the heavenlyВҰ12482 kingdomВҰ12480 can be likenedВҰ12477 to a kingВҰ12484 who wantedВҰ12486 to settleВҰ12487 accountsВҰ12487 with hisВҰ12492 slavesВҰ12491.\wj*
\v 24 \wj SoВҰ12494 when he began the process, a man was broughtВҰ12497 in who owed him millions,\wj*
\v 25 \wj butВҰ12508 since he had no way of repaying it, the masterВҰ12514 commandedВҰ12511 for him and hisВҰ12509 wifeВҰ12519 and childrenВҰ12524 and all their possessions to be sold to help pay off the debt.\wj*
\v 26 \wj Then that slaveВҰ12537 dropped to the ground and prostratedВҰ12539 himself to the master, sayingВҰ12541, вҖҳMasterВҰ12542, give me a little more time and then I'll be able to repay it all to youВҰ12551.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 27 \wj SoВҰ12553 the masterВҰ12555 felt sorry for that slaveВҰ12557 and sentВҰ12559 him away and forgaveВҰ12566 his loan.\wj*
\p
\v 28 вҖң\wj But when the slaveВҰ12571 got outside, he foundВҰ12573 one of his fellow-slaves who owed him a few thousand. He grabbed him and was stranglingВҰ12587 him with his hands sayingВҰ12588, вҖҳGive back what you owe!вҖҷ\wj*
\v 29 \wj The fellowВҰ12598 slave dropped to the ground and begged him, вҖҳGive me a little more time and I'll repay you.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 30 \wj ButВҰ12618 the other wasn't willingВҰ12620, and he went and had the man thrownВҰ12625 into prisonВҰ12628 untilВҰ12629 he repaid what he owed.\wj*
\v 31 \wj The other slaves who had observed all this were very upset, so they went and informed the masterВҰ12654 about what had happened.\wj*
\v 32 \wj So then the masterВҰ12665 calledВҰ12662 in \+add the slave that he had forgiven\+add* and told him, вҖҳYou evil slave! I forgaveВҰ12676 you all that obligationВҰ12674 becauseВҰ12678 you pleaded with me.\wj*
\v 33 \wj Wouldn't it have been reasonable for you also to have shownВҰ12695 mercy to yourВҰ12689 fellow-slave just like I was merciful to you?вҖҷ\wj*
\v 34 \wj Now the masterВҰ12700 who was now quite angry, handed him over to the torturers untilВҰ12706 he could repay everythingВҰ12709 thatВҰ12707 he owed.\wj*
\p
\v 35 вҖң\wj So that's how myВҰ12719 heavenlyВҰ12721 fatherВҰ12718 will treat you if you don'tВҰ12726 genuinely forgiveВҰ12727 others around you.\wj*вҖқ
\c 19
\s1 Yeshua answers about divorce
\rem /s1 Discussion about Divorce and Marriage; Teaching about Divorce; Jesus Teaches about Divorce; On the road to Jerusalem
\r (Mark 10:1-12)
\p
\v 1 When \nd Yeshua\nd* had finishedВҰ12743 theseВҰ12749 messagesВҰ12748, he left GalileeВҰ12753 andВҰ12739 wentВҰ12757 to the Yudean regionsВҰ12760 on the other side of the YordanВҰ12766 River
\v 2 and large crowdsВҰ12770 followedВҰ12768 himВҰ12769, and heВҰ12773 healedВҰ12773 them.
\p
\v 3 Some from the Pharisees' partyВҰ12780 approachedВҰ12777 him to test him by asking, вҖңIs there any causeВҰ12796 for which a man can dismiss hisВҰ12793 wifeВҰ12792?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 \x + \xo 19:4: \xt Gen 1:27; 5:2.\x*вҖң\wj Haven't you read,\wj*вҖқ he replied, вҖң\wj thatВҰ12797 \+add God\+add* made them male andВҰ12798 femaleВҰ12812 from the beginningВҰ12809?\wj*
\v 5 \x + \xo 19:5: \xt Gen 2:24.\x*\wj And then how he saidВҰ12817, вҖҳA manВҰ12821 will leave his parents and be joinedВҰ12830 togetherВҰ12830 with his wifeВҰ12833, and then the twoВҰ12838 of them will be a single bodyВҰ12840вҖҷ?\wj*
\v 6 \wj SoВҰ12851 then, they're no longerВҰ12843 twoВҰ12845 butВҰ12846 are now one bodyВҰ12847, therefore don'tВҰ12858 let any person separateВҰ12860 what \+nd GodВҰ12853\+nd* has joinedВҰ12854 togetherВҰ12854.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 7 \x + \xo 19:7: \xt Deu 24:1-4; Mat 5:31.\x*вҖңSoВҰ12864 why did MoshehВҰ12866 allow us to giveВҰ12868 her a letter of divorceВҰ12870 and then to sendВҰ12872 her away?вҖқ they asked himВҰ12862.
\p
\v 8 вҖң\wj It was becauseВҰ12883 of your hard heartsВҰ12885 that Mosheh allowed you to sendВҰ12890 away your wife,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answered, вҖң\wj but itВҰ12898 wasn't like that at the beginningВҰ12895.\wj*
\v 9 \x + \xo 19:9: \xt Mat 5:32; 1Cor 7:10-11.\x*\wj Now I'm telling youВҰ12903 that anyone who sends away hisВҰ12912 wifeВҰ12910 because of sexualВҰ12918 immoralityВҰ12918 andВҰ12920 thenВҰ12902 remarries, is \+add also\+add* causing adultery. Also the woman who was sentВҰ12931 away if she remarries, she causes adultery.\wj*
\p
\v 10 His followers made the point, вҖңIf that's the case for husbandВҰ12949 and wifeВҰ12953, it's better not to get married.вҖқ
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj Not everyone can acceptВҰ12963 this,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ12959, вҖң\wj butВҰ12967 only thoseВҰ12967 with a special gift.\wj*
\v 12 \wj BecauseВҰ12971 there are some men who are born from their mother'sВҰ12976 womb without testicles, there are some who've been castrated by others, and there are some who castrate themselvesВҰ12992 becauseВҰ12993 of the heavenlyВҰ12997 kingdomВҰ12995. Anyone who is able to accept this can accept it.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua blesses the children
\rem /s1 The Little Children and Jesus; Jesus Blesses Little Children; Jesus Blesses the Children
\r (Mark 10:13-16; Luke 18:15-17)
\p
\v 13 Then some smallВҰ13007 childrenВҰ13007 were broughtВҰ13005 to Yeshua hoping that he would place his handsВҰ13011 on them and pray for them, but the apprenticesВҰ13018 scolded them.
\v 14 But \nd Yeshua\nd* intervened, вҖң\wj Be patient with the children and don'tВҰ13031 stop them from coming to me, becauseВҰ13039 it's ones like these that make up the heavenlyВҰ13045 kingdomВҰ13043.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 15 ThenВҰ13046 after placing his handsВҰ13050 on them, heВҰ13054 left that place.
\s1 Answering the rich man
\rem /s1 The Rich Young Man
\r (Mark 10:17-31; Luke 18:18-30)
\p
\v 16 And look, a man approachedВҰ13059 Yeshua andВҰ13056 asked himВҰ13062, вҖңTeacherВҰ13064, what goodВҰ13067 thing do I need to do in orderВҰ13070 to have eternalВҰ13075 lifeВҰ13073?вҖқ
\p
\v 17 вҖң\wj Why are you askingВҰ13083 me aboutВҰ13085 what's good?\wj*вҖқ Yeshua respondedВҰ13079. вҖң\wj \+add Only\+add* one is good. ButВҰ13078 if you'reВҰ13100 wantingВҰ13100 to enter into lifeВҰ13104, you should obey \+add God's\+add* commandsВҰ13110.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 18 \x + \xo 19:18: a \xt Exo 20:13; Deu 5:17; \xo b \xt Exo 20:14; Deu 5:18; \xo c \xt Exo 20:15; Deu 5:19; \xo d \xt Exo 20:16; Deu 5:20.\x*вҖңWhichВҰ13113 ones?вҖқ he asked.
\p вҖң\wj Don't murderВҰ13122,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answered, вҖң\wj don't mess with another person's spouse, don't stealВҰ13126, don't lie in court,\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 19:19: a \xt Exo 20:12; Deu 5:16; \xo b \xt Lev 19:18.\x*\wj honourВҰ13129 your parents, and love your neighbourВҰ13139 like yourselfВҰ13142.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 20 вҖңI've keptВҰ13151 all of those,вҖқ the youngВҰ13146 manВҰ13146 said, вҖңso what else do I need to do?вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖң\wj If you want to be perfectВҰ13165,\wj*вҖқ answered \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\wj go and sell what you own and giveВҰ13174 to the poor, and then you'll have treasureВҰ13180 in the heavensВҰ13182. Then comeВҰ13185 and followВҰ13186 me.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 22 But when the youngВҰ13191 manВҰ13191 heardВҰ13188 that, he wentВҰ13195 away despondent becauseВҰ13198 he owned many propertiesВҰ13201.
\p
\v 23 SoВҰ13204 \nd Yeshua\nd* saidВҰ13206 to hisВҰ13209 apprenticesВҰ13208, вҖң\wj I can assure youВҰ13212 that it's \+add more\+add* difficultВҰ13216 for a wealthyВҰ13215 person to enter the heavenlyВҰ13222 kingdomВҰ13220.\wj*
\v 24 \wj In fact, it's easierВҰ13228 for a camelВҰ13230 to go through the eyeВҰ13233 of a needleВҰ13236 than for a wealthyВҰ13240 person to enter God's kingdomВҰ13244.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 25 When his apprenticesВҰ13251 heardВҰ13248 that, they were very surprised andВҰ13249 asked, вҖңWell, who can be savedВҰ13261 thenВҰ13249?вҖқ
\p
\v 26 \nd Yeshua\nd* looked them in the eyes andВҰ13263 answered, вҖң\wj It's impossibleВҰ13272 for humansВҰ13269, butВҰ13275 with \+nd GodВҰ13277\+nd*, everything is possibleВҰ13279.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 27 вҖңHey,вҖқ PeterВҰ13285 reacted, вҖңweВҰ13289 left everything to followВҰ13293 youВҰ13295, so what will happen to us?вҖқ
\p
\v 28 \x + \xo 19:28: a \xt Mat 25:31; \xo b \xt Luk 22:30.\x*вҖң\wj I can assure you all,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* respondedВҰ13303. вҖң\wj that afterВҰ13313 \+add the world\+add* is remade andВҰ13301 I sit down on hisВҰ13326 splendid throneВҰ13324, all of you who followedВҰ13312 me will also sit on twelve thronesВҰ13333 ruling over the twelve tribesВҰ13337 of Yisrael.\wj*
\v 29 \wj And everyoneВҰ13341 who left their housesВҰ13345, or brothersВҰ13347 or sistersВҰ13349, or fatherВҰ13351 or motherВҰ13353, or wifeВҰ13355 or childrenВҰ13357, or farmsВҰ13359 on accountВҰ13362 of myВҰ13364 nameВҰ13365 and commission, will be repaid a hundredВҰ13367 times over and will inheritВҰ13374 eternalВҰ13373 lifeВҰ13372.\wj*
\s1 The last will be first
\rem /s1 The Labourers in the Vineyard; The Workers in the Vineyard; The Parable of the Workers in the Vineyard; Story of the Vineyard Workers
\p
\v 30 \x + \xo 19:30: \xt Mat 20:16; Luk 13:30.\x*вҖң\wj But many who are first will end up last, andВҰ13381 the last will be first\wj*
\c 20
\nb
\v 1 \wj becauseВҰ13388 the heavenlyВҰ13393 kingdomВҰ13391 is like a landowner who cameВҰ13397 out in the morningВҰ13399 to hire labourers to work in hisВҰ13405 vineyardВҰ13404.\wj*
\v 2 \wj They all agreedВҰ13407 on the rate for the dayВҰ13415 andВҰ13408 thenВҰ13408 he sentВҰ13416 them off to work in hisВҰ13421 vineyardВҰ13420.\wj*
\v 3 \wj ThenВҰ13422 around 9am he noticed some othersВҰ13432 standing idle in the marketplaceВҰ13436,\wj*
\v 4 \wj and he told them, вҖҳYou can go and work in the vineyardВҰ13447 and I'll pay you all a fair day's wage at the end.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 5 \wj SoВҰ13458 they wentВҰ13459 off. ThenВҰ13458 he came out around midday and againВҰ13460 at 3pm and did the same.\wj*
\v 6 \wj When he came out around 5pm andВҰ13473 there were still people just standing around, he asked them, вҖҳWhy have you been idly standing here all dayВҰ13492?вҖҷ\wj*
\v 7 \wj вҖҳBecauseВҰ13496 no one has hiredВҰ13499 us,вҖҷ they said. So he also sent them off to work in the vineyardВҰ13507.\wj*
\p
\v 8 \x + \xo 20:8: \xt Lev 19:13; Deu 24:15.\x*вҖң\wj In the eveningВҰ13515, the landowner instructed hisВҰ13525 managerВҰ13524, вҖҳCall the workersВҰ13528 andВҰ13529 giveВҰ13530 them their wages, going from the last to start until the firstВҰ13540.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 9 \wj The ones who'd started late afternoon each receivedВҰ13550 the day's wage that the first workers had been promised,\wj*
\v 10 \wj so those firstВҰ13557 ones expected they'd receiveВҰ13563 more, but they all got the same day's wage.\wj*
\v 11 \wj When theyВҰ13576 got theirs, the first workers started grumblingВҰ13576 about the landowner\wj*
\v 12 \wj and complained, вҖҳTheseВҰ13585 last ones only worked an hourВҰ13589, and yet youВҰ13597 paid them the same as us who worked the entire dayВҰ13603 right through the scorchingВҰ13606 heat!вҖҷ\wj*
\v 13 \wj вҖҳBuddy,вҖҷ heВҰ13607 saidВҰ13614 to one of them, вҖҳI'm not cheating you. Didn't you agreeВҰ13621 to work for me for the daily wage?\wj*
\v 14 \wj Take what we agreed on andВҰ13626 go, butВҰ13630 I wanted to giveВҰ13636 these last workers the same amount.\wj*
\v 15 \wj Or aren'tВҰ13642 I permittedВҰ13644 to do what I want with my own \+add money\+add*? Or is yourВҰ13658 eyeВҰ13657 evilВҰ13659 just becauseВҰ13661 I am generous?вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 20:16: \xt Mat 19:30; Mrk 10:31; Luk 13:30.\x*вҖң\wj So the last will be first like that, andВҰ13670 the first will be last.\wj*вҖқ
