\p
\v 24 Now the other tenВҰ13867 who'd heardВҰ13865 all this, took offence at the twoВҰ13873 brothersВҰ13874
\v 25 \x + \xo 20:25-26: \xt Luk 22:25-26.\x*butВҰ13876 \nd Yeshua\nd* calledВҰ13878 them \add over\add* andВҰ13891 saidВҰ13880, вҖң\wj You all know that the rulersВҰ13885 of other nations practice total control over their people, as do other powerful people.\wj*
\v 26 \x + \xo 20:26-27: \xt Mat 23:11; Mrk 9:35; Luk 22:26.\x*\wj But among all of you, it shouldn'tВҰ13896 be like that. Instead anyone who wants to becomeВҰ13912 greatВҰ13911 should be yourВҰ13917 servantВҰ13918,\wj*
\v 27 \wj andВҰ13919 anyone who wants to be firstВҰ13928, should be yourВҰ13932 slaveВҰ13933,\wj*
\v 28 \wj in the same way that humanity's child didn'tВҰ13939 come to be servedВҰ13941, butВҰ13942 to serveВҰ13943 \+add others\+add* andВҰ13944 to giveВҰ13945 hisВҰ13948 lifeВҰ13947 as a ransomВҰ13949 for many people.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua heals two blind men
