\v 18 In the morningВҰ14472 as he headed back into the cityВҰ14481, Yeshua was hungry.
\v 19 He saw a single fig tree near the road, but when he got close, it only had leavesВҰ14502 on it, so he spoke to it, вҖң\wj You will never again bear fruit,\wj*вҖқ andВҰ14483 immediatelyВҰ14520 the fig tree witheredВҰ14519 up.
\p
\v 20 His followers who saw this happen were amazed andВҰ14523 asked \add each other\add*, вҖңHow did that treeВҰ14533 instantly witherВҰ14531 up?вҖқ
\p
\v 21 \x + \xo 21:21: \xt Mat 17:20; 1Cor 13:2.\x*вҖң\wj I can assure you all,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ14534, вҖң\wj if you have faithВҰ14545 and don'tВҰ14547 doubtВҰ14548, not only could you do that to a figВҰ14553 treeВҰ14553, you could tell this hill to move away and go into the seaВҰ14568, and itВҰ14569 would happen.\wj*
\v 22 \wj You'd be able to do everythingвҖ”anything that you requestВҰ14575 in prayerВҰ14578 andВҰ14570 believeВҰ14579.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The source of Yeshua's authority
