\rem /s1 Story of the Two Sons; The Parable of the Two Sons
\p вҖң\wj \+add Well thenВҰ14692,\+add* nor will I tell youВҰ14708 about my authorityВҰ14712 to do theseВҰ14713 things,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answered.
\s1 The parable about obedience
\p
\v 28 вҖң\wj ButВҰ14726 what does it matter to you all, anyway? There was a manВҰ14719 who had twoВҰ14725 childrenВҰ14724 and he went up to the firstВҰ14730 one and instructed, вҖҳSon, go and work in myВҰ14742 vineyardВҰ14740 todayВҰ14734.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 29 \wj вҖҳI can'tВҰ14751,вҖҷ he answeredВҰ14745, but laterВҰ14753 he regrettedВҰ14755 what he'd saidВҰ14746 and wentВҰ14756 and did the work.\wj*
\v 30 \wj The father also approachedВҰ14761 the otherВҰ14764 childВҰ14764 with the same instruction. вҖҳI will, masterВҰ14774вҖҷ this one answeredВҰ14770, but he never wentВҰ14782.\wj*
\v 31 \wj WhichВҰ14783 of the twoВҰ14786 did what the fatherВҰ14791 wanted?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңThe firstВҰ14798 one,вҖқ the hearers answered.
\p вҖң\wj I can assure you all,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* continued, вҖң\wj that taxВҰ14808 collectorsВҰ14808 and prostitutesВҰ14811 will enter God's kingdomВҰ14816 ahead of you lot,\wj*
\v 32 \x + \xo 21:32: \xt Luk 3:12; 7:29-30.\x*\wj becauseВҰ14820 Yohan came to you all \+add teaching\+add* the road to becoming rightВҰ14827 with God, but you didn't believe \+add that he was sent by God\+add*. Yet the taxВҰ14834 collectorsВҰ14834 and prostitutesВҰ14837 believed in him, and still, even when you saw that, you didn't laterВҰ14846 regretВҰ14845 and \+add change your minds and\+add* believe.\wj*
\s1 The parable about the evil tenants
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Wicked Tenants; Story of the Evil Farmers; The Parable of the Tenants in the Vineyard
\r (Mark 12:1-12; Luke 20:9-19)
\p
\v 33 \x + \xo 21:33: \xt Isa 5:1-2.\x*вҖң\wj Listen to anotherВҰ14851 parableВҰ14852: A landowner plantedВҰ14859 a vineyardВҰ14860 and fencedВҰ14862 it, and he carved a wine-press in it and builtВҰ14871 a watchtower. Then he rentedВҰ14874 it out to tenantВҰ14876 farmersВҰ14876 and moved away.\wj*
\v 34 \wj At harvest time, he sentВҰ14886 some of his slavesВҰ14888 to the tenantВҰ14892 farmersВҰ14892 to bring back his share of the harvest.\wj*
\v 35 \wj However, the tenantsВҰ14902 grabbed hisВҰ14905 slavesВҰ14904 and beat them. They killedВҰ14911 some and threwВҰ14914 rocksВҰ14914 at others.\wj*
\v 36 \wj So the owner sentВҰ14918 a larger group of slavesВҰ14920, but the tenants did the same things to them.\wj*
\p
\v 37 вҖң\wj Next he sentВҰ14930 his son because he thought his son would have influence over them.\wj*
\v 38 \wj But when the tenantВҰ14944 farmersВҰ14944 saw the son, they thought, вҖҳHey, this is the heir of the estate. If we killВҰ14956 him, then the inheritanceВҰ14962 will be ours.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 39 \wj SoВҰ14964 they grabbed the son, dragged him out of the vineyardВҰ14973, andВҰ14964 killedВҰ14975 him there outside.\wj*
\p
\v 40 вҖң\wj Now, when the owner of the vineyardВҰ14982 comes, what do you think he'll do to thoseВҰ14987 tenantВҰ14986 farmersВҰ14986?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 41 вҖңHe'll brutally destroyВҰ14992 those wicked tenants,вҖқ they answered, вҖңthen he'll rent the vineyardВҰ14996 out to otherВҰ14999 tenant farmersВҰ15000 who will give him his share of the harvest.вҖқ
\p
\v 42 \x + \xo 21:42: \xt Psa 118:22-23.\x*Then \nd Yeshua\nd* said to them, вҖң\wj Haven't you ever read in the scripturesВҰ15019:\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖҳThe stoneВҰ15020 whichВҰ15021 the buildersВҰ15024 rejectedВҰ15022,\wj*
\q2 \wj this would becomeВҰ15026 the cornerstoneВҰ15029.\wj*
\q1 \wj This one came from \+nd YahwehВҰ15031\+nd*,\wj*
\q2 \wj andВҰ15035 itВҰ15036 was amazing to see.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 43 вҖң\wj BecauseВҰ15042 of that, I'm telling you that God's kingdomВҰ15051 will be takenВҰ15047 away from all of you and be givenВҰ15055 to a peopleВҰ15056 who will produceВҰ15057 a harvest.\wj*
\v 44 \wj And anyone who falls down onto this stone will be shatteredВҰ15069, but anyone that this stone falls on will be \+add totally\+add* pulverisedВҰ15075.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 45 When the chiefВҰ15081 priestsВҰ15081 andВҰ15077 the Pharisees heardВҰ15078 those parablesВҰ15086, they knewВҰ15088 that he was talkingВҰ15092 aboutВҰ15090 them.
\v 46 They attempted to arrest him, but couldn't becauseВҰ15103 they knew that the crowdsВҰ15101 believed him to be a prophetВҰ15107 \add from God\add*.
\c 22
\s1 The parable about the wedding reception
\rem /s1 Story of the Great Feast; The Parable of the Wedding Banquet; The Parable of the Wedding Feast
\r (Luke 14:15-24)
\p
\v 1 \nd YeshuaВҰ15113\nd*, still answeringВҰ15111 them, told another parableВҰ15118:
\v 2 вҖң\wj The heavenlyВҰ15126 kingdomВҰ15124 is like a kingВҰ15128 who prepared the weddingВҰ15131 reception for hisВҰ15134 son\wj*
\v 3 \wj andВҰ15135 he sentВҰ15136 out some of hisВҰ15139 slavesВҰ15138 to remind those who'd been invitedВҰ15142, but they didn'tВҰ15147 want to comeВҰ15149.\wj*
\v 4 \wj So he sentВҰ15151 out some otherВҰ15152 slavesВҰ15153, instructing them, вҖҳTell those who are invitedВҰ15157: ListenВҰ15158, I've preparedВҰ15163 the dinnerВҰ15160, including some of myВҰ15161 grain-fed beef and everything's now readyВҰ15174. Come to the weddingВҰ15178 and celebrate.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 5 \wj But they ignored the message and went their various waysвҖ”one went off to his fieldВҰ15190 \+add to work\+add* and another went into his businessВҰ15198.\wj*
\v 6 \wj Still others grabbed the slavesВҰ15206 and mistreatedВҰ15208 them, and even killedВҰ15210 them.\wj*
\p
\v 7 вҖң\wj Now the kingВҰ15217 was angry and sentВҰ15223 in hisВҰ15228 soldiers to destroyВҰ15229 thoseВҰ15232 murderersВҰ15231 and to burn theirВҰ15236 cityВҰ15235.\wj*
\v 8 \wj Then he told hisВҰ15242 slavesВҰ15241, вҖҳWell, the weddingВҰ15245 reception is readyВҰ15246 but those that were invitedВҰ15250 aren'tВҰ15251 worthyВҰ15253 to come.\wj*
\v 9 \wj SoВҰ15255 spread out on the roadsВҰ15261 andВҰ15262 inviteВҰ15267 everywhere that youВҰ15266 find to come to the reception.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 10 \wj SoВҰ15271 thoseВҰ15276 slavesВҰ15274 went out onto the roadsВҰ15279 and invited everyone they foundВҰ15284вҖ”both evilВҰ15285 and goodВҰ15288 people, and thenВҰ15271 the seats at the weddingВҰ15293 reception were all full.\wj*
\p
\v 11 вҖң\wj But when the kingВҰ15302 came into to meet the seated guests, he sawВҰ15306 a manВҰ15308 thereВҰ15307 who wasn't dressedВҰ15311 in the proper clothesВҰ15312 for a weddingВҰ15313,\wj*
\v 12 \wj andВҰ15314 demanded, вҖҳFriendВҰ15317, how did youВҰ15320 get in here without the right clothesВҰ15324?вҖҷ ButВҰ15327 the man had nothing to say.\wj*
\v 13 \x + \xo 22:13: \xt Mat 8:12; 25:30; Luk 13:28.\x*\wj So the kingВҰ15332 told hisВҰ15337 servantsВҰ15335, вҖҳTie up the man's handsВҰ15343 and feetВҰ15340 and throwВҰ15349 him outside into the darknessВҰ15353, and there'll be weepingВҰ15359 and much anguish \+add out there\+add*.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 14 \wj BecauseВҰ15366 many are invited, butВҰ15370 few are selected.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 The question about paying tax
\rem /s1 Paying Taxes to Caesar; The Question about Paying Taxes
\r (Mark 12:13-17; Luke 20:20-26)
\p
\v 15 Then the \add members of\add* the Pharisees went away and had a discussion to try to figure out how to trap himВҰ15380 into saying something wrong.
\v 16 Afterwards, they sent some of theirВҰ15391 apprenticesВҰ15390 along with some supportersВҰ15394 of HerodВҰ15394 and asked, вҖңTeacherВҰ15397, we know that you are honest and that you teachВҰ15411 God's ways in all honesty irrespective of what people might say, becauseВҰ15419 you don'tВҰ15413 care aboutВҰ15416 people's opinions.
\v 17 SoВҰ15425 then, tell us what youВҰ15428 think: should we pay the poll taxВҰ15432 to CaesarВҰ15434 or not?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 But \nd Yeshua\nd* knew how wickedВҰ15443 they were and asked, вҖң\wj Why are you testingВҰ15449 me, you hypocritesВҰ15450?\wj*
\v 19 \wj Show me the coin used to pay the poll taxВҰ15456.\wj*вҖқ SoВҰ15458 theyВҰ15457 broughtВҰ15459 a coin to himВҰ15460.
\v 20 ThenВҰ15464 he asked, вҖң\wj Whose imageВҰ15471 is this on the coin, andВҰ15464 the inscriptionВҰ15475?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 21 вҖңCaesar's,вҖқ they answered.
\p вҖң\wj Then give Caesar's things to Caesar and God's things to God,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua responded.
\p
\v 22 When they heardВҰ15495 that, they were amazed, and left himВҰ15499 and wentВҰ15500 away.
\s1 The question about marriage in heaven
\rem /s1 The Question about Rising from Death; Discussion about Resurrection; The Question about the Resurrection; Marriage at the Resurrection
\r (Mark 12:18-27; Luke 20:27-40)
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 22:23: \xt Acts 23:8.\x*On that dayВҰ15505 some from the Sadducee sect (who claim there's no resurrectionВҰ15513) approachedВҰ15506 Yeshua andВҰ15514 askedВҰ15515,
\v 24 \x + \xo 22:24: \xt Deu 25:5.\x*вҖңTeacherВҰ15518, Mosheh wrote that if a married man dies childless, his brother should marryВҰ15528 the widow and so raise up children for his deceased brother.
\v 25 Well, there were sevenВҰ15546 brothersВҰ15547 amongstВҰ15544 up, and the firstВҰ15550 one got married and thenВҰ15543 diedВҰ15552 childless. SoВҰ15543 hisВҰ15560 brotherВҰ15562 married the widow.
\v 26 The same happened for the secondВҰ15567 brother, andВҰ15568 the thirdВҰ15570, all the way to the seventhВҰ15573.
\v 27 Finally the womanВҰ15580 diedВҰ15577.
\v 28 Now then, in the resurrectionВҰ15584, whichВҰ15586 of the brothers will sheВҰ15590 be the wifeВҰ15591 of, becauseВҰ15593 they were all married to herВҰ15595?вҖқ
\p
\v 29 вҖң\wj You've got it wrong,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ15597, вҖң\wj because you don'tВҰ15604 understand either the scripturesВҰ15607 or God's powerВҰ15610,\wj*
