\r (Mark 12:35-37; Luke 20:41-44)
\p
\v 41 Since all from the Pharisees' partyВҰ15774 were gatheredВҰ15771 togetherВҰ15771, \nd Yeshua\nd* askedВҰ15775 them a question,
\v 42 вҖң\wj How do you \+add interpret the scriptures\+add* about the \+nd messiahВҰ15785\+nd*? Who will he be a descendant of?\wj*вҖқ
\p вҖңA descendant of \add King\add* DavidВҰ15792,вҖқ they answered.
\p
\v 43 вҖң\wj Then how could DavidВҰ15797,\wj*вҖқ he continued, вҖң\wj under the \+add inspiration of God's\+add* \+nd spiritВҰ15799\+nd*, call himВҰ15802 вҖҳ\+nd masterВҰ15801\+nd*вҖҷ when he said,\wj*
\q1
\v 44 \x + \xo 22:44: \xt Psa 110:1.\x*\wj вҖҳ\nd YahwehВҰ15809\nd* said to my master:\wj*
\q1 \wj вҖңSit there on my rightВҰ15815\wj*
\q1 \wj untilВҰ15817 I conquer yourВҰ15822 enemiesВҰ15821.вҖқ\wj*
\m
\v 45 \wj SoВҰ15829 if DavidВҰ15830 is callingВҰ15833 him вҖҳ\+nd masterВҰ15835\+nd*вҖҷ, how could he be hisВҰ15838 descendant?\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 46 No one was able to answerВҰ15844 his question, andВҰ15840 after that dayВҰ15854 they didn't dare askВҰ15855 him anything else.
\c 23
\s1 Yeshua's warnings about show and status
\rem /s1 Jesus Denounces Scribes and Pharisees; Jesus Warns the Religious Leaders; Jesus Warns against the Teachers of the Law and the Pharisees; Seven Woes
\r (Mark 12:38-39; Luke 11:43,46; 20:45-46)
\p
\v 1 Then \nd Yeshua\nd* spokeВҰ15862 to the crowdsВҰ15864 andВҰ15865 to hisВҰ15868 followers,
\v 2 вҖң\wj The religiousВҰ15877 teachersВҰ15877 andВҰ15878 the Pharisees partyВҰ15880 claim the authority of Mosheh.\wj*
\v 3 \wj Because of that, do everything they tell you to do and \+add obey all the commands\+add* they tell you to obey. However, don'tВҰ15902 follow what they \+em do\+em*, becauseВҰ15905 they're \+add only\+add* good at telling and not at doing.\wj*
\v 4 \wj They package up heavyВҰ15914 and unbearableВҰ15917 loads and place them across the shouldersВҰ15922 of the peopleВҰ15924, while they themselves won'tВҰ15931 even move theirВҰ15930 little fingersВҰ15929.\wj*
\v 5 \x + \xo 23:5: a \xt Mat 6:1; \xo b \xt Deu 6:8; \xo c \xt Num 15:38.\x*\wj Everything that they do do, is \+add only\+add* done to be a public display in front of the peopleВҰ15945, so they have big prayer boxes and fancy robes.\wj*
\v 6 \wj They love the best placeВҰ15964 at dinners andВҰ15968 the best seatsВҰ15970 in the meetingВҰ15973 hallsВҰ15973\wj*
\v 7 \wj and beingВҰ15981 greetedВҰ15976 in the marketplacesВҰ15979 and to be addressed as вҖҳMyВҰ15985 greatВҰ15985 oneвҖҷ.\wj*
\v 8 \wj But don'tВҰ15989 let anyoneВҰ15992 call you вҖҳMy greatВҰ15991 oneвҖҷ, becauseВҰ15993 you only have one leader and you are all brothersВҰ16005 and sistersВҰ16005,\wj*
\v 9 \wj andВҰ16007 don'tВҰ16009 let anyoneВҰ16016 call you вҖҳFatherвҖҷ on earthВҰ16015, becauseВҰ16017 you all only have one heavenlyВҰ16027 father.\wj*
\v 10 \wj Don't let anyoneВҰ16040 call you their mentor, becauseВҰ16032 you all have only one teacher and that's the \+nd messiahВҰ16044\+nd*.\wj*
\v 11 \x + \xo 23:11: \xt Mat 20:26-27; Mrk 9:35; 10:43-44; Luk 22:26.\x*\wj The most important person will be everyone's servantВҰ16052\wj*
\v 12 \x + \xo 23:12: \xt Luk 14:11; 18:14.\x*\wj and anyone who praises themself will be humbled, and anyone who humbles themself will be praised.\wj*
\s1 Yeshua reveals the hypocrisy of those who are religious
\rem /s1 Jesus Condemns Their Hypocrisy
\r (Mark 12:40; Luke 11:39-42,44,52; 20:47)
\p
\v 13 вҖң\wj You religiousВҰ16066 teachersВҰ16066 and Pharisees are hypocritesВҰ16069 and will have a bad end becauseВҰ16080 you're \+add actually\+add* keeping peopleВҰ16078 away from the heavenlyВҰ16075 kingdomВҰ16073вҖ”you don't enter yourselves and nor do you allowВҰ16086 others to enter.\wj*
\p
\v 14 в—ҳ
\v 15 вҖң\wj You religiousВҰ16114 teachersВҰ16114 and Pharisees are hypocritesВҰ16117 and will have a bad end because you'd travel all the way aroundВҰ16119 the world to make one convertВҰ16129, and then you'd make himВҰ16134 twiceВҰ16137 the son of hell that you are yourselves.\wj*
\p
\v 16 вҖң\wj You blindВҰ16143 guidesВҰ16141 will have a bad end. You say that if anyone makes an oath on the temple it's worthless, but if they make an oath on the goldВҰ16160 in the temple then they have to honour it.\wj*
\v 17 \wj You are both stupid and blindВҰ16166, becauseВҰ16169 which is greaterВҰ16170: the gold, or the templeВҰ16177 which makes the gold valuable?\wj*
\v 18 \wj And you say thatВҰ16200 anyone who makes an oath on the altar it's worthless, but anyone who makes an oath on the giftВҰ16199 on the altar has to honour it.\wj*
\v 19 \wj You are both stupid and blindВҰ16206, becauseВҰ16208 which is greaterВҰ16209: the gift, or the altarВҰ16215 which makes the gift valuable?\wj*
\v 20 \wj Anyone who makes an oath on the altar, is bound by both the altar and the things on it.\wj*
\v 21 \wj Anyone who makes an oath on the temple, is bound by both the temple andВҰ16236 \+add God\+add* who lives in it.\wj*
\v 22 \x + \xo 23:22: \xt Isa 66:1; Mat 5:34.\x*\wj And anyone who makes an oath on heavenВҰ16256, is bound by both God's throneВҰ16260 andВҰ16263 the one who's sittingВҰ16266 on itВҰ16268.\wj*
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 23:23: \xt Lev 27:30.\x*вҖң\wj You religiousВҰ16271 teachersВҰ16271 and Pharisees are hypocritesВҰ16274 and will have a bad end because you give a tenth of your herbs butВҰ16302 you ignore the weightier parts of \+add God's\+add* commands like justiceВҰ16292 and mercyВҰ16296 and faithВҰ16300. \+em Those\+em* are the things that should have been observed and not left out.\wj*
\v 24 \wj You blind guidesВҰ16309! You try to strainВҰ16312 out a gnat andВҰ16317 \add end up\add* swallowingВҰ16320 a camelВҰ16318.\wj*
\p
\v 25 вҖң\wj You religiousВҰ16323 teachersВҰ16323 and Pharisees are hypocritesВҰ16326 and will have a bad end because you scrub the outsideВҰ16331 of \+add your\+add* cups and bowls but the insideВҰ16337 is \+add still\+add* full of greed and selfishness.\wj*
\v 26 \wj You blind Pharisees. First you \+add should\+add* clean the insideВҰ16350 of \+add your\+add* cup and dish so that the outsideВҰ16362 would also becomeВҰ16357 clean.\wj*
\p
\v 27 \x + \xo 23:27: \xt Acts 23:3.\x*вҖң\wj You religiousВҰ16368 teachersВҰ16368 and Pharisees are hypocritesВҰ16371 and will have a bad end because you are like whitewashedВҰ16376 tombsВҰ16375. On the outside they might look nice, but the insideВҰ16386 is full of the bonesВҰ16390 of the deadВҰ16391 and all kinds of impuritiesВҰ16394,\wj*
\v 28 \wj so even though the peopleВҰ16402 might think you're godlyВҰ16403 on the outside, actually your insidesВҰ16404 are full of hypocrisyВҰ16409 and lawlessnessВҰ16411.\wj*
\s1 Punishment for mistreating prophets
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts Their Punishment
\r (Luke 11:47-51)
\p
\v 29 вҖң\wj You religiousВҰ16414 teachersВҰ16414 and Pharisees are hypocritesВҰ16417 and will have a bad end because you \+add re\+add*build the prophets' tombs and adornВҰ16425 the tombs of godlyВҰ16429 people,\wj*
\v 30 \wj and youВҰ16431 tell yourselves, вҖҳIf we'd lived back in those daysВҰ16438, we wouldn'tВҰ16443 have had any part in killing the prophetsВҰ16453.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 31 \wj By saying that, you're admitting to yourselvesВҰ16456 that you're the descendants of the ones who killed the prophetsВҰ16463вҖ”\wj*
\v 32 \wj actually you're just the same as yourВҰ16472 ancestorsВҰ16471.\wj*
\v 33 \x + \xo 23:33: \xt Mat 3:7; 12:34; Luk 3:7.\x*\wj Bunch of snakes, broodВҰ16474 of vipersВҰ16475, how \+add do you think that\+add* you'll escapeВҰ16477 the judgementВҰ16480 of hell?\wj*
\v 34 \wj BecauseВҰ16483 of that, listen, I'm \+add now\+add* sendingВҰ16487 out \+add more\+add* prophetsВҰ16491 and wise \+add preachers\+add* and teachersВҰ16495 to you all. You'll kill off some of them and have others executedВҰ16501 on stakesВҰ16501. You'll flog some of them in yourВҰ16510 meetingВҰ16509 hallsВҰ16509, and you'll persecuteВҰ16512 others from city to city,\wj*
\v 35 \x + \xo 23:35: a \xt Gen 4:8; \xo b \xt 2Ch 24:20-21.\x*\wj so that \+add the judgement for\+add* all the deaths of godlyВҰ16523 people around the world will fall on you all. This includes the blood of the innocent HevelВҰ16531 \add (Abel)\add* all the way \+add through the centuries\+add* to the blood of Zekaryah (son of Berekiah) who you all murderedВҰ16541 betweenВҰ16542 the templeВҰ16544 and the altarВҰ16547.\wj*
\v 36 \wj Yes, I can assure youВҰ16550 that all theseВҰ16555 things will happen to this generationВҰ16558.\wj*
\s1 Yeshua's concern for Yerushalem
\rem /s1 The Lament over Jerusalem; Jesus Grieves over Jerusalem; Jesus' Love for Jerusalem
\r (Luke 13:34-35)
\p
\v 37 вҖң\wj Yerushalem, Yerushalem, the \+add cityВҰ16562\+add* that murders the prophetsВҰ16565 and throwsВҰ16568 rocksВҰ16568 to kill those who are sentВҰ16571 to her. How oftenВҰ16575 I wantedВҰ16576 to gatherВҰ16578 yourВҰ16583 inhabitants like a \+add mother\+add* hen gathers her chicksВҰ16591 underВҰ16594 her wingsВҰ16596, but you didn'tВҰ16598 want that.\wj*
\v 38 \x + \xo 23:38: \xt Jer 22:5.\x*\wj So listen, now yourВҰ16605 \+add temple\+add* will be left uninhabited,\wj*
\v 39 \x + \xo 23:39: \xt Psa 118:26.\x*\wj becauseВҰ16608 I'm telling you that you certainly won'tВҰ16612 seeВҰ16614 me again untilВҰ16617 you can sayВҰ16619, вҖҳThe person comingВҰ16622 in the nameВҰ16624 of \+nd YahwehВҰ16626\+nd* has been blessedВҰ16620.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\c 24
\s1 Yeshua foretells the destruction of the temple
\rem /s1 Warnings about the end; Jesus Speaks of the Destruction of the Temple; The Destruction of the Temple Foretold; Signs of the End of the Age; Jesus Foretells the Future
\r (Mark 13:1-2; Luke 21:5-6)
\p
\v 1 As \nd Yeshua\nd* exited the temple, he approachedВҰ16638 hisВҰ16641 followers andВҰ16627 asked them to show him around the buildingsВҰ16645,
\v 2 вҖң\wj You can see all of this,\wj*вҖқ he said, вҖң\wj but I can assure you that it'll be torn down so thoroughly that one stone won'tВҰ16654 be left on top of another.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Future calamities and persecution
\rem /s1 Troubles and Persecutions; Signs of the End of the Age
\r (Mark 13:3-13; Luke 21:7-19)
\p
\v 3 When Yeshua was sittingВҰ16674 on the MountВҰ16679 of OliveВҰ16681, his apprenticesВҰ16688 came up to him by themselvesВҰ16691, asking, вҖңTell us when all those things will happen and what the signs will be of your comingВҰ16705 and of the end of this age?вҖқ
\p
\v 4 вҖң\wj Watch out in case others misleadВҰ16722 youВҰ16721,\wj*вҖқ \nd Yeshua\nd* answeredВҰ16713,
\v 5 вҖң\wj becauseВҰ16724 many will come claiming to be me and sayingВҰ16731 that they're the \+nd messiahВҰ16736\+nd* and misleadingВҰ16739 many.\wj*
\v 6 \wj You will hearВҰ16743 about wars andВҰ16745 reportsВҰ16746 about wars \+add further away\+add*. Don't be alarmedВҰ16750, butВҰ16755 keep watchingВҰ16748 becauseВҰ16752 these things need to happen, although that's not yet the endВҰ16759\wj*
\v 7 \wj becauseВҰ16761 \add вүҲpeople groups will turn against each other\add* and country \add вүЎrise\add* against country, plus there'll be faminesВҰ16771 and earthquakesВҰ16778.\wj*
\v 8 \wj But all of those things are just like the beginningВҰ16786 of labour painsВҰ16788.\wj*
\rem /s1 Persecutions Foretold
\p
\v 9 \x + \xo 24:9: \xt Mat 10:22.\x*вҖң\wj ThenВҰ16798 they'll turn \+add myВҰ16808 followers\+add* in for persecution, andВҰ16795 some will be killed.\wj*
\v 10 \wj Many \+add of my followers\+add* will be caused to stumbleВҰ16811 and they'll turn each other in and hate each other.\wj*
\v 11 \wj Also, many falseВҰ16823 prophetsВҰ16823 will appear andВҰ16827 they will misleadВҰ16829 many,\wj*
\v 12 \wj and as a result, lawlessnessВҰ16838 will increase and the loveВҰ16841 of many people will cool off\wj*
\v 13 \x + \xo 24:13: \xt Mat 10:22.\x*\wj butВҰ16845 anyone who lasts until the endВҰ16848 will be savedВҰ16850.\wj*
\v 14 \wj This goodВҰ16855 messageВҰ16855 about \+add God's\+add* kingdomВҰ16858 will be proclaimedВҰ16852 right around the worldВҰ16865 as a testimonyВҰ16868 to all the nationsВҰ16871, andВҰ16872 thenВҰ16851 the endВҰ16876 will come.\wj*
\s1 Desecration and false teachers
\rem /s1 The Desolating Sacrilege; The Awful Horror
\r (Mark 13:14-23; Luke 21:20-24)
\p
\v 15 \x + \xo 24:15: \xt Dan 9:27; 11:31; 12:11.\x*вҖң\wj SoВҰ16878 wheneverВҰ16877 youВҰ16880 all seeВҰ16880 the irreverent object thatВҰ16885 the prophetВҰ16891 DanielВҰ16889 wrote about being placed in the holy placeВҰ16895 (anyone readingВҰ16898 this shouldВҰ16899 try to understandВҰ16899 it),\wj*
\v 16 \wj those in YudeaВҰ16904 shouldВҰ16905 flee to the hills,\wj*
\v 17 \x + \xo 24:17-18: \xt Luk 17:31.\x*\wj anyone outside on the \+add flat\+add* roof shouldn'tВҰ16915 go back inside to get things out of the houseВҰ16924,\wj*
\v 18 \wj andВҰ16926 anyone in the fieldВҰ16930 shouldn'tВҰ16931 go back \+add to the house\+add* to get their coatВҰ16937.\wj*
\v 19 \wj It will be very difficult for pregnant women and breast-feeding mothers in thoseВҰ16951 daysВҰ16953,\wj*
\v 20 \wj butВҰ16955 pray that yourВҰ16962 escape won'tВҰ16957 be in winterВҰ16963 or on a rest dayВҰ16966.\wj*
\v 21 \x + \xo 24:21: \xt Dan 12:1; Rev 7:14.\x*\wj This will be followed by incredible troubles like nothing that has been observed in this worldВҰ16979 from creationВҰ16978 untilВҰ16980 the present timeВҰ16981, and which won'tВҰ16974 happen like that againвҖ”\wj*
\v 22 \wj in fact if those days weren't shortened, nobody wouldВҰ16996 survive, however becauseВҰ17000 of the chosenВҰ17003, those days will be shortened.\wj*
\p
\v 23 вҖң\wj Then if anyoneВҰ17011 says, вҖҳLookВҰ17014, here's the \+nd messiahВҰ17017\+nd*вҖҷ or вҖҳHere he isвҖҷ, don'tВҰ17021 believeВҰ17022 it,\wj*
\v 24 \wj becauseВҰ17025 false messiahsВҰ17027 and false prophetsВҰ17029 will emerge, and theyВҰ17031 will do amazing miracles that would misleadВҰ17037 even the chosenВҰ17044 if possibleВҰ17041.\wj*
\v 25 \wj ListenВҰ17045, I'm telling youВҰ17047 all before it happens.\wj*
\p
\v 26 \x + \xo 24:26-27: \xt Luk 17:23-24.\x*вҖң\wj SoВҰ17049 if they tell you all, вҖҳLookВҰ17052, he's out in the wildernessВҰ17055,вҖҷ don't go out there, or if they sayВҰ17050, вҖҳHe's here in these privateВҰ17062 roomsВҰ17062,вҖҷ don't believeВҰ17064 itВҰ17064,\wj*
\v 27 \wj becauseВҰ17066 when humanity's child comes, it'll be like how the lighteningВҰ17068 goes right across the sky from one side to the other.\wj*
\p
\v 28 \x + \xo 24:28: \xt Luk 17:37.\x*вҖң\wj WhereverВҰ17087 there'sВҰ17095 something dead, that's where the vulturesВҰ17098 will gatherВҰ17096.\wj*
\s1 The miraculous appearance of the messiah
\rem /s1 The Coming of the Son of Man
\r (Mark 13:24-27; Luke 21:25-28)
\p
\v 29 \x + \xo 24:29: a \xt Isa 13:10; Yoel 2:10,31; 3:15; Rev 6:12; \xo b \xt Isa 13:10; Eze 32:7; Yoel 2:10; 3:15; \xo c \xt Isa 34:4; Rev 6:13.\x*вҖң\wj But immediatelyВҰ17099 afterВҰ17101 the troubles of that time, the sunВҰ17108 will go dark and the moonВҰ17112 won'tВҰ17113 give itsВҰ17117 light. The starsВҰ17120 will fall from the skyВҰ17125 and the powersВҰ17128 of the heavensВҰ17130 will be shakenВҰ17131.\wj*
\v 30 \x + \xo 24:30: \xt Dan 7:13; Zech 12:10-14; Rev 1:7.\x*\wj And thenВҰ17132 a miracle will appear in the sky as humanity's child arrives. All the peoples of the earthВҰ17154 will be upset and they'll see humanity's child arriving on the cloudsВҰ17164 in the sky with powerВҰ17168 and greatВҰ17172 splendour.\wj*
\v 31 \wj There'll be a trumpetВҰ17180 blast as he sends out his messengersВҰ17177 to bring togetherВҰ17185 all his chosenВҰ17188 people from every part of the earthвҖ”from one \+add pole\+add* to the other.\wj*
\s1 Watch the fig tree
\rem /s1 The Lesson of the Fig Tree
\r (Mark 13:28-31; Luke 21:29-33)
\p
\v 32 вҖң\wj SoВҰ17217 learnВҰ17220 the parableВҰ17222 about the figВҰ17219 treeВҰ17219: wheneverВҰ17223 itsВҰ17228 branchesВҰ17227 green up andВҰ17231 leavesВҰ17233 start to sproutВҰ17234 out, youВҰ17236 know that summerВҰ17242 is coming.\wj*
\v 33 \wj In the same way, wheneverВҰ17246 you seeВҰ17247 all those things happening, you'll know then that \+add the end of this age\+add* is very close.\wj*
\v 34 \wj I can assure youВҰ17260 that that generationВҰ17266 won'tВҰ17263 passВҰ17264 away untilВҰ17268 all of those things happen.\wj*
\v 35 \wj The sky and the earthВҰ17278 will pass away, but myВҰ17284 messagesВҰ17283 will certainly \+em not\+em* pass away.\wj*
\s1 The day of his return isn't known
\rem /s1 The Day and Hour Unknown; No One Knows the Day and Hour; The Necessity for Watchfulness
\r (Mark 13:32-37; Luke 17:26-30,34-36)
\p
\v 36 вҖң\wj No one knows the \+add exact\+add* dayВҰ17291 or timeвҖ”not even the messengersВҰ17300 in the heavensВҰ17302 or the sonвҖ”only the fatherВҰ17309 knows it.\wj*
\v 37 \x + \xo 24:37: \xt Gen 6:5-8.\x*\wj The comingВҰ17323 of humanity's child will be just like it was in Noah's time.\wj*
\v 38 \wj In the daysВҰ17334 leading up to the floodВҰ17339, people were eatingВҰ17340 and drinkingВҰ17342, and marryingВҰ17344 and getting engagedвҖ”right untilВҰ17348 the very dayВҰ17351 thatВҰ17336 NoahВҰ17353 entered the barge.\wj*
\v 39 \x + \xo 24:39: \xt Gen 7:6-24.\x*\wj They didn'tВҰ17358 realise that anything was coming untilВҰ17361 the floodВҰ17365 cameВҰ17363 andВҰ17357 took everything away. It'll be just like that at the coming of humanity's child.\wj*
\v 40 \wj Two people will be working out on the farmвҖ”one will be takenВҰ17388 andВҰ17389 one left behind.\wj*
\v 41 \wj Two people will be grinding grainвҖ”one will be takenВҰ17400 andВҰ17401 one left behind.\wj*
\v 42 \wj SoВҰ17414 be watchingВҰ17413, becauseВҰ17415 none of you know exactly when yourВҰ17423 \+nd masterВҰ17422\+nd* will return.\wj*
\v 43 \x + \xo 24:43-44: \xt Luk 12:39-40.\x*\wj But you do know that if the home-owner knew when the thief would come, he would be there watchingВҰ17436 and not allowВҰ17445 the thief to break into the houseВҰ17449.\wj*
\v 44 \wj BecauseВҰ17452 of that, you all should also be readyВҰ17457 becauseВҰ17458 otherwise you wouldn't realise that humanity's child is comingВҰ17468 at that time.\wj*
\s1 The watchful servant and the slacker
\rem /s1 The Faithful or the Unfaithful Slave; The Faithful or the Unfaithful Servant
\r (Luke 12:41-48)
\p
\v 45 вҖң\wj As a result, \+add we'll see\+add* who the faithfulВҰ17474 andВҰ17476 watchful slaveВҰ17475 isвҖ”the one who the masterВҰ17482 appointedВҰ17479 to run all the affairs of hisВҰ17489 householdВҰ17487.\wj*
\v 46 \wj That slaveВҰ17501 will be rewarded if the masterВҰ17506 finds him working faithful when he arrives \+add suddenly\+add*.\wj*
\v 47 \wj I can assure you that he'll appointВҰ17521 the slave to supervise everything that he possessesВҰ17519.\wj*
\v 48 \wj But if the evilВҰ17527 slaveВҰ17528 says to himself, вҖҳAh, the masterВҰ17538 won't be back for a long time yet,вҖҷ\wj*
\v 49 \wj and starts beating hisВҰ17547 fellowВҰ17545 slaves, and spends time eatingВҰ17548 and drinkingВҰ17553 with drunkardsВҰ17557,\wj*
\v 50 \wj then his masterВҰ17561 will arrive when he's not expectingВҰ17569 it\wj*
\v 51 \wj and will torture him and place him in with the hypocritesВҰ17586 where there'llВҰ17588 be crying and great anguish.\wj*
\c 25
\s1 The parable about not being prepared
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Ten Young Women; Story of the Ten Bridesmaids; The Parable of the Ten Bridesmaids; The Parable of the Ten Virgins
\p
\v 1 \x + \xo 25:1: \xt Luk 12:35.\x*вҖң\wj The heavenlyВҰ17603 kingdomВҰ17601 can also be likenedВҰ17598 to ten young women \+add in a wedding party\+add* who took theirВҰ17611 lampsВҰ17609 and wentВҰ17612 off to meet the groom.\wj*
\v 2 \wj Five of them were harebrained andВҰ17624 five were sensible.\wj*
\v 3 \wj The less clever ones tookВҰ17647 theirВҰ17645 lampsВҰ17643 but didn'tВҰ17646 take any oil for them,\wj*
\v 4 \wj whereas the sensible ones had oil in containersВҰ17662 along with the lampsВҰ17666.\wj*
\v 5 \wj When the groom was held up, they started noddingВҰ17673 off andВҰ17675 napping.\wj*
\p
\v 6 вҖң\wj But in the middleВҰ17677 of the nightВҰ17679 there was a shout, вҖҳLookВҰ17683, the groom's on his way. Come out and meet him.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 7 \wj So all the young women got up andВҰ17700 trimmedВҰ17701 \+add the wicks on\+add* their lampsВҰ17703,\wj*
\v 8 \wj andВҰ17707 the less sensible ones asked the others, вҖҳHere, give us some of yourВҰ17718 oil becauseВҰ17719 ourВҰ17722 lampsВҰ17721 are starting to splutter.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 9 \wj But the sensible ones answeredВҰ17725, вҖҳWe don'tВҰ17732 have enough for everyone. You need to go to the stall and buy some for your lamps.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 10 \wj However, while they were still away buying \+add oil\+add*, the groom appeared and those who were readyВҰ17760 wentВҰ17755 in with himВҰ17763 to the weddingВҰ17766 and the doorВҰ17770 was shut.\wj*
\p
\v 11 \x + \xo 25:11-12: \xt Luk 13:25.\x*вҖң\wj Later the otherВҰ17777 young women arrived andВҰ17772 called out, вҖҳMasterВҰ17780, masterВҰ17781, let us in.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 12 \wj But heВҰ17784 answeredВҰ17786, вҖҳI can assure you all that I don'tВҰ17791 know you.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 13 вҖң\wj SoВҰ17795 then, be watchfulВҰ17794 becauseВҰ17796 youВҰ17798 all don't know the dayВҰ17800 or the time.\wj*
\s1 The parable about using what you're given
\rem /s1 The Parable of the Three Servants; The Parable of the Talents; Story of the Three Servants
\r (Luke 19:11-27)
\p
\v 14 \x + \xo 25:14-30: \xt Luk 19:11-27.\x*вҖң\wj It's like a manВҰ17813 who was leaving on a trip. He calledВҰ17815 his slavesВҰ17818 andВҰ17819 shared his savings among them \+add for them to manage\+add*.\wj*
\v 15 \wj He gaveВҰ17829 fiveВҰ17830 bags of silver\f + \fr 25:15 \ft Probably silver coins, or possibly gold, and perhaps each bag weighing up to 24kg, although these details aren't vital to the story. (See https://wpmu2.azurewebsites.net/nlt/2024/02/01/word-studies-in-the-new-living-translation-П„О¬О»ОұОҪП„ОҝОҪ-talanton.)\f* to one, twoВҰ17834 bags to another, and one to the other, each accordingВҰ17840 to his abilityВҰ17843, and thenВҰ17826 he departed.\wj*
\v 16 \wj In his absence, the one with five bags of silver used it for trading and gainedВҰ17859 five more bags.\wj*
\v 17 \wj Similar, the one with two bags gainedВҰ17876 two more bags.\wj*
\v 18 \wj But the one who receivedВҰ17884 the one bag, he went off and dug a hole in the groundВҰ17891 and hid hisВҰ17899 master'sВҰ17898 silverВҰ17896.\wj*
\p
\v 19 вҖң\wj Eventually the masterВҰ17908 of thoseВҰ17911 slavesВҰ17910 returned, andВҰ17901 he \+add called them in\+add* to settleВҰ17913 up their accountsВҰ17913.\wj*
\v 20 \wj The slave who'd receivedВҰ17925 five bags of silver approachedВҰ17919, also bringing the otherВҰ17927 five bags, and said, вҖҳMasterВҰ17931, you entrusted me with five bags, and look, I gainedВҰ17940 anotherВҰ17937 five.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 21 \wj вҖҳWell done, good and faithful slaveВҰ17952,вҖҷ said the master. вҖҳYou were faithful over a few things, so I'll put you in charge of a lot more things. Come and join yourВҰ17971 master in celebrating.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 22 \wj The slave who'd received two bags approachedВҰ17972 and said, вҖҳMasterВҰ17981, you entrusted me with two bags of silver. LookВҰ17986, I gainedВҰ17992 anotherВҰ17988 two.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 23 \wj вҖҳWell done, good and faithful slaveВҰ18002,вҖҷ said the master. вҖҳYou were faithful over a few things, so I'll put you in charge of a lot more things. Come and join yourВҰ18022 master in celebrating.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 24 \wj ThenВҰ18024 the slave with one bag of silverВҰ18030 also approachedВҰ18023 and saidВҰ18032, вҖҳMasterВҰ18033, I knewВҰ18034 that you'd are hard manВҰ18039, harvesting where you didn't plant, and gatheringВҰ18047 where you didn't spread seed.\wj*
\v 25 \wj So because I was afraidВҰ18054, I went andВҰ18053 hid yourВҰ18069 silverВҰ18060 in the groundВҰ18064. So look, here's all of it back.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 26 \wj вҖҳYou evil and lazy slaveВҰ18078,вҖҷ hisВҰ18074 masterВҰ18073 answeredВҰ18070. вҖҳYou know that I harvest where I didn't plant and gatherВҰ18093 where I didn't spread seed\wj*
\v 27 \wj so youВҰ18098 should have at least invested myВҰ18106 silverВҰ18104 with the bankersВҰ18108 andВҰ18109 then I could have gotten itВҰ18097 back with some interestВҰ18119.\wj*
\v 28 \wj ThereforeВҰ18121 take the bag of silver off him and give it to the one with ten bags\wj*
\v 29 \x + \xo 25:29: \xt Mat 13:12; Mrk 4:25; Luk 8:18.\x*\wj becauseВҰ18135 everyoneВҰ18137 who has will be givenВҰ18138 \+add more\+add* andВҰ18139 will have plenty, butВҰ18144 anyone who doesn't have, even what they do have will be takenВҰ18151 away from them.\wj*
\v 30 \x + \xo 25:30: \xt Mat 8:12; 22:13; Luk 13:28.\x*\wj SoВҰ18154 throwВҰ18158 that uselessВҰ18156 slaveВҰ18157 out into the darknessВҰ18164 where there'll be crying andВҰ18171 great anguish.\wj*
\s1 Separating sheep and goats
\rem /s1 The Sheep and the Goats; The Judgment of the Nations; The Final Judgment
\p
\v 31 \x + \xo 25:31: a \xt Mat 16:27; \xo b \xt Mat 19:28.\x*вҖң\wj But when humanity's child comes in his glory and all the messengersВҰ18191 with him, then he'll sit down on his splendid throneВҰ18197\wj*
\v 32 \wj andВҰ18210 all the nationsВҰ18207 will be gatheredВҰ18201 togetherВҰ18201 in front of himВҰ18204. He'll separate them all from each other, just like a shepherdВҰ18217 separates the sheepВҰ18220 from the goatsВҰ18224.\wj*
\v 33 \wj ThenВҰ18225 the sheepВҰ18229 will be standingВҰ18226 on his rightВҰ18231, andВҰ18225 the goatsВҰ18235 on his left\wj*
\v 34 \wj and the kingВҰ18242 will say to the \+add sheep\+add* on hisВҰ18246 rightВҰ18245, вҖҳCome all of you who've been blessedВҰ18249 by myВҰ18252 fatherВҰ18251. Now you'll inheritВҰ18253 the kingdomВҰ18258 that has been preparedВҰ18256 for you since the creation of the worldВҰ18261\wj*
\v 35 \wj becauseВҰ18263 I was hungry and you gave me something to eatВҰ18267, I was thirstyВҰ18269 and you gave me something to drinkВҰ18271, I was a strangerВҰ18274 and you accommodated me,\wj*
\v 36 \wj I was nakedВҰ18279 and you gave me clothesВҰ18281, I was sick and you visitedВҰ18285 me, I was in prisonВҰ18288 and you cameВҰ18291 to \+add see\+add* me.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 37 \wj Then those godlyВҰ18298 people will ask, вҖҳ\+nd MasterВҰ18300\+nd*, when did we ever see you hungry and we fed you, or thirstyВҰ18308 and we gaveВҰ18310 you a drinkВҰ18310?\wj*
\v 38 \wj And when did we see you as a strangerВҰ18316 and accommodate you, or nakedВҰ18321 and we clothedВҰ18323 you?\wj*
\v 39 \wj And when did we see you in prisonВҰ18333, andВҰ18326 we cameВҰ18335 to \+add see\+add* you?вҖҷ\wj*
\v 40 \wj ThenВҰ18338 the kingВҰ18341 will answerВҰ18339 them, вҖҳI can assure you that whenever you did it to one of the leastВҰ18358 of theseВҰ18353 myВҰ18356 brothersВҰ18355 andВҰ18338 sistersВҰ18355, thenВҰ18338 you did it to me.вҖҷ\wj*
\p
\v 41 вҖң\wj Then the king will also speak to the ones on his left, вҖҳGet away from me you who are cursedВҰ18373. You'll go into the eternalВҰ18378 fireВҰ18376 whichВҰ18379 was preparedВҰ18381 for the devilВҰ18387 andВҰ18388 his messengersВҰ18390.\wj*
\v 42 \wj BecauseВҰ18393 I was hungry and you didn't give me anything to eatВҰ18398, I was thirstyВҰ18400 and you didn't give me anything to drinkВҰ18403,\wj*
\v 43 \wj I was a strangerВҰ18405 and you didn't offer me shelter, I was nakedВҰ18412 and you didn't give me any clothesВҰ18416, and I was sickВҰ18418 and in prisonВҰ18421 and you never visitedВҰ18424 me.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 44 \wj Then they'll also respond, вҖҳ\+nd MasterВҰ18433\+nd*, when did we ever see you hungry or thirstyВҰ18439, or a strangerВҰ18441 or nakedВҰ18443, or sickВҰ18445 or in prisonВҰ18449 and we didn'tВҰ18451 help you?вҖҷ\wj*
\v 45 \wj вҖҳI can assure you,вҖҷ the king answeredВҰ18456, вҖҳthat whenever you failed to help even one of the leastВҰ18469 of theseВҰ18467 others, you failed to serve me.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 46 \x + \xo 25:46: \xt Dan 12:2.\x*\wj ThenВҰ18473 this \+add group\+add* will be sent off to eternal punishmentВҰ18477, butВҰ18480 the guiltless ones \+add will receive\+add* eternal lifeВҰ18483.\wj*вҖқ
\c 26
\s1 The plan to kill Yeshua
\rem /s1 The trial and crucifixion of Jesus; The Plot Against Jesus; The Plot to Kill Jesus
\r (Mark 14:1-2; Luke 22:1-2; Yhn 11:45-53)
\p
\v 1 After \nd Yeshua\nd* had completed his teaching, he told his apprenticesВҰ18502,
\v 2 \x + \xo 26:2: \xt Exo 12:1-27.\x*вҖң\wj The pass-overВҰ18511 celebration is in twoВҰ18507 more daysВҰ18508, andВҰ18513 humanity's child will be handed over to be executedВҰ18521 on a stakeВҰ18521.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 3 At that time, the chief priestsВҰ18525 andВҰ18530 the local eldersВҰ18532 were gatheredВҰ18523 togetherВҰ18523 in the courtyardВҰ18537 of CaiaphasВҰ18542, the chief priestВҰ18539,
\v 4 and they plottedВҰ18544 togetherВҰ18544 to devise a way to arrest \nd YeshuaВҰ18548\nd* so they could execute him.
\v 5 However, theyВҰ18554 decided not to do it during the celebrations so it wouldn't cause a big public disturbance.
\s1 Yeshua is anointed with lotion
\rem /s1 Jesus Is Anointed at Bethany; The Anointing at Bethany
\r (Mark 14:3-9; Yhn 12:1-8)
\p
\v 6 Meanwhile \nd Yeshua\nd* arrived in BethanyВҰ18573 at the houseВҰ18575 of SimonВҰ18576 who \add had previously\add* had leprosyВҰ18579.
\v 7 \x + \xo 26:7: \xt Luk 7:37-38.\x*A womanВҰ18582 \add inside the house\add* came up to him carrying a \add carved\add* alabasterВҰ18584 flaskВҰ18584 of very expensive lotion, which she pouredВҰ18591 over hisВҰ18597 head as he was seated,
\v 8 butВҰ18601 some of his followers were upset when they saw this, and complained, вҖңWhy all this waste?
\v 9 That could have been sold andВҰ18619 raised a lot of money to give to the poor.вҖқ
\p
\v 10 But \nd Yeshua\nd* knew what they were saying and respondedВҰ18627, вҖң\wj Why are youВҰ18631 all causing problems for this woman, becauseВҰ18635 sheВҰ18637 did something beautifulВҰ18636 for me.\wj*
\v 11 \x + \xo 26:11: \xt Deu 15:11.\x*\wj You'll always have the poor with you, but you won'tВҰ18649 always have me \+add around\+add*.\wj*
\v 12 \wj This womanВҰ18655 put this lotion on myВҰ18662 bodyВҰ18661 in a sense as a burial \+add spice\+add*.\wj*
\v 13 \wj I can assure youВҰ18672 all that whereverВҰ18673 the goodВҰ18678 messageВҰ18678 \+add about me\+add* is retold anywhere in the worldВҰ18683, this womanВҰ18688 and what she did will also be mentioned as a memorialВҰ18690 to herВҰ18691.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yudas agrees to turn in Yeshua
\rem /s1 Judas Agrees to Betray Jesus
\r (Mark 14:10-11; Luke 22:3-6)
\p
\v 14 Then one of the twelveВҰ18696 named YudasВҰ18699 IscariotВҰ18700 went to the chiefВҰ18703 priestsВҰ18703
\v 15 \x + \xo 26:15: \xt Zech 11:12.\x*andВҰ18721 asked, How much are you willingВҰ18709 to pay me if I hand him over to you all?вҖқ They offered thirtyВҰ18725 silverВҰ18726 coinsВҰ18726
\v 16 so from thenВҰ18729 on, he was lookingВҰ18733 forВҰ18733 an opportunityВҰ18734 to hand him over.
\s1 Yeshua gets ready to celebrate Passover
\rem /s1 The Lord's Supper; The Last Supper; The Passover with the Disciples; Jesus Eats the Passover Meal with His Disciples
\r (Mark 14:12-21; Luke 22:7-13,21-23; Yhn 13:21-30)
\p
\v 17 On the firstВҰ18741 dayВҰ18741 of the \it Flat Bread Celebration\it*, the \nd Yeshua's\nd* apprenticesВҰ18746 approachedВҰ18744 him andВҰ18740 asked, вҖңWhereВҰ18752 do you want us to prepareВҰ18755 the pass-overВҰ18760 meal for you?вҖқ
\p
\v 18 вҖң\wj Go into the cityВҰ18767 to so-and-so,\wj*вҖқ answered Yeshua, вҖң\wj and tell himВҰ18773 that the teacherВҰ18775 saidВҰ18763, вҖҳMyВҰ18779 timeВҰ18778 is getting close, but I'll celebrate the pass-overВҰ18788 meal with youВҰ18783, along with myВҰ18779 apprenticesВҰ18792.вҖҷ\wj* вҖқ
\p
\v 19 SoВҰ18794 the apprenticesВҰ18798 did as \nd YeshuaВҰ18803\nd* had instructed them, andВҰ18804 thenВҰ18794 theyВҰ18805 preparedВҰ18805 the pass-overВҰ18807 meal.
\p
\v 20 That eveningВҰ18808 as Yeshua was sittingВҰ18811 with the twelveВҰ18814,
\v 21 heВҰ18819 saidВҰ18819 to them while they were still eatingВҰ18817, вҖң\wj I can assure you that one of you is going to turn me in.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 22 They were very upset andВҰ18830 one by one theyВҰ18833 asked himВҰ18835, вҖңSurelyВҰ18839 it won'tВҰ18839 be me, \nd masterВҰ18842\nd*?вҖқ
\p
\v 23 \x + \xo 26:23: \xt Psa 41:9.\x*вҖң\wj It's the one who dippedВҰ18848 his \+add bread\+add* into the bowl at the same time as I did,\wj*вҖқ Yeshua answeredВҰ18845. вҖң\wj He's the one who's going to turn me in.\wj*
\v 24 \wj It's true that humanity's child is goingВҰ18874 \+add to suffer\+add* what has already been writtenВҰ18876 aboutВҰ18877, but on the otherВҰ18881 hand, the end won'tВҰ18898 be good for the man who turns him in, in fact it would have been betterВҰ18894 for him if he'd never been born.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 25 вҖңSurelyВҰ18912 it won'tВҰ18912 be me, honoured \add teacher\add*?вҖқ asked YudasВҰ18907, the one who would hand him in.\f + \fr 26:25 \ft https://www.billmounce.com/monday-with-mounce/Yeshua%E2%80%99-possible-play-judas%E2%80%99-words\f*
\p вҖң\wj You said it,\wj*вҖқ he replied.
\s1 Yeshua shares the bread and the wine
\rem /s1 The Institution of the Lord's Supper
\r (Mark 14:22-26; Luke 22:14-20; 1 Cor. 11:23-25)
\p
\v 26 ThenВҰ18924 during the meal, \nd Yeshua\nd* took some breadВҰ18932 and blessedВҰ18934 \add it\add*, thenВҰ18924 he brokeВҰ18937 it into pieces and gaveВҰ18941 it to his apprenticesВҰ18943, saying, вҖң\wj Take this and eatВҰ18949 itвҖ”it's myВҰ18955 bodyВҰ18954.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 27 ThenВҰ18956 he took a cup \add of wine\add* andВҰ18956 after giving thanksВҰ18961, he shared it with them sayingВҰ18964, вҖң\wj Everyone drinkВҰ18965 some,\wj*
\v 28 \x + \xo 26:28: a \xt Exo 24:8; \xo b \xt Jer 31:31-34.\x*\wj becauseВҰ18970 this is myВҰ18974 blood of the agreement which is \+add about to\+add* be pouredВҰ18983 out for the forgivenessВҰ18985 of the sins of many people.\wj*
\v 29 \wj I can assure you all that I certainly won'tВҰ18992 drink this \+add pass-over\+add* wine again untilВҰ19002 I'm able to drink it together with you all in myВҰ19019 father'sВҰ19018 kingdomВҰ19016.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 30 ThenВҰ19020 theyВҰ19022 sang some songs before heading out of the city to the MountВҰ19025 of OlivesВҰ19027.
\s1 Yeshua predicts Peter's denials
\rem /s1 Jesus Predicts Peter's Denial; Peter's Denial Foretold
\r (Mark 14:27-31; Luke 22:31-34; Yhn 13:36-38)
\p
\v 31 \x + \xo 26:31: \xt Zech 13:7.\x*Then \nd Yeshua\nd* told them, вҖң\wj All of youВҰ19034 will flounder tonight concerning me, becauseВҰ19044 it's been writtenВҰ19043, вҖҳI'll strikeВҰ19045 the shepherdВҰ19047 andВҰ19048 the flockВҰ19054 will be scatteredВҰ19050.вҖҷ\wj*
\v 32 \x + \xo 26:32: \xt Mat 28:16.\x*\wj But afterВҰ19055 I come back to life, I'll go to GalileeВҰ19064 ahead of youВҰ19061 all.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 33 вҖңEven if all the others flounder,вҖқ answeredВҰ19065 PeterВҰ19068, вҖңI won't.вҖқ
\p
\v 34 вҖң\wj I can assure you,\wj*вҖқ responded \nd Yeshua\nd*, вҖң\wj that you'll disown me threeВҰ19100 times tonight beforeВҰ19095 the roosterВҰ19098 crows \+add in the morning\+add*.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 35 вҖңEven if I have to dieВҰ19114 with you,вҖқ said PeterВҰ19108, вҖңI'd certainly never disown you,вҖқ and all the other apprenticesВҰ19125 said likewiseВҰ19120.
\s1 Yeshua prays at Gethsemane
\rem /s1 Jesus Prays in Gethsemane
\r (Mark 14:32-42; Luke 22:39-46)
\p
\v 36 Then they went together to a propertyВҰ19136 named GethsemaneВҰ19138 where he told his apprenticesВҰ19142 to sit down while he went on a little further to pray.
\v 37 He took PeterВҰ19157, Yacob, and Yohan with him, and thenВҰ19154 he was struck by feelings of sorrowВҰ19164 and distressВҰ19166
\v 38 and told them, вҖң\wj MyВҰ19176 soulВҰ19175 is deathlyВҰ19178 sad. Stay here and look out for me.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 39 He went on a littleВҰ19189 further, andВҰ19196 knelt with hisВҰ19194 faceВҰ19193 to the ground, sayingВҰ19197, вҖң\wj MyВҰ19199 fatherВҰ19198, if it's possibleВҰ19201, let me avoid this suffering. HoweverВҰ19209, it's not what I want because I want to do what \+em youВҰ19216\+em* want.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 40 ThenВҰ19217 he went back to the apprenticesВҰ19221, but found them napping andВҰ19217 said to PeterВҰ19231, вҖң\wj Weren't you even able to stay awake for an hourВҰ19238 for me?\wj*
\v 41 \wj Stay alert and pray so that youВҰ19248 all don'tВҰ19246 fall into temptationВҰ19250. Your spiritsВҰ19253 are eagerВҰ19254, but your endurance is lacking.\wj*вҖқ
\p
\v 42 Then he went off a secondВҰ19261 time and prayedВҰ19263, вҖң\wj MyВҰ19268 fatherВҰ19267, if this can'tВҰ19270 be done any other way than me havingВҰ19262 to suffer, then I'll submit to yourВҰ19286 will.\wj*вҖқ
\v 43 Returning again, he foundВҰ19291 the apprentices sleepingВҰ19294 becauseВҰ19296 they were very tired.
\p
\v 44 SoВҰ19301 he left them there andВҰ19301 went back a thirdВҰ19310 timeВҰ19310, praying in the sameВҰ19312 way.
\v 45 Then he went back to his apprenticesВҰ19323 and told them, вҖң\wj You're all sleepingВҰ19328 to get some rest? But look, it's time now, and humanity's child is about to be handed over to sinnersВҰ19346.\wj*
\v 46 \wj Get upвҖ”weВҰ19348 need to move. The one about to turn me in is coming.\wj*вҖқ
\s1 Yeshua is arrested
