\r (Mark 16:14-18; Luke 24:36-49; Yhn 20:19-23; Acts 1:6-8)
\p
\v 16 \x + \xo 28:16: \xt Mat 26:32; Mrk 14:28.\x*The elevenВҰ21482 apprenticesВҰ21483 travelled up to GalileeВҰ21487 to the hill that \nd Yeshua\nd* had \add previously\add* told them to go to,
\v 17 andВҰ21496 when they saw him there, they immediately bowed down to the ground, even though their minds weren't sure \add that it was really him\add*.
\v 18 ThenВҰ21504 \nd Yeshua\nd* came closer and told them, вҖң\wj I have been givenВҰ21511 authorityВҰ21514 over both heavenlyВҰ21517 and earthlyВҰ21522 affairs\wj*
\v 19 \x + \xo 28:19: \xt Acts 1:8.\x*\wj so I want you to leave here and go and trainВҰ21527 followersВҰ21527 in every country, immersingВҰ21531 them \+add in water\+add* with the authority of the fatherВҰ21538 and the son and the holy \+nd spiritВҰ21545\+nd*.\wj*
\v 20 \wj ThenВҰ21553 teachВҰ21546 them to do everything just like I instructedВҰ21551 all of you. And listen, I will be with you all every day right through untilВҰ21563 the end of \+add this\+add* age.\wj*вҖқ
